insert  into `rs_questions_db_24052015`(`id`,`topic_id`,`q_type`,`Introduction`,`Question`,`Op1`,`Op2`,`Op3`,`Op4`,`Answer`,`Solution`,`Difficulty_level`) values (1,1,'1','','<p>A man invests Rs. 24,000 in some shares in the ratio 1: 2: 3 which pay dividends of 10%, 30% and 25% (on his investment) for that year respectively. Find his dividend income in rupees.</p>','<p>6000</p>','<p>6700</p>','<p>5800</p>','<p>7500</p>','3','<p>The dividend paid out by the first type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.1.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"171\" height=\"40\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The dividend paid out by the second type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.1.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"170\" height=\"38\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The dividend paid out by the third type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.1.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"176\" height=\"39\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Total dividend paid out is 400 + 2400 + 3000 = Rs. 5800.</p>','Easy'),(2,1,'1','','<p>6 persons, with varying ages, are standing in queue. After two years, their average age will be 43 and seventh person joined with them. Hence the current average age has become 44. Find the age of seventh person.</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>62</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>52</p>','2','<p>The present average of the 6 persons in the line is 43 - 2 = 41 years.</p>\r\n<p>The average after the seventh person joined them is 44.</p>\r\n<p>So, age of the seventh person is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.2.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"19\" />&nbsp;years.</p>','Easy'),(3,1,'1','','<p>In a group of cows and chicken, the number of legs was 14 more than twice the number of heads. The number of cows was:</p>','<p>6</p>','<p>7</p>','<p>8</p>','<p>Cannot be determined</p>','2','<p>Since each cow has 2 legs more than twice the heads, the number of cows is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.3.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"57\" height=\"38\" />.</p>','Easy'),(4,1,'1','','<p>There are 4 quarts in a gallon. A gallon of petrol sells for Rs.12 and a quart of the same petrol sells for Rs.5. The owner of a rental agency has 6 machines and each machine needs 5 quarts of petrol. What is the minimum average amount of money per quart that he must spend to purchase enough petrol?</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>3.08</p>','<p>3.12</p>','<p>3.2</p>','3','<p>Total petrol required is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.4.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"76\" height=\"18\" />&nbsp;quarts.</p>\r\n<p>The price is gallon is less than that of 4 quarts individually.</p>\r\n<p>So, the smallest price is obtained when we purchase 7 gallons and 2 quarts.</p>\r\n<p>So, total cost is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.4.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"160\" height=\"19\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, average price per quart is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.4.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"84\" height=\"29\" />.</p>','Easy'),(5,1,'1','','<p>The marks obtained by a student in five subjects are 73, 74, 75, 72, 71 and 79. Find the average score.</p>','<p>75</p>','<p>74</p>','<p>73</p>','<p>60</p>','2','<p>The average of a data set <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.5.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"94\" height=\"25\" />, is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.5.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"102\" height=\"38\" />, where x is a random number.</p>\r\n<p>Let x = 70 in this case.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.5.5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"268\" height=\"47\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the actual mean is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.5.6.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"195\" height=\"53\" />.</p>','Easy'),(6,1,'1','','<p>The average income of a group of 10 workers is Rs. 190 and that of another group of 8 workers is Rs. 100. The average income of all the persons is:</p>','<p>120</p>','<p>130</p>','<p>150</p>','<p>165</p>','3','<p>Total income of first group of workers is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.6.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"119\" height=\"23\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Total income of second group of workers is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.6.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"105\" height=\"20\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Average income of the all the groups is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.6.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"198\" height=\"42\" />.</p>','Easy'),(7,1,'1','','<p>There are 40 boys in a class. One boy weighing 60 kg goes away, and at the same time another boy joins the class. If the average weight of the class is thus decreased by 150 grams, the weight of the new boy is:</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>54</p>','<p>42</p>','<p>66</p>','2','<p>The number of boys remains the same. So, the difference in the mean is equal to the change in the values divided by the number of values.</p>\r\n<p>So, change in weight is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.7.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"138\" height=\"40\" />kg. The answer is negative because the average is decreased.</p>\r\n<p>So, weight of the new boy is 60 - 6 = 54 kgs.</p>','Easy'),(8,1,'1','','<p>The average temperature on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday was 37&deg; centigrade. The average temperature on Wednesday, Thursday and Friday was 38&deg; centigrade. If the temperature on Friday was 39&deg; centigrade, the temperature on Tuesday in Celsius was:</p>','<p>36</p>','<p>42</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>38</p>','1','<p>Wednesday and Thursday are common in both the groups.</p>\r\n<p>So, the difference of the temperature of Friday and Tuesday is equal to <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.8.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"152\" height=\"21\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, temperature on Tuesday is equal to <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.8.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"98\" height=\"19\" />.</p>','Easy'),(9,1,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The average age of 60 soldiers in troop is 30 years. If the captain&#039;s age is included, the average age of all of them still remains the same. What is the captain&#039;s age in years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The average does not change if the added values have the same value as the average.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the age of captain is 30 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(10,1,'1','','<p>Two towns A and B are some distance apart. A boy cycles from A to B at a speed of 18 km/hr and then back from B to A at the rate of 12 km/hr. The average speed during the journey is:</p>','<p>15 kmph</p>','<p>14.4 kmph</p>','<p>16.2 kmph</p>','<p>13.6 kmph</p>','2','<p>Average velocity when we travel the same distance, once with a speed <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.10.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"19\" height=\"17\" />&nbsp;and once with a speed <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.10.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"21\" height=\"21\" />&nbsp;is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.10.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"82\" height=\"43\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Here <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.10.4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"95\" height=\"19\" />&nbsp;and <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.10.5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"102\" height=\"20\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.10.6.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"265\" height=\"49\" />.</p>','Easy'),(11,1,'1','','<p>The average marks of 12 students was calculated as 40. But it was later found that marks of one student had been entered wrongly as 42 instead of 54 and of another as 74 instead of 50. The correct average is:</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>39</p>','<p>38</p>','<p>42</p>','2','<p>The number of boys remain the same. So, the difference in the mean is equal to sum of all changes in the values divided by the number of values.</p>\r\n<p>So, change in average is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.11.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"257\" height=\"50\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the new average is marks 40 - 1 = 39 marks.</p>','Easy'),(12,1,'1','','<p>The average age of a husband and a wife who were married seven years ago was 18 years then. What will be the average age of the family now if they have a four years old child?</p>','<p>17</p>','<p>18</p>','<p>19</p>','<p>25</p>','2','<p>The average age of the couple if we do not include the child is &nbsp;18 + 7 = 25 years.</p>\r\n<p>If the 4 year old child is included, then the average becomes <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.12.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"159\" height=\"39\" />&nbsp;years.</p>','Easy'),(13,1,'1','','The sum of two consecutive even numbers is 23 more than the average of these two numbers. What is the second number?','22','24','26','28','2','Average of two consecutive even numbers is the odd number in between them. So, we can easily say that in the present case, the numbers are 22 and 24.','Easy'),(14,1,'1','','<p>The average of seventeen numbers is 11. If the average of first nine is 13 and that of the last nine is 10, the middle number is:</p>','<p>18</p>','<p>13</p>','<p>20</p>','<p>15</p>','3','<p>Here, the sum of all 17 elements is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.14.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"106\" height=\"19\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The sum of the first 9 numbers is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.14.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"99\" height=\"18\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The sum of the last 9 numbers is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.14.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"90\" height=\"18\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The middle number is repeated twice in these two sums. So, the middle number is 117 + 90 - 187 = 20.</p>','Easy'),(15,1,'1','','<p>The average age of 19 students and the principal is 16 years. When the principal&rsquo;s age is excluded, the average age decreases by 1 year. What is the age of the principal?</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>35</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>25</p>','2','<p>The total age of principal and students is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/112.15.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"136\" height=\"21\" />years.</p>\r\n<p>The total age of 