So, when there are 100 boarders, total cost is a + 100b = 500 + (45 &times; 100) = 5000.</p>\r\n<p>So, average charge required is (5000/100) = Rs.50.</p>','Hard'),(42,1,'3','','<p>A 30-litre bucket contains a mixture of milk and water in the ratio 2: 1. A certain quantity of this mixture is replaced by water such that the ratio of milk and water becomes 8: 7. This resultant mixture is added to 20 litres of another mixture containing milk and water in the ratio 3: 1. What is the percentage of milk in the new mixture?</p>','<p>0.5</p>','<p>0.6</p>','<p>0.62</p>','<p>0.65</p>','3','<p>We need not consider ourselves with how much water is replaced because we know the final ratio 8:7.</p>\r\n<p>So, out of a total of 30 + 20 = 50 litres, the amount of milk is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.2.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"149\" height=\"47\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, percentage of milk is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.2.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"117\" height=\"47\" />.</p>','Hard'),(43,1,'3','','<p>Susan works for a book marketing company and gets a stipend of Rs.3800. She also gets commission on books sold at the rate of Rs.8 per copy for first 25 copies, Rs.10 per copy for the next 25 copies, Rs.12 per copy for the next 50, and for every copy sold thereafter, she gets Rs.15 per copy. If in a month she makes Rs.4430, how many books did she sell?</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>65</p>','<p>70</p>','<p>75</p>','2','<p>The commission that she got is Rs. 4430 - 3800 = Rs.630.</p>\r\n<p>Commission for first 25 books is 8 &times; 25 = 200.</p>\r\n<p>Commission for next 25 books is 10 &times; 25 = 250.</p>\r\n<p>Commission for first 50 books is 200 + 250 = 450.</p>\r\n<p>Remaining commission is 630 - 450 = 180 and for the next 50 books, she gets Rs. 12 for each book. So, she sold (180/12) = 15 books after 50.</p>\r\n<p>So, total number of books sold is 65.</p>','Hard'),(44,1,'3','','<p>A shipping clerk has five boxes of different integral but unknown weights. The clerk weighed the boxes in pairs. He obtained the weights, in kg, as 122, 124, 125, 126, 127, 128, 129, 130, 132 and 133. How much would the third heaviest box weigh? (in kg)</p>','<p>63</p>','<p>64</p>','<p>65</p>','<p>66</p>','2','<p>Let the weights in ascending order be A, B, C, D, E.</p>\r\n<p>The maximum possible weight is because of the two heaviest boxes. So, D + E = 133.</p>\r\n<p>The minimum weight is due to the two lightest boxes. So, A + B = 122.</p>\r\n<p>When they are weighed in pairs, each box will feature 4 times in these measurements.<br />So, 4(A + B + C + D + E) = 1276 =&gt; A + B + C + D + E = 319.</p>\r\n<p>So, the weight of third heaviest box is C = 319 - 122 - 133 = 64 kg.</p>','Hard'),(45,1,'3','','<p>The average weight of 5 men is increased by 3 kg when one of them weighing 150 kg is replaced by another person. This new person is again replaced by another person whose weight is 30 kg lower than the person he replaced. What is the overall change in the average due to this dual change?</p>','<p>3 Kg decrease</p>','<p>3 Kg increase</p>','<p>6 Kg increase</p>','<p>6 Kg decrease</p>','1','<p>The change in average due to the second change will be (30/5) = 6 kg decrease.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total average decrease is -3 + 6 = 3 kg. The first value is negative because there is an increase in that case.</p>','Hard'),(46,1,'3','','<p>There are five boxes in a cargo hold. The weight of the first box is 100 kg and the weight of the second box is 20% higher than the weight of the third box, whose weight is 25% higher than the first box&rsquo;s weight. The fourth box at 240 kg is 20% lighter than the fifth box. Find the difference in the average weight of the four heaviest boxes and the four lightest boxes</p>','<p>30 Kg</p>','<p>40 Kg</p>','<p>50 Kg</p>','<p>60 Kg</p>','3','<p>The weight of first box is 100 kg. The weight of third box is (125/100) &times; 100 = 125 kg. The weight of second box is (120/100) &times; 125 = 150 kg.</p>\r\n<p>The weight of fourth box is 250 kg. It is 20% lighter than 5th box. Let its weight be w. So, (80/100) w = 240 =&gt; w = 300 kg.</p>\r\n<p>The difference in the averages required is equal to one fourth the difference in weights of the heaviest and the lightest boxes. So, the required difference is (300 - 100)/4 = 50 kg.</p>','Hard'),(47,1,'3','','<p>A batsman makes a score of 270 runs in the 87th inning and thus increases his average by a certain number of runs that is a whole number. Find the possible values of the new average</p>','<p>96</p>','<p>97</p>','<p>98</p>','<p>99</p>','3','<p>Let his initial average be A. The final average is A+n, n&isin;N.</p>\r\n<p>So, 86A + 270 = 87(A + n) =&gt; A = 270 - 87n.</p>\r\n<p>So, possible values of A are 270 - 87 = 183; 270 - 174 = 96; 270 - 261 = 9.</p>\r\n<p>So, possible values for new average is 184, 98, 12.</p>','Hard'),(48,1,'3','','<p>There were 40 students in a hostel. Due to the admission of 10 new students, the expenses of the mess increase by 60 per day while the average expenditure per head diminished by 3. What was the original expenditure of the mess?</p>','<p>840</p>','<p>900</p>','<p>870</p>','<p>740</p>','1','<p>Let the expense per student for the mess be A initially. The final average is A - 3. The mess expenses increased by a total of Rs. 60.</p>\r\n<p>So, 40A + 60 = 50(A - 3) =&gt; 10A = 210 =&gt; A = 21.</p>\r\n<p>Original expenditure of mess is 40A = 840 rupees.</p>','Hard'),(49,1,'3','','<p>A team of miners planned to mine 1800 tons of ore during a certain number of days. Due to technical difficulties in one-third of the planned number of days, the team was able to achieve an output of 20 tons of ore less than the planned output for each day. To make up for this, the team overachieved for the rest of the days by 20 tons. The end result was that the team completed the task one day ahead of time. How many tons of ore did the team initially plan to ore per day?</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>100</p>','<p>150</p>','<p>200</p>','2','<p>Let they plan to extract x tons of ore each day.</p>\r\n<p>So, number of days required is 1800/x.</p>\r\n<p>The initial one third of the days, the output per day is (x - 20). So, after the one third days, the amount of ore still to be mined is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.9.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"264\" height=\"47\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Now, for the remaining days, production is (x + 20) tons per day and the work is finished one day before time.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.9.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"499\" height=\"54\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.9.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"29\" />&nbsp;tons.</p>','Hard'),(50,1,'3','','<p>On an average, three litres of milk and one litre of water are needed to be mixed to make 1 kg of sweet of type A and 2 litres of milk and 2 litres of water are needed to be mixed to make 1 kg of sweet of type B. How many kilograms of sweet of type B was manufactured if it is known that 155 litres of milk and 105 litres of water were used?</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>35</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>45</p>','3','<p>x kg of type A sweet and y kg of type B sweet is prepared.</p>\r\n<p>So, 3x + 2y = 155; x + 2y = 105 =&gt; 2x = 50 =&gt; x = 25 =&gt; y = 40.</p>\r\n<p>So, 40 kg of sweet B is prepared.</p>','Hard'),(51,1,'3','','<p>One fashion house has to make 810 dresses and another one 900 dresses during the same period of time. In the first house, the order was ready 3 days ahead of time and in the second house, 6 days ahead of time. How many dresses did the first fashion house make in a day if the second house made 21 dresses more a day than the first?</p>','<p>54</p>','<p>57</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>63</p>','1','<p>The time difference in between both the houses is 3 days. Let us assume the first house made x dresses per day. So the second house made x + 21 dresses each day.</p>\r\n<p>So, we can say that <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.11.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"503\" height=\"38\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.11.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"30\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the first shop makes 54 dresses per day.</p>','Hard'),(52,1,'3','','<p>An enterprise got a bonus and decided to share it in equal parts between the exemplary workers. It tuned out. However, that there were 3 more exemplary workers than it had been assumed. In that case, each of them would have got 4 rupees less. The administration had found the possibility to increase the total sum of the bonus by 90 rupees and as a result each exemplary worker got 25 rupees. How many people got the bonus?</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>15</p>','<p>18</p>','<p>21</p>','3','<p>If there are x rupees as bonus and the company thought that there are n exemplary workers, then, we can say that, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.12.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"42\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Now, if the bonus increases by 90, each of the (n + 3) members will get Rs. 25 each.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.12.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"586\" height=\"27\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, total number of people getting the bonus is 15 + 3 = 18.</p>','Hard'),(53,1,'3','','<p>2 passengers have together 560 kilograms of luggage and are charged for the excess above the weight allowed at 10$ and 26$. If all the luggage had belonged to one of them he would have to pay 46$. The amount of luggage each passenger is allowed without any charge is</p>','<p>100 Kg</p>','<p>75 Kg</p>','<p>125 Kg</p>','<p>150 Kg</p>','1','<p>Let the amount of luggage allowed without charge be x kgs.</p>\r\n<p>So, if there are 2 passengers, they will be charged for (560 - 2x) kg of the luggage.</p>\r\n<p>If there is only one passenger, he is charged for (560 - x) kg of luggage.</p>\r\n<p>The charge is proportional to the excess luggage.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.13.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"311\" height=\"49\" />.</p>','Hard'),(54,1,'3','','<p>Mohan is a carpenter who specialises in making chairs. For every assignment he undertakes, he charges his commission and cost. His commission is fixed and equals Rs.560 per assignment while the cost equals Rs.2n&sup2; where n is the total number of chairs he makes. If for a certain assignment the average cost per chair is not more than Rs.68 then the minimum and maximum possible number of chairs in the assignment are, respectively.</p>','<p>14, 20</p>','<p>14, 21</p>','<p>13, 21</p>','<p>14, 19</p>','1','<p>Since his average cost is not more than Rs. 68, total price he takes should not be more than Rs. 68n when he makes 2 chairs.</p>\r\n<p>His total price for n chairs will be <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.14.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"79\" height=\"25\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, we can say that&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.14.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"376\" height=\"23\" />.</p>','Hard'),(55,1,'3','','<p>400 students took a mock exam in Delhi. 60% of the boys and 80% of the girls cleared the cut off in the examination. If the total percentage of students qualifying is 65%, how many girls appeared in the examination?</p>','<p>100</p>','<p>125</p>','<p>150</p>','<p>200</p>','1','<p>Since the difference from the boys percentage to the average is 5% and that from girls cutoff to the average is 15%, we can say that ratio of the number of girls that have written the exam to the number of boys is (5/15) = (1/3).</p>\r\n<p>Since the total strength is 400, the number of girls is (1/4) &times; 400 = 100. The remaining 300 are boys.</p>','Hard'),(56,1,'3','','<p>Grass in lawn grows equally thick and in a uniform rate. It takes 24 days for 70 cows and 60 days for 30 cows to eat the whole of the grass. How many cows are needed to eat the grass in 96 days?</p>','<p>15</p>','<p>20</p>','<p>25</p>','<p>18</p>','2','<p>Let the initial amount of grass be a and amount that grows each day be b.</p>\r\n<p>So, we can say that a + 24b = 70 &times; 24 and a + 60b = 30 &times; 60.</p>\r\n<p>From these two relations, we can say 36b = 120 =&gt; b = 10/3 =&gt; a = 1600.</p>\r\n<p>So, the number of cows that can eat for 96 days is (a + 96b)/96 = (1600 + 320)/96 = 20.</p>','Hard'),(57,1,'3','','<p>The sum of three numbers is 98. If the ratio between the first and second is 2: 3 and that between the second and the third is 5: 8, then the second number is</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>45</p>','<p>54</p>','<p>15</p>','1','<p>Since the numbers involved for the second number in the two cases are 3 and 5, let us assume that the second number is 15k. So, the first number will be (2/3) &times; 15k = 10k and the third number will be (8/5) &times; 15k = 24k.</p>\r\n<p>So, 10k + 15k + 24k = 49k = 98 =&gt; k = 2.</p>\r\n<p>So, the second number is 15k = 30.</p>','Hard'),(58,1,'3','','<p>Out of three numbers, the first is twice the second and three times the third. The average of the three numbers is 88. The smallest number is</p>','<p>48</p>','<p>72</p>','<p>64</p>','<p>40</p>','1','<p>If the first number is x, then the second number is x/2 and the third number is x/3. The third number is the smallest number.</p>\r\n<p>The average of all three is 88.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/114.18.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"447\" height=\"53\" />.</p>','Hard'),(59,1,'3','','<p>The average of the set of data 6, 7, 9, 9, 5, 8, 7, 10, 6, 8, 7, 6, 5, 9, 10, 8, 6, 9 is</p>','<p>11</p>','<p>7.5</p>','<p>5</p>','<p>10</p>','2','<p>For a data with unequal values, the average will always be inside the range of the data.</p>\r\n<p>So, the average can only be 7.5 because, 11 is outside the range and 5 and 10 are the extremes of the range.</p>','Hard'),(60,1,'3','','<p>The average of 4 numbers is 17, that of the first two is 18 and that of the first three is 16. Find the difference between the third and the fourth number.</p>','<p>8</p>','<p>10</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>Data insufficient</p>','1','<p>The fourth number is (4 &times; 17) - (3 &times; 16) = 20.</p>\r\n<p>The third number is (3 &times; 16) - (2 &times; 18) = 12.</p>\r\n<p>So, the difference is 20 - 12 = 8.</p>','Hard'),(61,1,'4','','<p>Ramesh invests Rs. 18,000 in some shares in the ratio 1: 3: 4 which pay dividends of 20%, 40% and 30% (on his investment) for that year respectively. Find his dividend income in rupees.</p>','<p>6150</p>','<p>6050</p>','<p>5950</p>','<p>5850</p>','3','<p>The dividend paid out by the first type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.1.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"166\" height=\"40\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The dividend paid out by the second type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.1.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"167\" height=\"41\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The dividend paid out by the third type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.1.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"168\" height=\"44\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Total dividend paid out is 450 + 2700 + 2700 = Rs.5950.</p>','Easy'),(62,1,'4','','<p>Suresh invests Rs. 25,000 in some shares in the ratio 1: 2: 7 which pay dividends of 20%, 30% and 50% (on his investment) for that year respectively. Find his dividend income in rupees</p>','<p>6000</p>','<p>6700</p>','<p>10750</p>','<p>7500</p>','3','<p>The dividend paid out by the first type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.2.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"166\" height=\"49\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The dividend paid out by the second type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.2.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"47\" />.</p>\r\n<p>The dividend paid out by the third type is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.2.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"176\" height=\"46\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Total dividend paid out is 500 + 1500 + 8750 = Rs.10750.</p>','Easy'),(63,1,'4','','<p>8 persons, with varying ages, are standing in queue. Their average age is 45 and ninth person joined with them. Hence the current average age has become 49. Find the age of ninth person?</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>81</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>52</p>','2','<p>The present average age of the 8 persons in the line is 45 years.</p>\r\n<p>The average after the ninth person joined them is 49.</p>\r\n<p>So, age of the ninth person is (49 x 9) - (45 x 8) = 441 - 360 = 81 years.</p>','Easy'),(64,1,'4','','<p>10 persons, with varying ages, are standing in queue. After four years, their average age will be 60 and eleventh person joined with them. Hence the current average age has become 56. Find the age of eleventh person?</p>','<p>58</p>','<p>56</p>','<p>54</p>','<p>52</p>','2','<p>The present average of the 10 persons in the line is 60 - 4 = 56 years.</p>\r\n<p>The average after the eleventh person joined them is 56.</p>\r\n<p>Since there is no change in average, the age of the person should be the same as the average.</p>','Easy'),(65,1,'4','','<p>The marks obtained by a student in six subjects are 83, 84, 85, 82, 81 and 89. Find the average score.</p>','<p>75</p>','<p>84</p>','<p>73</p>','<p>60</p>','2','<p>The average score always lies with the range of the data.</p>','Easy'),(66,1,'4','','<p>The average age of a family of 6 members is 30 years. If the age of the youngest member be 7 years, what was the average age of the family just before the birth of the youngest member?</p>','<p>24</p>','<p>27.6</p>','<p>23</p>','<p>23.5</p>','2','<p>The average age of the family just after the birth of the boy is 30 - 7 = 23 years.</p>\r\n<p>Just before it, there will be only 5 members instead of 6.</p>\r\n<p>So, average just before his birth is (23 &times; 6)/5 = 138/5 = 27.6 years.</p>','Easy'),(67,1,'4','','<p>There are 50 boys in a class. One boy weighing 70 kg goes away, and at the same time another boy joins the class. If the average weight of the class is thus decreased by 200 grams, the weight of the new boy is</p>','<p>65</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>42</p>','<p>66</p>','2','<p>The number of boys remains the same. So, the difference in the mean is equal to the change in the values divided by the number of values.</p>\r\n<p>So, change in weight is (-200/1000) &times; 50 = -10 kg. The answer is negative because the average decreased.</p>\r\n<p>So, weight of the new boy is 70 - 10 = 60 kgs.</p>','Easy'),(68,1,'4','','<p>The average age of a husband and a wife who were married five years ago was 15 years then. What will be the average age of the family now if they have a two years old child?</p>','<p>17</p>','<p>14</p>','<p>19</p>','<p>25</p>','2','<p>The average age of the couple if we do not include the child is 15 + 5 = 20 years.</p>\r\n<p>If the 2 year old child is included, then the average becomes [(20 x 2)+ 2]/3 = 14 years.</p>','Easy'),(69,1,'4','','<p>The average of 18 numbers is 10. If the average of first seven is 13 and that of the last twelve is 7, the seventh number is</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>33</p>','<p>45</p>','<p>15</p>','3','<p>Here, the sum of all 18 elements is 18 x 10 = 180.</p>\r\n<p>The sum of the first 7 numbers is 7 x 13 = 91.</p>\r\n<p>The sum of the last 12 numbers is 7 x 12 = 84.</p>\r\n<p>The seventh number is repeated twice in these two sums. So, the seventh number is 180 - 91 - 84 = 5.</p>','Easy'),(70,1,'4','','<p>The average of 7 consecutive numbers is 20. The highest of these numbers will be</p>','<p>25</p>','<p>23</p>','<p>19</p>','<p>21</p>','2','<p>The average of a group of odd number of consecutive numbers is the middle number.</p>\r\n<p>So, middle number is 20. The highest number is 20 + 3 = 23.</p>','Easy'),(71,1,'4','','<p>The average of 9 consecutive numbers is 24. What is the difference between the largest number and the smallest number?</p>','<p>28</p>','<p>8</p>','<p>20</p>','<p>16</p>','2','<p>Since the 9 numbers are consecutive, the required difference is equal to 9 - 1 = 8.</p>','Easy'),(72,1,'4','','<p>Six years ago, the average age of a family of 6 members was 17 years. A baby having been born, the average age of the family last year is 19. What is the age of the baby?</p>','<p>4</p>','<p>1</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>2</p>','4','<p>Average age of the family excluding the baby now is 17 + 6 = 23.</p>\r\n<p>Average today including the baby is 20. So, age of the baby is (20 x 7) - (23 x 6) = 2 years.</p>','Easy'),(73,1,'4','','<p>Six years ago, the average age of a family of 8 members was 26 years. A baby having been born, the average of the family is 29 years. What is the age of the baby?</p>','<p>5</p>','<p>4</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>2</p>','1','<p>Average age of the family excluding the baby now is 26 + 6 = 32.</p>\r\n<p>Average today including the baby is 29. So, age of the baby is (29 x 9) - (32 x 8) = 5 years.</p>','Easy'),(74,1,'4','','<p>The cost of producing a photograph is partly fixed, i.e. Rs. 600 for plate making, and partly variable, i.e. Rs. 2.75 per copy. What is the least number of copies that must be sold at Rs. 8.75 each to ensure a</p>','<p>100</p>','<p>101</p>','<p>89</p>','<p>58</p>','2','<p>Total selling price for n copies is S = 8.75n.</p>\r\n<p>Total cost price for n copies is C = 600 + 2.75n.</p>\r\n<p>According to the question, S = C =&gt; 8.75n = 600 + 2.75n.</p>\r\n<p>So, 6n = 600 =&gt; n = 100.</p>\r\n<p>Least number of copies to get actual profit is 101.</p>','Medium'),(75,1,'4','','<p>The cost of printing a magazine is partly fixed, i.e. Rs. 240 for setting up the apparatus, and partly variable, i.e. Rs. 1.85 per copy. What is the least number of copies that must be sold at Rs. 5.85 each to ensure a profit?</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>61</p>','<p>19</p>','<p>48</p>','2','<p>Total selling price for n copies is S = 5.85n.</p>\r\n<p>Total cost price for n copies is C = 240 + 1.85n.</p>\r\n<p>According to the question, S = C =&gt; 5.85n = 240 + 1.85n.</p>\r\n<p>So, 4n = 240 =&gt; n = 60.</p>\r\n<p>Least number of copies to get actual profit is 61.</p>','Medium'),(76,1,'4','','<p>Two liquids A and B are in the ratio 5: 2 in container 1 and in the ratio 2:5 in container 2. In what ratio should the contents of the two containers be mixed so as to obtain a mixture of A and B in the ratio 1: 2?</p>','<p>1: 8</p>','<p>8: 1</p>','<p>4: 1</p>','<p>2: 3</p>','1','<p>Let the required ratio be m:n.</p>\r\n<p>Total quantity of A is 5m + 2n.</p>\r\n<p>Total quantity of B is 2m + 5n.</p>\r\n<p>Ratio of A to B is 1:2.</p>\r\n<p>So, 2 x (5m + 2n) = 2m + 5n =&gt; 8m = n.</p>','Medium'),(77,1,'4','','<p>Two liquids A and B are in the ratio 7: 2 in container 1 and in the ratio 2: 4 in container 2. In what ratio should the contents of the two containers be mixed so as to obtain a mixture of A and B in the ratio 1: 1?</p>','<p>2: 5</p>','<p>2: 1</p>','<p>1: 2</p>','<p>5: 2</p>','1','<p>Let the required ratio be m:n.</p>\r\n<p>Total quantity of A is 7m + 2n.</p>\r\n<p>Total quantity of B is 2m + 4n.</p>\r\n<p>Ratio of A to B is 1:1.</p>\r\n<p>So, 7m + 2n = 2m + 4n =&gt; 5m = 2n.</p>','Medium'),(78,1,'4','','<p>Visitors to a show were charged Rs.25.00 each on the first day, Rs. 12.50 on the second day, Rs. 3.00 on the third day and total attendance on the three days were in the ratio 1:4:5 respectively. The average charge per person for the whole show is</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>4.5</p>','<p>9</p>','<p>7.5</p>','3','<p>In average problems, ratio can be taken as the actual representation.</p>\r\n<p>Average charge per person is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.18.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"398\" height=\"46\" />.</p>','Medium'),(79,1,'4','','<p>In a group of 11 members, the average age is 26 years. Out of these, the average of three groups of three players each are 24 years, 26 years and 28 years. In the remaining two persons, one is 12 years younger than the other. The age of the older person is</p>','<p>33 years</p>','<p>28 years</p>','<p>27 years</p>','<p>36 years</p>','3','<p>Let the age of youngest player be x and so, the age of the older one is (x + 12).</p>\r\n<p>Now, total age of 11 players is 26 x 11 = 286.</p>\r\n<p>Age of 9 players among them is (24 x 3) + (26 x 3) + (28 x 3) = 234.</p>\r\n<p>So, age of captain and youngest player is 2x + 12 = 286 - 234 = 52 =&gt; x = 15.</p>\r\n<p>So, age of the older person is 15 + 12 = 27 years.</p>','Medium'),(80,1,'4','','<p>In a management entrance test, a student scores 3 marks for every correct answer and loses 0.5 marks for every wrong answer. A student attempts all the 100 questions and scores exactly 195 marks. The number of questions he answered correctly was</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>70</p>','4','<p>If he answers x questions correctly, then (100 - x) questions are wrong.</p>\r\n<p>So, total number of marks is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.20.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"328\" height=\"42\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, he correctly answers 70 questions.</p>','Medium'),(81,1,'4','','<p>In an exam, a student scores 2 marks for every correct answer and loses 0.5 marks for every wrong answer. A student attempts all the 120 questions and scores exactly 100 marks. The number of questions he answered correctly was</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>64</p>','<p>74</p>','3','<p>If he answers x questions correctly, then (120 - x) questions are wrong.</p>\r\n<p>So, total number of marks is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.21.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"43\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, he correctly answers 64 questions.</p>','Medium'),(82,1,'4','','<p>In a bag, there are 100 coins of Re. 1, 50 p and 25 p denominations. If the total value of coins is Rs. 50 and the number of Rs. 1 coins are the same as number of 50 p coins, then find how many rupees can be constituted by 50 p coins.</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>12.5</p>','<p>25</p>','<p>50</p>','2','<p>Let there be x Rs. 1 coins and y 25 p coins. So there are x 50p coins.</p>\r\n<p>So, number of coins is x + x + y = 100 =&gt; 2x + y = 100.</p>\r\n<p>Value of coins is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.22.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"353\" height=\"45\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So x = y/2 =&gt; 4x = 100 =&gt; x = 25.</p>\r\n<p>So, 12.50 rupees can be made with 50 p coins.</p>','Medium'),(83,1,'4','','<p>In a bag, there are 200 coins of Re. 1, 50 p and 25 p denominations. If the total value of coins is Rs. 120 and the number of Rs. 1 coins are two times the number of 50 p coins, then find how many rupees can be constituted by 50 p coins.</p>','<p>20</p>','<p>25</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>35</p>','1','<p>Let there be x 50p coins and y 25 p coins. So there are 2x Rs. 1 coins.</p>\r\n<p>So, number of coins is x + 2x + y = 200 =&gt; 3x + y = 200.</p>\r\n<p>Value of coins is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.23.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"376\" height=\"48\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So 10x + y = 480 =&gt; 7x = 280 =&gt; x = 40.</p>\r\n<p>So, 20 rupees can be made with 50 p coins.</p>','Medium'),(84,1,'4','','<p>With an average speed of 60kmph, a train reaches its destination in time. If it goes with an average speed of 40 kmph, it is late by 10 minutes. The length of the total journey is</p>','<p>30 Km</p>','<p>20 Km</p>','<p>10 Km</p>','<p>40 Km</p>','2','<p>Let the length of journey be d. The time difference in both the cases is 10 mins.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.24.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"320\" height=\"45\" />&nbsp;km.</p>','Medium'),(85,1,'4','','<p>With an average speed of 30kmph, a train reaches its destination in time. If it goes with an average speed of 20 kmph, it is late by 6 minutes. The length of the total journey is</p>','<p>20 Km</p>','<p>9 Km</p>','<p>10 Km</p>','<p>40 Km</p>','2','<p>Let the length of journey be d. The time difference in both the cases is 6 mins.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.25.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"323\" height=\"44\" />.</p>','Medium'),(86,1,'4','','<p>One-fourth of a certain journey is covered at the rate of 30 km/h. one-fourth at the rate of 50 km/h and the rest at 20 km/h. Find the average speed for the whole journey.</p>','<p>28.75</p>','<p>26.08</p>','<p>32.67</p>','<p>25.67</p>','2','<p>If the total length of journey is d, then average speed is</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.26.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"624\" height=\"93\" />.</p>','Medium'),(87,1,'4','','<p>In an exam, the average was found to be x marks. After deducting computational error, the average marks of 60 candidates got reduced from 85 to 65. The average thus came down by 12 marks. The numbers of candidates who took the exam were</p>','<p>80</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>120</p>','<p>150</p>','2','<p>The number of boys remains the same. So, the difference in the mean is equal to sum of all changes in the values divided by the number of values.</p>\r\n<p>So, if the total number of students is n, then the change in average is (20 x 60)/n = 12 =&gt; n = 100.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total number of students is 100.</p>','Medium'),(88,1,'4','','<p>The average age of a group of persons going for a picnic is 25 years. 30 new persons with an average age of 12.5 years join the group on the spot due to which the average of the group becomes 30 years. Find the number of persons initially going for the picnic.</p>','<p>100</p>','<p>95</p>','<p>105</p>','<p>120</p>','3','<p>Total age of first group, if there are n persons is 25n.</p>\r\n<p>Total age of the second group is 30 x 12.5 = 375.</p>\r\n<p>So, average age of all groups is (25n + 375)/(30 + n) = 30 =&gt; 5n = 900 - 375 = 525 =&gt; n = 105.</p>\r\n<p>So, number of persons in the first group is 105.</p>','Medium'),(89,1,'4','','<p>The total expenses of a boarding house are partly fixed and partly variable with the number of boarders. The charge is Rs.70 per head when there are 50 boarders and Rs.60 when there are 100 boarders. Find the charge per head when there are 200 boarders.</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>55</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>45</p>','2','<p>There will be a fixed cost for all the students combined. Let it be a. There will be variable cost per student which will change with the number of students. Let the cost per student be b.</p>\r\n<p>Initially when there are 50 boarders, total cost is a + 50b = (70 x 50) = 3500.</p>\r\n<p>When there are 100 boarders, total cost is a + 100b = (60 x 100) = 6000.</p>\r\n<p>So, 50b = 2500 =&gt; b = 50 =&gt; a = 1000.</p>\r\n<p>So, when there are 200 boarders, total cost is a + 200b = 1000 + (50 x 200) = 11000.</p>\r\n<p>So, average charge required is (11000/200) = Rs.55.</p>','Hard'),(90,1,'4','','<p>A 30-litre bucket contains a mixture of milk and water in the ratio 4:1. This resultant mixture is added to 20 litres of another mixture containing milk and water in the ratio 3: 1. What is the percentage of milk in the new mixture?</p>','<p>0.75</p>','<p>0.76</p>','<p>0.78</p>','<p>0.8</p>','3','<p>The ratio of milk to water in both the containers is 4:1 for 30 litres and 3:1 for 20 litres.</p>\r\n<p>So, out of a total of 30 + 20 = 50 litres, the amount of milk is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.30.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"144\" height=\"47\" />&nbsp;litres.</p>\r\n<p>So, percentage of milk is (39/50) x 100 = 78%.</p>','Hard'),(91,1,'4','','<p>Susan works for a book marketing company and gets a stipend of Rs.5000. She also gets commission on every book sold after the first 25 books. The commission is Rs.10 per copy for the first 25 copies, Rs.15 per copy for the next 25 copies, Rs.20 per copy for the next 50, and for every copy sold thereafter, she gets Rs.25 per copy. If in a month she makes Rs.5885, how many books did she sell?</p>','<p>85</p>','<p>88</p>','<p>90</p>','<p>87</p>','2','<p>The commission that she got is Rs.5885 - 5000 = Rs.885.</p>\r\n<p>Commission for first 25 books is 10 x 25 = 250.</p>\r\n<p>Commission for next 25 books is 15 x 25 = 375.</p>\r\n<p>So, Commission for 50 books is 625.</p>\r\n<p>Remaining commission is 885 - 625 = 260 and for the next 50 books, she gets Rs. 20 for each book.</p>\r\n<p>So, she sold 260/20 = 13 books after 50.</p>\r\n<p>She gets no commission for the first 25 books.</p>\r\n<p>So, total number of books sold is 25 + 50 + 13 = 88.</p>','Hard'),(92,1,'4','','<p>A shipping clerk has five boxes of different integral but unknown weights. The clerk weighed the boxes in pairs. He obtained the weights, in kg, as 122, 124, 125, 126, 127, 128, 129, 130, 132 and 133. How much would the heaviest box weigh? (in kg)</p>','<p>65</p>','<p>66</p>','<p>67</p>','<p>68</p>','2','<p>Let the weights in ascending order be A, B, C, D, E.</p>\r\n<p>The maximum possible weight is because of the two heaviest boxes. So, D + E = 133.</p>\r\n<p>The minimum weight is due to the two lightest boxes. So, A + B = 122.</p>\r\n<p>When they are weighed in pairs, each box will feature 4 times in these measurements.</p>\r\n<p>So, 4(A + B + C + D + E) = 1276 =&gt; A + B + C + D + E = 319.</p>\r\n<p>So, the weight of third heaviest box is C = 319 - 122 - 133 = 64 kg.</p>\r\n<p>The second highest reading will be when the third highest and the heaviest box are weighed. So, the weight of the heaviest box is 132 - 64 = 68.</p>','Hard'),(93,1,'4','','<p>The average weight of 5 men is increased by 2 kg when one of them weighing 100 kg is replaced by another person. This new person is again replaced by another person whose weight is 20 kg lower than the person he replaced. What is the overall change in the average due to this dual change?</p>','<p>3 Kg decrease</p>','<p>3 Kg increase</p>','<p>6 Kg increase</p>','<p>6 Kg decrease</p>','4','<p>The change in average due to the second change will be (20/5) = 4 kg decrease.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total average decrease is 2 + 4 = 6 kg.</p>','Hard'),(94,1,'4','','<p>A batsman makes a score of 77 runs in the 15th inning and thus increases his average by a certain number of runs that is a whole number. Find the possible values of the new average</p>','<p>47</p>','<p>49</p>','<p>48</p>','<p>50</p>','2','<p>Let his initial average be A. The final average is A + n; n&isin;N.</p>\r\n<p>So, 14A + 77 = 15(A + n) =&gt; A = 77 - 15n.</p>\r\n<p>So, possible values of A are 77 - 15 = 62; 77 - 30 = 47; 77 - 45 = 32; 77 - 60 = 17; 77 - 75 = 2.</p>\r\n<p>So, possible values for new average is 62 + 1 = 63, 47 + 2 = 49, 32 + 3 = 35, 17 + 4 = 21, 2 + 5 = 7.</p>','Hard'),(95,1,'4','','<p>A person having a weight of 120 kg joins a group already having 32 members and thus increases the average weight of the group by a certain number of runs that is a whole number. Find the possible values of the new average</p>','<p>54</p>','<p>58</p>','<p>56</p>','<p>60</p>','3','<p>Let his initial average be A. The final average is A+n; n&isin;N.</p>\r\n<p>So, 32A + 120 = 33(A + n) =&gt; A = 120 - 33n.</p>\r\n<p>So, possible values of A are 120 - 33 = 87; 120 - 66 = 54; 120 - 99 = 21.</p>\r\n<p>So, possible values for new average is 87 + 1 = 88, 54 + 2 = 56 and 21 + 3 = 24.</p>','Hard'),(96,1,'4','','<p>There were 30 students in a hostel. Due to the admission of 5 new students, the expenses of the mess increase by 50 per day while the average expenditure per head diminished by 5. What was the original expenditure of the mess?</p>','<p>1350</p>','<p>1400</p>','<p>1450</p>','<p>1550</p>','1','<p>Let the expense per student for the mess be A initially. The final average is A - 3. The mess expenses increased by a total of Rs. 60.</p>\r\n<p>So, 30A + 50 = 35(A - 5) =&gt; 5A = 50 + 175 = 225 =&gt; A = 45.</p>\r\n<p>Original expenditure of mess is 30A = 1350 rupees.</p>','Hard'),(97,1,'4','','<p>On an average, three litres of milk and 2 litres of water are needed to be mixed to make 1 kg of sweet of type A and 1 litre of milk and 4 litres of water are needed to be mixed to make 1 kg of sweet of type B. How many kilograms of sweet of type B was manufactured if it is known that 110 litres of milk and 140 litres of water were used?</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>25</p>','<p>20</p>','<p>35</p>','3','<p>x kg of type A sweet and y kg of type B sweet is prepared.</p>\r\n<p>So, 3x + y = 110; 2x + 4y = 140 =&gt; x = 30 =&gt; y = 20.</p>\r\n<p>So, 20 kg of sweet B is prepared.</p>','Hard'),(98,1,'4','','<p>2 passengers have together 420 kilograms of luggage and are charged for the excess above the weight allowed at 10$ and 26$. If all the luggage had belonged to one of them he would have to pay 46$. The amount of luggage each passenger is allowed without any charge is</p>','<p>75 Kg</p>','<p>100 Kg</p>','<p>125 Kg</p>','<p>150 Kg</p>','1','<p>Let the amount of luggage allowed without charge be x kgs.</p>\r\n<p>So, if there are 2 passengers, they will be charged for (560 - 2x) kg of the luggage.</p>\r\n<p>If there is only one passenger, he is charged for (560 - x) kg of luggage.</p>\r\n<p>The charge is proportional to the excess luggage.</p>\r\n<p>So, (420 - 2x)/(420 - x) = 36/46 =&gt; 4200 = 56x =&gt; x = 75 kg.</p>','Hard'),(99,1,'4','','<p>Mohan is a carpenter who specialises in making chairs. For every assignment he undertakes, he charges his commission and cost. His commission is fixed and equals Rs.750 per assignment while the cost equals Rs.2n&sup2; where n is the total number of chairs he makes. If for a certain assignment the average cost per chair is not more than Rs.80 then the minimum and maximum possible number of chairs in the assignment are, respectively.</p>','<p>15, 25</p>','<p>14, 25</p>','<p>14, 26</p>','<p>14, 24</p>','1','<p>Since his average cost is not more than Rs. 80, total price he takes should not be more than Rs. 80n when he makes 2 chairs.</p>\r\n<p>His total price for n chairs will be 750 + 2n<sup>2</sup>.</p>\r\n<p>So, we can say that <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/115.39.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"376\" height=\"24\" />.</p>','Hard'),(100,1,'4','','<p>400 students took a mock exam in Delhi. 50% of the boys and 60% of the girls cleared the cut off in the examination. If the total percentage of students qualifying is 52%, how many boys appeared in the examination?</p>','<p>320</p>','<p>300</p>','<p>280</p>','<p>325</p>','1','<p>Since the difference from the boys percentage to the average is 2% and that from girls cutoff to the average is 8%, we can say that ratio of the number of boys that have written the exam to the number of girls is 8/2 = 4:1.</p>\r\n<p>Since the total strength is 400, the number of boys is (4/5) x 400 = 320.</p>','Hard'),(101,1,'4','','<p>The sum of three numbers is 183. If the ratio between the first and second is 2: 5 and that between the second and the third is 3: 8, then the first number is</p>','<p>18</p>','<p>45</p>','<p>120</p>','<p>36</p>','1','<p>Since in the numbers involved, the second number in the two cases are 3 and 5, let us assume that the second number is 15k. So, the first number will be (2/5) x 15k = 6k and the third number will be (8/3) x 15k = 40k.</p>\r\n<p>So, 6k + 15k + 40k = 61k = 183 =&gt; k = 3.</p>\r\n<p>So, the first number is 6k = 18.</p>','Hard'),(102,2,'1','','<p>X and Y are two stations 600 km apart. A train stats from X and moves towards Y at the rate of 25 km/hr. Another train stats from Y at the rate of 35 km/hr. How far from X will they cross each other?</p>','<p>200 Km</p>','<p>250 Km</p>','<p>300 Km</p>','<p>350 Km</p>','2','<p>Since they are moving in opposite directions, their relative velocity is 25 + 35 = 60 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken to meet will be 600/60 = 10 hours.</p>\r\n<p>Distance from X when they meet is the distance travelled by the first train.</p>\r\n<p>The distance is 10 x 25 = 250 km.</p>','Easy'),(103,2,'1','','<p>Walking at 3/4 of his normal speed, Ashok is 16 minutes late in reaching his office. The usual time taken by him to cover the distance between his home and his office is</p>','<p>16 min</p>','<p>32 min</p>','<p>48 min</p>','<p>64 min</p>','3','<p>Let the normal speed be v. Speed right now is 3v/4. Let the distance he walks be d. The time difference in both the cases is 16 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.2.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"249\" height=\"44\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken usually is 48 minutes.</p>','Easy'),(104,2,'1','','<p>Ram and Bharat travel the same distance at the rate of 6 km per hour and 10 km per hour respectively. If Ram takes 30 minutes longer than Bharat, the distance travelled by each is</p>','<p>6 Km</p>','<p>7.5 Km</p>','<p>8 Km</p>','<p>10 Km</p>','2','<p>Let the distance that they travel be d. The difference in time is 30 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.3.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"90\" height=\"43\" />&nbsp;=&gt; 4d = 30 =&gt; d = 7.5 km.</p>','Easy'),(105,2,'1','','<p>A and B start from the same place in opposite directions with 25 kmph and 30 kmph respectively. In what time will they be 110 km apart?</p>','<p>2 hr. 5 min</p>','<p>5 hr</p>','<p>3 hr 20 min</p>','<p>2 hr</p>','4','<p>Gap between the two trains increases at the rate of 25 + 30 = 55 km per hour.</p>\r\n<p>They will be 110 km apart in 110/55 = 2 hours.</p>','Easy'),(106,2,'1','','<p>Two towns A and B are 160 km apart. A bus starts from A to B at 7 A.M at a speed of 50 kmph. Another bus starts from B to A at 8 A.M at a speed of 60 kmph. The time of their meeting is:</p>','<p>9 A.M.</p>','<p>9.30 A.M.</p>','<p>10 A.M.</p>','<p>8.30 A.M.</p>','1','<p>By the time the second bus starts, first bus has already travelled a distance 50/1 = 50 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance between them is 160 - 50 = 110 km.</p>\r\n<p>Since both are travelling in opposite directions, the relative velocity will be 50 + 60 = 110 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken to meet will be 110/110 = 1 hour.</p>\r\n<p>Time that they meet is 8 + 1 = 9 AM.</p>','Easy'),(107,2,'1','','<p>Sam beats Paul by 30 metres or 10 seconds. How much time was taken by Sam to complete a race 1200 meters?</p>','<p>6 min</p>','<p>6 2/3 min</p>','<p>7 min</p>','<p>6 4/3 min</p>','2','<p>30 metres for Sam is equal to 10 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of Sam is 30/10 = 3m/s.</p>\r\n<p>So, time he takes to run 1200 metres is 1200/3 = 400 seconds or 6 2/3 minutes.</p>','Easy'),(108,2,'1','','<p>A car travels from A to B at v_1 kmph, travels back from B to A at v_2 kmph and again goes back rom A to B at v_2 kmph. The average speed of the car is</p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.7.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"52\" height=\"46\" /></p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.7.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"67\" height=\"46\" /></p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.7.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"66\" height=\"47\" /></p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.7.4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"80\" height=\"49\" /></p>','2','<p>Total distance travelled at v<sub>1</sub> speed is d. distance travelled at v<sub>2</sub> is 2d.</p>\r\n<p>So, average speed is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.7.5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"134\" height=\"60\" />.</p>','Easy'),(109,2,'1','','<p>Jay goes to office at a speed of 6 km/h and returns to his home at a speed of 4 km li. If he takes 10 hours in all, what is the distance between his office and his home?</p>','<p>20 Km</p>','<p>24 Km</p>','<p>30 Km</p>','<p>25 Km</p>','2','<p>Let the distance be d km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.8.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"44\" height=\"42\" />&nbsp;= 10 =&gt; d = 24 km.</p>','Easy'),(110,2,'1','','<p>A motor cyclist travels for 10 hours, the first half at 21 km/hr. and the other half at 24 km/hr. Find the distance travelled.</p>','<p>225 km</p>','<p>224 Km</p>','<p>200 Km</p>','<p>324 km</p>','1','<p>Here the time taken for each part is the same. So, average velocity is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.9.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"46\" height=\"38\" />&nbsp;= 22.5 Kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Total time taken is 10 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, total distance is 22.5 &times; 10 = 225 Km.</p>','Easy'),(111,2,'1','','<p>Sujit covers a distance in 40 minutes if he drives at a speed of 60 kilometre per hour on an average. Find the speed at which he must dive at to reduce the time of the journey by 25%?</p>','<p>70 Kmph</p>','<p>80 kmph</p>','<p>90 kmph</p>','<p>75 kmph</p>','2','<p>His initial time taken is 40 minutes. If he reduces it by 25%, then the time will become 30 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>His initial speed is 60 kmph. Let his final speed be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Since the distance is same in both the cases, 60 &times; 40 = 30v =&gt; v = 80 kmph.</p>','Easy'),(112,2,'1','','<p>Two trains whose lengths 180 m and 220m respectively are running in directions opposite to one another with respective speeds of 40 kmph and 50 kmph. Time taken by them to cross one another will be</p>','<p>16 s</p>','<p>17 s</p>','<p>18 s</p>','<p>22 s</p>','1','<p>Since both are running in opposite directions, the relative velocity of the trains is 40 + 50 = 90 kmph = 90 &times; 5/18 m/s = 25 m/s.</p>\r\n<p>In order for the trains to cross each other, distance travelled is equal to the sum of lengths of both the trains.</p>\r\n<p>So, time taken is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.11.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"40\" />.</p>','Easy'),(113,2,'1','','<p>A car driver, driving in a fog passes a pedestrian who was walking at the rate of 2 km/h in the same direction. The pedestrian could see the car for 6 minutes and it was visible to him up to a distance of 0.6 km. What was the speed of the car in kmph?</p>','<p>7</p>','<p>8</p>','<p>9</p>','<p>10</p>','2','<p>Since both are moving in same directions, relative velocity for the pedestrian wrt car is (v-2) kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The car travelled 0.6 km in 6 minutes with a velocity (v-2).</p>\r\n<p>So, v - 2 = (0.6/6) &times; 60 = 6 =&gt; v = 8 kmph.</p>','Easy'),(114,2,'1','','<p>Harsh and Vijay move towards Vijayawada stating from Guntur, at a speed of 50 kmph and 75 kmph respectively. If Vijay reaches Vijayawada 200 minutes earlier then Harsh, what is the distance between Vijayawada and Guntur?</p>','<p>400 km</p>','<p>500 km</p>','<p>450 km</p>','<p>550 km</p>','2','<p>Let the distance be d.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.13.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"318\" height=\"42\" />.</p>','Easy'),(115,2,'1','','<p>Two identical trains A and B running in opposite directions at same speed take 2 minutes to cross each other completely. The number of bogies of A are increased from 12 to 16. How much more time would they now require to cross each other?</p>','<p>20 sec</p>','<p>25 sec</p>','<p>30 sec</p>','<p>40 sec</p>','1','<p>If the length of each train is l, then the new length of one train is 4l/3.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total length now is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.14.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"80\" height=\"44\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, time taken to complete the journey now is&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.14.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"152\" height=\"50\" />.</p>','Easy'),(116,2,'1','','<p>A car covers a distance of 715 km at a constant speed. If the speed of the car had been 10 km/hr. more, then it would have taken 2 hours less to cover the same distance. What was the original speed of the car in km/hr.?</p>','<p>55</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>65</p>','<p>60</p>','1','<p>Let its initial speed be v. So, according to the question, time difference is 2 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, [715/v] - [715/(v+10)] = 2</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 2v<sup>2</sup> - 20v = 7150</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v<sup>2</sup> - 3575 - 10v = 0</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v = 55 kmph .</p>','Easy'),(117,2,'1','','<p>Two cars stated simultaneously toward each other from town A and B. that are 480 km apart. It took the first car travelling from A to B, 8 hours to cover the distance and the second car travelling from B to A, 12 hours. Determine at what time after both the cars start they will meet.</p>','<p>4 hrs 40 min</p>','<p>4 hrs 48 min</p>','<p>4 hrs 30 min</p>','<p>4 hrs 36 min</p>','2','<p>Speed of first car is 480/8 = 60 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Speed of second car is 480/12 = 40 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Since they are moving in opposite directions, the relative velocity will be 60 + 40 = 100 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken for them to meet is 480/100 = 4.8 hours.</p>','Easy'),(118,2,'1','','<p>A man rows 6 kmph in still water. If the river is running at 3 km per hour, it takes him 45 minutes to row to a place and back. How far is the place in kilometres?</p>','<p>27/16</p>','<p>25/16</p>','<p>13/8</p>','<p>14/8</p>','1','<p>His speed upstream is 6 + 3 = 9 kmph and his speed downstream is 6 - 3 = 3 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, let the distance travelled be d.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.17.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"255\" height=\"43\" />.</p>','Easy'),(119,2,'1','','<p>The speed of a boat in still water is 16 kmph and the rate of the current is 2 kmph. The distance travelled downstream in 15 minutes is:</p>','<p>4 km</p>','<p>4.5 km</p>','<p>6 km</p>','<p>8.5 km</p>','2','<p>The velocity of the boat is u = 16 kmph and that of the stream is v = 2 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Speed downstream is 16 + 2 = 18 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Distance travelled in 15 minutes is 18 &times; (15/60) = 4.5 km.</p>','Easy'),(120,2,'1','','<p>Two trains are running at 40 km/hr. and 20 km/hr. respectively in the same direction. The faster train completely passes a man sitting in the slower train in 5 seconds. What is the length of the faster train?</p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.19.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"46\" height=\"49\" />&nbsp;m</p>','<p>27 m</p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.19.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"42\" height=\"44\" />&nbsp;m</p>','<p>23 m</p>','3','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the man is the lengths of the train.</p>\r\n<p>The relative velocity of the train with respect to the passenger is 40 - 20 = 20kmph = 100/18 m/s with respect to the passenger.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken is 5 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>Length of the train is speed &times; time =&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/122.19.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"184\" height=\"47\" />.</p>','Easy'),(121,2,'1','','<p>Without stoppage, a train travels a certain distance with an average speed of 60 kmh. and with stoppage, it covers the same distance with an average speed of 40 km/h. On an average, how many minutes per hour does the train stop during the journey?</p>','<p>10</p>','<p>20</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>40</p>','2','<p>Difference in the distance travelled is 20 km.</p>\r\n<p>Time usually taken to cover 20 km is 20/60 = 1/3 hour or 20 minutes.</p>','Easy'),(122,2,'2','','<p>A student walks from his house at the speed of 5 km/hr. and thus reaches the school 10 minutes late. If his speed had been 6 km/hr. he would have reached 15 minutes earlier. Then the distance of the school from his house is</p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.1.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"36\" height=\"34\" /></p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.1.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"42\" height=\"37\" /></p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.1.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"43\" height=\"39\" /></p>','<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.1.4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"44\" height=\"37\" /></p>','3','<p>The difference in the two times is 25 minutes or 5/12 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.1.5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"332\" height=\"40\" />.</p>','Medium'),(123,2,'2','','<p>Hyderabad and Nagpur are two stations 600 km apart. A train stats from Nagpur and moves towards Hyderabad at the rate of 25 km/h. After two hours, another train starts from Hyderabad at the rate of 30 km/h. How far from Nagpur will they will cross each other?</p>','<p>250 km</p>','<p>300 km</p>','<p>275 km</p>','<p>225 km</p>','2','<p>By the time the second train starts, the distance travelled by the first train is 2 &times; 25 = 50 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance between them is 600 - 50 = 550 km.</p>\r\n<p>Relative velocity between the trains will be 25 + 30 = 55 kmph since they are moving in opposite directions.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken for them to meet is 550/55 = 10 hours.</p>\r\n<p>The first train is travelling for 12 hours and so the distance from Nagpur when they meet is 25 &times; 12 = 300 km.</p>','Medium'),(124,2,'2','','<p>Ashok walks to a viewpoint and returns to the starting point by his car and thus takes a total time of 6 hours 45 minutes. He would have gained 2 hours by driving both ways. How long would it have taken for him to walk both ways?</p>','<p>8 hr</p>','<p>8 hr 45 min</p>','<p>8 hr 30 min</p>','<p>7 hr 45 min</p>','2','<p>Let the time taken for him to walk be x and by car be y.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.3.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"113\" height=\"47\" />&nbsp;and <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.3.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"221\" height=\"41\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken to go and come on foot is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.3.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"179\" height=\"40\" />&nbsp;or 8 hrs.45 mins.</p>','Medium'),(125,2,'2','','<p>A train running at uniform speed takes 54 seconds to pass a platform of 324 m long and 45 seconds to pass another platform of 240m long. The length of the train in metres is</p>','<p>180</p>','<p>170</p>','<p>190</p>','<p>100</p>','1','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the platform is the sum of lengths of the train and the platform.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l and its speed be v m/s.</p>\r\n<p>So, for the first platform, l + 324 = 54v and for the second platform, l + 240 = 45v.</p>\r\n<p>We get that 9v = 324 - 240 = 84 =&gt; v = 84/9.</p>\r\n<p>Substituting it we get l = 50v - 324 = [54 &times; (84/9)] - 324 = 504 - 324 = 180 m.</p>','Medium'),(126,2,'2','','<p>Train A starts from x at 12:00 pm &amp; reaches Y at 2:30 pm &amp; train B starts from Y at 12:15 and reaches X on 2:15 so, when does both trains cross each other?</p>','<p>1 PM</p>','<p>1.15 PM</p>','<p>1.30 PM</p>','<p>1.20 PM</p>','2','<p>Let them meet after a time x hours from 12.00 pm.</p>\r\n<p>So, the first train travels the first leg in x hours and the second leg in [(5/2) - x] hours.</p>\r\n<p>For the second train, the legs will be reversed.</p>\r\n<p>So, it will travel second leg in [x - (1/4)] hours and the first leg in <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.5.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"186\" height=\"40\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Since they travel with same speeds, ratio of times taken to travel same distances will be equal.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.5.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"425\" height=\"54\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, they both meet at 1.15 pm.</p>','Medium'),(127,2,'2','','<p>In a race of 200 meters, A beats S by 20 meters and N by 40 metres. If S and N are running a race of 100 metres with exactly the same speed as before, then by how many metres will S beat N?</p>','<p>10</p>','<p>11.11</p>','<p>12.5</p>','<p>13.75</p>','2','<p>By the time S could run 180 m, N could only run 160 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, by the time S will run 100 metres, N would run (160/180) &times; 100 = 88.89 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, S will beat N by 11.11 meters.</p>','Medium'),(128,2,'2','','<p>Karan and Arjun run a 100-metre race, where Karan beats Arjun by 10 metres. To do a favour to Arjun, Karan starts 10 metres behind the starting line in a second 100-metre race. They both run at their earlier speeds. Which of the following is true in connection with the second race?</p>','<p>Arjun wins it.</p>','<p>Karan wins it.</p>','<p>It will be a tie.</p>','<p>Data Insufficient.</p>','2','<p>Ratio of speeds od Karan and Arjun is 100 : 90 = 10 : 9.</p>\r\n<p>So, by the time Karan travels 110 m, Arjun will travel (9/10) &times; 110 = 99 metres.</p>\r\n<p>So, Karan will beat Arjun by 1 m.</p>','Medium'),(129,2,'2','','<p>In a stream, B lies in between A and C such that it is equidistant from both A and C. A boat can go from A to B and back in 6 h 30 minutes while it goes from A to C in 9 h. How long would it take to go from C to A?</p>','<p>4 hours</p>','<p>3 &frac12; hours</p>','<p>6 &frac12; hours</p>','<p>4 &frac12; hours</p>','1','<p>Since C is exactly equidistant, the total time that is required to go from A to C and return back is twice the time taken to go from A to B and return back.</p>\r\n<p>If the time taken to go from C to A is x, we can say that x + 9 = 2 x (13/2) = &gt; x = 4 hours.</p>','Medium'),(130,2,'2','','<p>Two trains pass each other on parallel lines. Each train is 100 metres long. When they are going in the same direction, the faster one takes 60 seconds to pass the other completely. If they are going in opposite directions they pass each other completely in 10 seconds. Find the speed of the slower train in km/h</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>35</p>','<p>42</p>','1','<p>Let the speeds be x and y. The relative speed when going in opposite directions is x+y and in same direction is x - y.</p>\r\n<p>The times taken will be in inverse ratio of the speeds. So <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.9.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"236\" height=\"45\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Distance taken to cross each other is the length of the two trains which is 100 + 100 = 200 m.</p>\r\n<p>When going in opposite directions, time taken is 10 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.9.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"428\" height=\"48\" />.</p>','Medium'),(131,2,'2','','<p>A boat can be rowed 9 km upstream or 18 km downstream in a period of 3 hrs. What is the speed of the boat in still water in kmph?</p>','<p>1.5</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>4.5</p>','<p>6</p>','3','<p>Let the velocity of the boat be u kmph and that of the stream be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken to go 9 km upstream is same as time taken to go 18 km downstream which is 3 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, 3(u - v) = 9; 3(u + v) = 18 =&gt; 6u = 27 =&gt; u = 4.5 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The speed of the boat in still water is 4.5 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(132,2,'2','','<p>A motorboat went down the river for 14 km and then up the river for 9 km. It took a total of 5 hours for the entire journey. Find the speed of the river flow in km/hr. if the speed of the boat in still water is 5 km/h.</p>','<p>1</p>','<p>2</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>4</p>','2','<p>If the speed of the river flow is v km/hr, then <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.11.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"98\" height=\"43\" />&nbsp;= 5 =&gt; 115 - 5v = 125 - 5v<sup>2</sup>.</p>\r\n<p>So, 5v<sup>2</sup> - 5v - 10 = 0 =&gt; v<sup>2</sup> - v - 2 = 0 =&gt; v = 2 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(133,2,'2','','<p>Two motorists met at 10 a.m. at the Hyderabad railway station. After their meeting, one of them proceeded in the East direction while the other proceeded in the North direction. Exactly at noon, they were 60 km apart. Find the speed of the slower motorist if the difference of their speeds is 6 km/h.</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>18</p>','<p>24</p>','<p>30</p>','2','<p>Since they are moving in perpendicular directions, distance between them increases as &radic;(v12 + v22 ).</p>\r\n<p>The distance increased by 60 km in 2 hours and one of the speeds is 6 km/hr. higher than the other.</p>\r\n<p>So, &radic;(v<sup>2</sup> + (6 + v)<sup>2</sup> ) = 30 = &radic;(18<sup>2</sup> + 24<sup>2</sup>) =&gt; v = 18 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(134,2,'2','','<p>A boat sails down the river for 10 km and then up the river for 6 km. The speed of the river flow is 1 km/h. What should be the minimum speed of the boat in km/hr. for the trip to take a maximum of 4 hours?</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>4</p>','<p>5</p>','<p>6</p>','2','<p>If the speed of the boat in still water is v km/hr, then <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.13.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"94\" height=\"43\" />&nbsp;&le; 4</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 10v - 10 + 6v + 6 &le; 4v<sup>2</sup> - 4</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 4v<sup>2</sup> &ge; 16v</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v &ge; 4 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(135,2,'2','','<p>A tourist covered a journey partly by foot and partly by bicycle. He walked for 90 km and rode the bicycle for 10 km. He spent 4 h less on the bicycle than on walking. If the tourist had reversed the times he travelled by foot and on bicycle, the distances travelled on each part of the journey would be equal. How long did he ride the bicycle?</p>','<p>1 hr</p>','<p>1 &frac12; hours</p>','<p>1 &frac34; hours</p>','<p>2 hours</p>','4','<p>Let his speed of walking be u kmph and bicycling is v kmph. If he travels for a time t hours on foot initially, then the time spent on bicycle initially is (t - 4) hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, we can say that ut = 90; v(t - 4) = 10 and also u(t - 4) = v(t).</p>\r\n<p>So, 90 - 4u = 10 + 4v =&gt; u + v = 20.</p>\r\n<p>4v = 20t - 100 =&gt; v = 5t - 25 =&gt; 5(t - 5)(t - 4) = 10 =&gt; t - 5 = 1 =&gt; t = 6 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, he spent a total of 2 hours on bicycle.</p>','Medium'),(136,2,'2','','<p>Two cyclists start simultaneously towards each other from Aurangabad and Ellora, which are 30 km apart. An hour later they meet and keep pedalling with the same speed without stopping. The second cyclist arrives at Ellora 50 minutes later than the first arrives at Aurangabad. Find the speed of the cyclist who stated from Ellora.</p>','<p>12 kmph</p>','<p>15 kmph</p>','<p>18 kmph</p>','<p>20 kmph</p>','3','<p>Let the respective speeds be u kmph and v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Since they take 1 hour to meet each other, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.15.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"46\" height=\"45\" />&nbsp;= 1 =&gt; u + v = 30.</p>\r\n<p>Since the difference in times of journey is 50 minutes, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.15.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"114\" height=\"44\" />&nbsp;=&gt; 36(30 - 2u) = 30u - u<sup>2</sup>.</p>\r\n<p>So, u<sup>2&nbsp;</sup>- 102u + 1080 = 0 =&gt; u = 12 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the speeds are 12 kmph and 18 kmph. The cyclist who started at Ellora is the faster one and so his speed is 18 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(137,2,'2','','<p>An ant climbing up a vertical pole ascends 12 meters and slips down 5 meters in every alternate hour. If the pole is 40 meters high how long will it take it to reach the top?</p>','<p>9</p>','<p>10</p>','<p>11</p>','<p>12</p>','1','<p>Every two hours, it will climb up 7 m on aggregate.</p>\r\n<p>So, in 8 hours, it will go up by (7/2) &times; 8 = 28 meters.</p>\r\n<p>During the ninth hour, it will climb 12 m and come out of the hole. So, time taken is 9 hours.</p>','Medium'),(138,2,'2','','<p>The Sabarmati Express left Ahmedabad for Mumbai. Having travelled 300 km. which constitutes 66.666 per cent of the distance between Ahmedabad and Mumbai. The train was stopped by a red signal. Half an hour later, the track was cleared and the engine-driver, having increased the speed by 15 km per hour, arrived at Mumbai on time. Find the initial speed of the Sabarmati Express</p>','<p>60 kmph</p>','<p>45 kmph</p>','<p>75 kmph</p>','<p>50 kmh</p>','1','<p>Total distance left to be travelled is [300 &times; (100/66.67)] - 300 = 150 km.</p>\r\n<p>The speed difference in both the cases is 15 km/hr. let the speeds be v kmph and v + 15 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The time difference in both the cases is 30 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.17.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"117\" height=\"44\" />&nbsp;=&gt; 300 &times; 15 = v(v + 15) = 60 &times; 75 =&gt; v = 60 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(139,2,'2','','<p>The J&amp;K Express from Delhi to Srinagar was delayed by snowfall for 16 minutes and made up for the delay on a section of 80 km travelling with a speed 10 km per hour higher than its normal speed. Find the original speed of the J&amp;K Express (according to the schedule)</p>','<p>50 kmph</p>','<p>45 kmph</p>','<p>60 mph</p>','<p>65 kmph</p>','1','<p>Let the speeds be v and v + 10.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/123.18.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"99\" height=\"40\" />&nbsp;=&gt; 3000 = v(v + 10) = 50 &times; 60 =&gt; v = 50 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(140,2,'2','','<p>At a game of billiards, A can give B 15 points in 60 and A can give C 20 in 60. How many points can B give C in a game of 90?</p>','<p>10</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>9</p>','<p>11</p>','1','<p>By the time B comes to 45 points in a game of 60, C will come only to 40 points. So, in a game of 45 points, B can give A an edge of 45 - 40 = 5 points.</p>\r\n<p>So, the maximum chance that B can give in game of 90 is (1/9) &times; 90 = 10.</p>','Medium'),(141,2,'2','','<p>A dog sees a cat. It estimates that the cat is 25 leaps away. The cat sees the dog and stats running with the dog in hot pursuit. If in every minute, the dog makes 5 leaps and the cat makes 6 leaps and one leap of the dog is equal to 2 leaps of the cat. Find the time in minutes, in which the cat is caught by the dog (assume an open field with no trees).</p>','<p>10</p>','<p>12.5</p>','<p>15</p>','<p>6.25</p>','2','<p>Initial distance between them is 25 dog leaps or 50 cat leaps.</p>\r\n<p>Distance between them decreases in every minute by [5 - (6/2)] = 2 dog leaps.</p>\r\n<p>So, time taken to catch the cat is (25/2) = 12.5 minutes.</p>','Medium'),(142,2,'3','','<p>Two trains A and B start simultaneously in the opposite direction from two points A and B and arrive at their destinations 9 and 4 hours respectively after their meeting each other. At what rate does the second train B travel if the first train travels at 80 km per km?</p>','<p>100 kmph</p>','<p>53.3 kmph</p>','<p>120 kmph</p>','<p>90 kmph</p>','3','<p>Ratio of the speeds if they take u hours and v hours to reach the destination after meeting is &radic;v : &radic;u.</p>\r\n<p>Here u = 9, v = 4.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of the second train is 80 &times; &radic;(9/4) = 120 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(143,2,'3','','<p>Two trains travel toward each other on the same track, beginning 100 miles apart. One train travels at 40 miles per hour; the other travels at 60 miles an hour. A bird starts flight at the same location as the faster train, flying at a speed of 90 miles per hour. When it reaches the slower train, it turns around, flying the other direction at the same speed. When it reaches the faster train again, it turns around -- and so on. What is the total distance the bird travels?</p>','<p>100 km</p>','<p>90 km</p>','<p>80 km</p>','<p>75 km</p>','2','<p>Since its speed is constant and the trains take <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.2.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"62\" height=\"47\" />&nbsp;=1 hour to meet each other, the distance travelled by the bird is 1 hr &times; 90 kmph = 90 km.</p>','Hard'),(144,2,'3','','<p>Every day a cyclist meets a train at a particular crossing. The road is straight before the crossing and both are travelling in the same direction. The cyclist travels with a speed of 12 Kmph. One day the cyclist comes late by 20 min and meets the train 5km before the crossing. What is the speed of the train in kmph?</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>48</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>36</p>','3','<p>Since the cyclist comes late by 20 minutes, by the time the train reaches their usual meeting place, the cyclist will be behind by 20/60 &times; 12 = 4 km.</p>\r\n<p>The cyclist meets the train 5 km before the meeting point.</p>\r\n<p>So, by the time the cyclist travels the 1 km distance, the train will reach the meeting point and so has travelled 5 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of the train is 5 &times; 12 = 60 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(145,2,'3','','<p>Boat A leaves shore P and Boat B leaves shore Q. (P and Q are opposite shores of a river.) A and B travel at constant speed. But the speeds are not same. Both boats meet at 600m from P for the first time. In their return journeys (i.e. after touching the shores), they meet again at 200m from Q. Find distance between P and Q.</p>','<p>1.6 km</p>','<p>1.2km</p>','<p>0.8 km</p>','<p>2 km</p>','1','<p>Let the distance between P and Q be x km.</p>\r\n<p>By the first starting time:</p>\r\n<p>Distance travelled by the two boats are 0.6 and (x - 0.6) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>By the second starting time:</p>\r\n<p>Distance travelled by the two boats are (x + 0.2) and (2x - 0.2) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>Since the speeds of the two boats remain constant, we can say that the ratios of distanced for same times will be constant.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.4.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"128\" height=\"44\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 1.2x - 0.12 = x<sup>2</sup> - 0.4x - 0.12</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x<sup>2</sup> = 1.6x</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x = 1.6 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance between P and Q is 1.6 km.</p>','Hard'),(146,2,'3','','<p>The metro service has a train going from Mumbai to Pune and Pune to Mumbai every hour. The first one starts at 6 a.m. The trip from one city to another takes 4 1/2 hours, and all trains travel at the same speed. How many trains will pass while going from Mumbai to Pune, if you start at 12 noon?</p>','<p>8</p>','<p>9</p>','<p>10</p>','<p>11</p>','2','<p>The first train that this train will encounter is the one that arrives back at 12.30 PM. So, it has started at the first station at 8 AM.</p>\r\n<p>Since this train reaches its destination at 4:30 PM, the last train it encounters is the train that started its journey at 4 PM.</p>\r\n<p>The train will also encounter all the trains that have started in between these times at some point in its journey.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total number of trains it encounters is 5 + 4 = 9.</p>','Hard'),(147,2,'3','','<p>Two boats, traveling at 5 and 10 km per hour, head directly towards each other. They begin at a distance of 20 km from each other. How far apart are they (in km) one minute before they collide?</p>','<p>0.25</p>','<p>0.5</p>','<p>0.2</p>','<p>0.45</p>','1','<p>Since they are moving towards each other, distance covered in one minute will be (5 + 10) &times; (1/60) = 1/4 km.</p>','Hard'),(148,2,'3','','<p>Ganesh and Sarah walk up an escalator which moves up with a constant speed. For every two steps that Ganesh takes, Sarah takes one step. Ganesh gets to the top of the escalator after having taken 30 steps, while Sarah takes only 20 steps to reach the top. If the escalator were turned off, how many steps should each of them take to reach the top?</p>','<p>50</p>','<p>55</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>65</p>','3','<p>Let us assume that the speed of escalator is n steps for every step of Ganesh.</p>\r\n<p>So, we can say that the total distance travelled by Ganesh is 30 + 30n.</p>\r\n<p>Since one step of Sarah is equal to two steps of Ganesh, 2n steps of the escalator is equal to 1 step of Sarah.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total distance travelled by Sarah is 20 + 40n.</p>\r\n<p>Since both travel the same distance up, we can say that 30 + 30n = 20 + 40n =&gt; n = 1.</p>\r\n<p>So, total number of steps to be taken, if the escalator is turned off is 60.</p>','Hard'),(149,2,'3','','<p>Ram and Shyam run a race of 2000 m. First, Ram gives Shyam a start of 200 m and beats him by 30 s. Next, Ram gives Shyam a stat of 3 minutes and is beaten by 1000 metres. Find the time in minutes in which Ram can finish the race.</p>','<p>4</p>','<p>5</p>','<p>6</p>','<p>7</p>','1','<p>Let the speeds of Ram and Shyam be x m/s and y m/s.</p>\r\n<p>In the first case, Ram gives Shyam a head start of 200 m and still beats him by 30 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken by Ram to travel 2000 m is still less than the time taken by Shyam to travel 1800 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.8.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"133\" height=\"43\" />.</p>\r\n<p>In the second case, Ram gives Shyam a head start of 3 minutes and is beaten by 1000 meters.</p>\r\n<p>So, if the time taken by Ram to travel 1000 m is t seconds, then the time taken for Shyam to travel 2000 m is t + 180 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.8.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"136\" height=\"47\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.8.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"436\" height=\"51\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, time taken by Shyam to travel 2000 m is 2000/(20/3) = 300 seconds.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.8.4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"336\" height=\"43\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, time taken by Ram to travel 2000 m is 2000/(50/6) = 240 seconds.</p>','Hard'),(150,2,'3','','<p>A boatman can row to a place 48 km distant and back, in 14 hrs. If he can row 4 km with the stream in the same time as 3 km against it, the speed of the stream (in kmph) is</p>','<p>1</p>','<p>2.2</p>','<p>3</p>','<p>0.5</p>','4','<p>Let the velocity of the boat be u kmph and that of the stream be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Now, time taken to go upstream is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.9.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"45\" height=\"42\" />&nbsp;and time taken to go downstream is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.9.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"48\" height=\"46\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.9.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"245\" height=\"47\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken to go 3 km upstream is same as time taken to go 4 km downstream.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.9.4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"334\" height=\"47\" />.</p>\r\n<p>Substituting the result, we get 96v/(48v<sup>2</sup>) = 14 =&gt; v = 0.5 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the speed of the stream is 0.5 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(151,2,'3','','<p>Two horses stated simultaneously towards each other and meet each other 200 minutes later. How much time will it take for the slower horse to cover the whole distance if the first arrived at the place of departure of the second 5 hours later than the second arrived at the point of departure of the first?</p>','<p>12 hours</p>','<p>10 1/3 hours</p>','<p>11 2/3 hours</p>','<p>10 hours</p>','4','<p>Let the two end points be A and B and let them meet at a point C in between.</p>\r\n<p>So, one horse covers distance AC in 10/3 hours and the other covers distance BC in 10/3 hours.</p>\r\n<p>Let the faster horse take x hours to cover the distance BC. So, the slower horse will take (x + 5) hours to cover the distance AC.</p>\r\n<p>Since they travel with same speed, ratio of times taken to cover same distance will be equal.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.10.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"339\" height=\"68\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total time taken by the slower horse to travel the entire distance is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.10.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"146\" height=\"40\" />.</p>','Hard'),(152,2,'3','','<p>Ronaldo had to cover a distance of 60 km. However, he stated 6 minutes later than his scheduled time and raced at a speed 1 km/h higher than his originally planned speed and reached the finish at the time he would reach it if he began to race strictly at the appointed time and raced with the assumed speed. Find the speed at which he travelled during the journey described.</p>','<p>24 km/hr.</p>','<p>25 km/hr.</p>','<p>30 km/hr.</p>','<p>30 km/hr.</p>','2','<p>Let his normal speed be v kmph. So, his speed during the journey is (v + 1) kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The distance to be covered is 60 km.</p>\r\n<p>The time difference in both the cases is 6 min = (1/10) hours.</p>\r\n<p>So,&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.11.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"114\" height=\"46\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v<sup>2</sup> + v = 600</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v<sup>2</sup> + v - 600 = 0</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v = 24 kmph</p>\r\n<p>So, his speed during the journey is 24 + 1 = 25 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(153,2,'3','','<p>Three cars leave Patna for Ranchi after equal time intervals. They reach Ranchi simultaneously and then leave for Vizag which is 120 km from Ranchi. The first car arrives there an hour after the second car and the third car having reached Vizag, immediately reverses the direction and 40 km from Vizag meets the first car. Find the speed of the first car in km/hr.</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>20</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>60</p>','1','<p>By the time the first car has covered 120 - 80 km on its journey to Vizag, the third car has covered 120 + 40 = 160 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, ratio of their speeds is 1:2.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken for the third car for the Patna to Ranchi trip is half the time taken by the first car.</p>\r\n<p>So, if the first car takes x hours for journey, then the thitd car takes x/2 hours and the second car will take 3x/4 hours because the time intervals is same.</p>\r\n<p>So, ratio of speeds of first and second cars is 3:4.</p>\r\n<p>Let the speed of the first car be 3v, then the speed of second car is 4v and third car is 6v.</p>\r\n<p>Time difference for travel of 120 km for first and second cars is 1 hour.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.12.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"72\" height=\"41\" />&nbsp;= 1</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 12v = 120</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v = 10</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 3v = 30 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(154,2,'3','','<p>Three cars started simultaneously rom Ajmer to Banaras along the same highway. The second car travelled with a speed that was 10 km/h higher than the first car&rsquo;s speed and arrived at Banaras 1 hour earlier than the first car. The third car arrived at Banaras 33.33 minutes earlier than the first car by travelling half the time at the speed of the first car and the other half at the speed of the second car. Find the distance between Ajmer and Banaras in kilometres.</p>','<p>150</p>','<p>200</p>','<p>180</p>','<p>240</p>','2','<p>Let the speed of the first car be v kmph. So, the speed of second car is (v + 10)kmph. Since the third car travelled half of the time with one velocity and other half at the other velocity, its average velocity will be <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.13.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"78\" height=\"40\" />&nbsp;= (v + 5)kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Let the total distance be d km.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.13.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"79\" height=\"42\" />&nbsp;= 1 =&gt; 10d = v<sup>2</sup> + 10v.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.13.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"160\" height=\"43\" />&gt; 9d = v<sup>2</sup> + 5v.</p>\r\n<p>So, d = 5v =&gt; v<sup>2</sup> = 40v =&gt; v = 40 kmph =&gt; d = 200 km.</p>','Hard'),(155,2,'3','','<p>Two trains start from the same point simultaneously and in the same direction. The first train travels at 40 km/h. and the speed of the second train is 25 per cent more than the speed of the first train. Thirty minutes later, a third train stats from the same point and in the same direction. It overtakes the second train 90 minutes later than it overtook the first train. What is the speed of the third train?</p>','<p>60 kmph</p>','<p>55kmph</p>','<p>75 kmph</p>','<p>70 kmph</p>','1','<p>The speed of the first train is 40 kmph and that of the second train is (125/100) &times; 40 = 50 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Let the third train speed be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>It starts 30 minutes later. So, the distance from the first train is (40/2) = 20 km and from the second train is (50/2) = 25 km at the starting point.</p>\r\n<p>Since they are travelling in the same direction, relative speed of the third train is (v - 40) for the first and (v - 50) for the second.</p>\r\n<p>So, according to the question, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.14.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"145\" height=\"49\" />&nbsp;=&gt; v = 60 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(156,2,'3','','<p>Ram and Raju stat together from the same point on a circular path and walk around, each at his own pace, until both arrive together at the starting point. If Ram performs the circuit in 3 minutes 44 seconds and Raju in 6 minutes 4 seconds, how many times does Ram go around the path?</p>','<p>13</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>26</p>','<p>20</p>','1','<p>Ratio of their speeds is (224/364) = 8/13.</p>\r\n<p>Since they complete integral number of rounds, the minimum number of round that Ram should complete is 13, by which time Raju will have completed exactly 8 rounds.</p>','Hard'),(157,2,'3','','<p>Two cars stated simultaneously toward each other from town A and B that are 480 km apart. It took the first car travelling from A to B, 8 hours to cover the distance and the second car travelling from B to A, 12 hours. Determine at what distance from A the two cars meet.</p>','<p>240 km</p>','<p>272 km</p>','<p>288 km</p>','<p>192 km</p>','3','<p>Speed of first car is 480/8 = 60 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Speed of second car is 480/12 = 40 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Since they are moving in opposite directions, the relative velocity will be 60 + 40 = 100 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken for them to meet is 480/100 = 4.8 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance from A that they meet is 4.8 &times; 60 = 288 km.</p>','Hard'),(158,2,'3','','<p>Two ports A and B are 300 km apart. Two ships leave A for B such that the second leaves 8 hours after the first. The ships arrive at B simultaneously. Find the time the slower ship spent on the trip if the speed of one of them is 10 km/h higher than that of the other.</p>','<p>12 hours</p>','<p>15 hours</p>','<p>20 hours</p>','<p>18 hours</p>','3','<p>Let the faster ship take t hours for the journey. So, the slower ship takes (t + 8) hours for the journey.</p>\r\n<p>The total distance is 300 km, and let the the respective speeds be (v + 10) and v respectively.</p>\r\n<p>So, (v + 10)t = 300 and v(t + 8) = 300.</p>\r\n<p>So, 10t = 8v</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v = 5t/4.</p>\r\n<p>So, t(t + 8) = 300 &times; (4/5) = 240 = 12 &times; 20.</p>\r\n<p>So, t = 12.</p>\r\n<p>So, the slower boat took 20 hours for the journey.</p>','Hard'),(159,2,'3','','<p>A bus left point X for point Y. Two hours later a car left point X for Y and arrived at Y at the same time as the bus. If the car and the bus left simultaneously from the opposite ends X and Y towards each other, they would meet 1.33 hours after the start. How much time, in hours, did it take the bus to travel rom X to Y?</p>','<p>2</p>','<p>4</p>','<p>6</p>','<p>8</p>','2','<p>Let the bus take t hours for the journey. So, the car takes (t - 2) hours for the journey.</p>\r\n<p>If the total distance is d km, then the respective speeds are d/t and d/(t - 2) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>When they travel in opposite directions, the velocities will add up and so, the time taken to meet is:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.18.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"202\" height=\"57\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 3t<sup>2</sup> - 14t + 8 = 0</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; t = 4 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, the bus will take 4 hours for the journey.</p>','Hard'),(160,2,'3','','<p>A train has to travel the distance between Aurangabad and Daulatabad equal to 20 km. at a constant speed. It travelled half the way with the specified speed and stopped for three minutes. To arrive at Daulatabad on time, it had to increase its speed by 10 km/h for the rest of the way. Next time the train stopped half-way for five minutes. By what speed must it increase its speed for the remaining half of the distance to arrive at Daulatabad as per the schedule?</p>','<p>20 kmph</p>','<p>15 kmph</p>','<p>30 kmph</p>','<p>25 kmph</p>','1','<p>It must travel 10 km and the time difference in both the cases is 3 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>If the initial speed is v kmph, then the final speed is (v + 10) kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.19.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"121\" height=\"44\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v<sup>2</sup> + 10v - 2000 = 0</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v = 40 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Now, let the final speed is u and the time difference is 5 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So,&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/124.19.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"152\" height=\"38\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; u = 60 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the difference is 20 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(161,2,'3','','<p>A cyclist left point A for point B and travelled at the constant speed of 25 km/hr. When he covered the distance of 8.33 km. he was overtaken by a car that left point A twelve minutes after the cyclist and travelled at a constant speed too. When the cyclist travelled another 25 km, he encountered the car returning from B. Assume that the car did not stop at point B. Find the distance between A and B.</p>','<p>52 km</p>','<p>50 km</p>','<p>45 km</p>','<p>60 km</p>','1','<p>Time taken by the cyclist to cover 8.33 km is 8.33/25 = 1/3 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, the car travelled this distance in 20 - 12 = 8 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So, the speed of the car is 8.33/(8/60) = 62.475 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Let the distance between the points be x km.</p>\r\n<p>So, by their second meeting point, total distance travelled by cyclist is 8.33 + 25 = 33.33 km and the time taken will be 33.33/25 = 4/3 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, by their second meeting point, total distance travelled by car is (2x - 33.33) km. and the time taken will be 80 - 12 = 68 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So, (68/60) &times; 62.475 = 2x - 33.33</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 2x = 70.805 + 33.33 = 104.135</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x = 52.067 km.</p>','Hard'),(162,2,'4','','<p>A person can row downstream at 10 kmph and upstream at 7 kmph. Then, the rate of the person in still water is:</p>','<p>7.5 kmph</p>','<p>12 kmph</p>','<p>8.5 kmph</p>','<p>9.5 kmph</p>','3','<p>If the speed of upstream is u and that of downstream is v, then the speed of the boat in still water is (v + u)/2.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed required is (10 + 7)/2 = 8.5 kmph.</p>','Easy'),(163,2,'4','','<p>A man can row upstream at 8 kmph and downstream at 6 kmph. Find the speed of the man in still water.</p>','<p>8 kmph</p>','<p>6 kmph</p>','<p>9 kmph</p>','<p>7 kmph</p>','4','<p>If the speed of upstream is u and that of downstream is v, then the speed of the boat in still water is (v + u)/2.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed required is (6 + 8)/2 = 7 kmph.</p>','Easy'),(164,2,'4','','<p>A person can row upstream 8 km/hr. and downstream at 12 km/hr. Then, the rate of the current is</p>','<p>6 kmph</p>','<p>2 kmph</p>','<p>8 kmph</p>','<p>10 kmph</p>','2','<p>If the speed of upstream is u and that of downstream is v, then the rate of current is (v - u)/2.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed required is (12 - 8)/2 = 2 kmph.</p>','Easy'),(165,2,'4','','<p>A man can row upstream 14 km/hr. and downstream at 22 km/hr. Then, the rate of the current is</p>','<p>8 kmph</p>','<p>4 kmph</p>','<p>6 kmph</p>','<p>10 kmph</p>','2','<p>If the speed of upstream is u and that of downstream is v, then the rate of current is (v - u)/2.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed required is (22 - 14)/2 = 4 kmph.</p>','Easy'),(166,2,'4','','<p>Walking at 1/2 of his normal speed, Ashok is 48 minutes late in reaching his office. The usual time taken by him to cover the distance between his home and his office is</p>','<p>16 min</p>','<p>32 min</p>','<p>48 min</p>','<p>64 min</p>','3','<p>Let the normal speed be v. Speed right now is v/2. Let the distance he walks be d. The time difference in both the cases is 48 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.5.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"166\" height=\"43\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken usually is 48 minutes.</p>','Easy'),(167,2,'4','','<p>Walking at 2/5th of his normal speed, Ashok is 30 minutes late in reaching his office. The usual time taken by him to cover the distance between his home and his office is</p>','<p>20 min</p>','<p>30 min</p>','<p>40 min</p>','<p>50 min</p>','1','<p>Let the normal speed be v. Speed right now is 2v/5. Let the distance he walks be d. The time difference in both the cases is 30 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.6.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"41\" />.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken usually is 20 minutes.</p>','Easy'),(168,2,'4','','<p>A and B start from the same place in opposite directions with 20 kmph and 40 kmph respectively. In what time will they be 240 km apart?</p>','<p>3 hrs. 45 min</p>','<p>5 hrs.</p>','<p>3 hrs. 20 min</p>','<p>4 hrs.</p>','4','<p>Gap between the two increases at the rate of 20 + 40 = 60 km. per hour.</p>\r\n<p>They will be 240 km. apart in 240/60 = 4 hours.</p>','Easy'),(169,2,'4','','<p>A and B start from the same place in same directions with 20 kmph and 30 kmph respectively. In what time will they be 50 km apart?</p>','<p>2 hrs. 5 min.</p>','<p>2 hrs. 5 min.</p>','<p>3 hrs. 20 min</p>','<p>2 hrs.</p>','2','<p>Gap between the two increases at the rate of 30 - 20 = 10 km. per hour.</p>\r\n<p>They will be 50 km. apart in 50/10 = 5 hours.</p>','Easy'),(170,2,'4','','<p>Two towns A and B are 200 km apart. A bus starts from A to B at 8 A.M at a speed of 60 kmph. Another bus starts from B to A at 10 A.M at a speed of 20 kmph. The time of their meeting is:</p>','<p>11 AM</p>','<p>11.30 AM</p>','<p>11.15 AM</p>','<p>10.45 AM</p>','1','<p>By the time the second bus starts, first bus has already travelled a distance 60 &times; 2 = 120 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance between them is 200 - 120 = 80 km.</p>\r\n<p>Since both are travelling in opposite directions, the relative velocity will be 20 + 60 = 80 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken to meet will be 80/80 = 1 hour.</p>\r\n<p>Time that they meet is 10 + 1 = 11 AM.</p>','Easy'),(171,2,'4','','<p>Two towns A and B are 500 km apart. A bus starts from A to B at 7.30 A.M at a speed of 30 kmph. Another bus starts from A to B at 9.30 A.M at a speed of 60 kmph. The time of their meeting is:</p>','<p>11 AM</p>','<p>11.30 AM</p>','<p>11.15 AM</p>','<p>10.45 AM</p>','2','<p>By the time the second bus starts, first bus has already travelled a distance 30 &times; 2 = 60 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance between them is 60 km.</p>\r\n<p>Since both are travelling in same direction, the relative velocity will be 60 - 30 = 30 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken to meet will be 60/30 = 2 hours.</p>\r\n<p>Time that they meet is 9.30 + 2 = 11.30 AM.</p>','Easy'),(172,2,'4','','<p>Sam beats Paul by 60 metres or 15 seconds. How much time was taken by Sam to complete a race 1000 meters?</p>','<p>4 min</p>','<p>4 1/6 minutes</p>','<p>4 2/6 minutes</p>','<p>5 minutes</p>','2','<p>60 metres for Sam is equal to 15 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of Sam is 60/15 = 4 m/s.</p>\r\n<p>So, time he takes to run 1000 metres is 1000/4 = 250 seconds or 4 1/6 minutes.</p>','Easy'),(173,2,'4','','<p>Jay goes to office at a speed of 8 km/h and returns to his home at a speed of 6 km/hr. If he takes 7 hours in all, what is the distance between his office and his home?</p>','<p>20 km</p>','<p>24 km</p>','<p>30 km</p>','<p>25 km</p>','2','<p>Let the distance be d km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken is <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.12.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"51\" height=\"45\" />&nbsp;= 7</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; d = 24 km.</p>','Easy'),(174,2,'4','','<p>Suman covers a distance in 25 minutes if he drives at a speed of 40 kilometres per hour on an average. Find the speed at which he must drive at to reduce the time of the journey by 20%?</p>','<p>45 kmph</p>','<p>50 kmph</p>','<p>48 kmph</p>','<p>55 kmph</p>','2','<p>His initial time taken is 25 minutes. If he reduces it by 20%, then the time will become 20 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>His initial speed is 40 kmph. Let his final speed be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Since the distance is same in both the cases, 40 &times; 25 = 20v =&gt; v = 50 kmph.</p>','Easy'),(175,2,'4','','<p>A train with the speed of 52 m/s crosses the platform of the length 420 meters in 16 seconds. The length of the train in metres is</p>','<p>420</p>','<p>412</p>','<p>424</p>','<p>398</p>','2','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the platform is the sum of lengths of the train and the platform.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l meters. Speed is 52 m/s. Distance is (420 + l) m.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken will be (420 + l)/52 = 16</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 420 + l = 832</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; l = 412 metres.</p>\r\n<p>So, the length of the train is 412 m.</p>','Easy'),(176,2,'4','','<p>A train with the speed of 35 m/s crosses the platform of the length 300 meters in 22 seconds. The length of the train in metres is</p>','<p>470</p>','<p>420</p>','<p>460</p>','<p>440</p>','1','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the platform is the sum of lengths of the train and the platform.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l meters. Speed is 35 m/s. Distance is (300 + l) m.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken will be (300 + l)/35 = 22</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 300 + l = 770</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; l = 470 metres.</p>\r\n<p>So, the length of the train is 470 m.</p>','Easy'),(177,2,'4','','<p>Harsh and Vijay move towards Mysore stating from Bangalore, at a speed of 50 kmph and 80 kmph respectively. If Vijay reaches Vijayawada 75 minutes earlier then Harsh, what is the distance between Mysore and Bangalore?</p>','<p>250 km</p>','<p>200 km</p>','<p>225 km</p>','<p>275 km</p>','2','<p>Let the distance be d.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.16.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"304\" height=\"47\" />.</p>','Easy'),(178,2,'4','','<p>A train 320 m long is running at a speed of 48 km/hr. It will cross a man coming from the opposite direction at a speed of 6km/hr in</p>','<p>23.33 sec.</p>','<p>26.11 sec.</p>','<p>21.33 sec</p>','<p>21.62 sec</p>','3','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the man is the lengths of the train.</p>\r\n<p>Since both are moving in opposite directions, relative velocity of the train will be u + v = 48 + 6 kmph = 54 kmph = 54 &times; 5/18 m/s = 15m/s.</p>\r\n<p>Distance to be covered will be 320 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, time taken is 320/15 = 21.33 seconds.</p>','Easy'),(179,2,'4','','<p>Two trains are running at 75 km/hr. and 45 km/hr. respectively in the same direction. The faster train completely passes a man sitting in the slower train in 18 seconds. What is the length of the faster train?</p>','<p>150 m</p>','<p>120 m</p>','<p>100 m</p>','<p>135 m</p>','1','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the man is the lengths of the train.</p>\r\n<p>The relative velocity of the train with respect to the passenger is 75 - 45 = 30kmph = 150/18 m/s with respect to the passenger.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken is 18 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>Length of the train is speed &times; time = 150/18 &times; 18 = 150 m.</p>','Easy'),(180,2,'4','','<p>A train takes 15 seconds to pass a pole on the platform of length 150 meters, and pass completely through the platform in 30 seconds. Then the length of the train is</p>','<p>100 m</p>','<p>150 m</p>','<p>80 m</p>','<p>105 m</p>','2','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the pole is the lengths of the train.</p>\r\n<p>Distance to be covered to cross the platform is the sum of lengths of the train and the platform.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l and its speed be v m/s.</p>\r\n<p>It crosses the poll in 15 seconds. So, l = 15v.</p>\r\n<p>It crosses the 150 m platform in 30 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>So, l + 150 = 30v So, 15v = 150 =&gt; v = 10 m/s.</p>\r\n<p>Length of the train is l = 15v = 150 m.</p>','Medium'),(181,2,'4','','<p>A train takes 30 seconds to pass a man on the platform of length 250 meters, and pass completely through the platform in 40 seconds. Then the length of the train is</p>','<p>540 metres</p>','<p>560 metres</p>','<p>600 metres</p>','<p>580 metres</p>','3','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the man is the lengths of the train.</p>\r\n<p>Distance to be covered to cross the platform is the sum of lengths of the train and the platform.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l and its speed be v m/s.</p>\r\n<p>It crosses the man in 30 seconds. So, l = 30v.</p>\r\n<p>It crosses the 250 m platform in 40 seconds. So, l + 250 = 40v.</p>\r\n<p>So, 10v = 250 =&gt; v = 20 m/s.</p>\r\n<p>Length of the train is l = 30v = 600 m.</p>','Medium'),(182,2,'4','','<p>Sam walks to a viewpoint and returns to the starting point by his car and thus takes a total time of 3 hours. He would have gained 1 hour by driving both ways. How long would it have taken for him to walk both ways?</p>','<p>5 hours</p>','<p>4 hours</p>','<p>4 hours 30 minutes</p>','<p>4 hours 45 minutes</p>','2','<p>Let the time taken for him to walk be x and by car be y.</p>\r\n<p>So, x + y = 3 and 2y = 3 - 1 = 2 =&gt; y = 1 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, the time taken to go and come on foot is 2x = 2[3 - 1] = 4 hours.</p>','Medium'),(183,2,'4','','<p>A train running at uniform speed takes 60 seconds to pass a platform of 360 m long and 80 seconds to pass another platform of 560 m long. The length of the train in metres is</p>','<p>180</p>','<p>240</p>','<p>225</p>','<p>200</p>','2','<p>Distance to be covered to cross the platform is the sum of lengths of the train and the platform.</p>\r\n<p>Let the length of the train be l and its speed be v m/s.</p>\r\n<p>So, for the first platform, l + 360 = 60v and for the second platform, l + 560 = 80v.</p>\r\n<p>We get that 20v = 200 =&gt; v = 10 m/s.</p>\r\n<p>Substituting it we get l = 60v - 360 = 600 - 360 = 240 m.</p>','Medium'),(184,2,'4','','<p>Train A starts from x at 1:00 pm &amp; reaches Y at 3:00 pm &amp; train B starts from Y at 1:20 and reaches X on 3:00 so, when does both trains cross each other?</p>','<p>1.55 pm</p>','<p>2.06 pm</p>','<p>2.10 pm</p>','<p>2.00 pm</p>','2','<p>Let them meet after a time x hours from 1 pm.</p>\r\n<p>So, the first train travels the first leg in x hours and the second leg in (2 - x) hours.</p>\r\n<p>For the second train, the legs will be reversed.</p>\r\n<p>So, it will travel second leg in [x - (1/3)] hours and the first leg in <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.23.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"94\" height=\"46\" />&nbsp;= 2 - x hours.</p>\r\n<p>Since they travel with same speeds, ratio of times taken to travel same distances will be equal.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.23.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"98\" height=\"63\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x<sup>2</sup> - (x/3) = 4 - 4x + x<sup>2</sup></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 11x/3 = 4</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x = 12/11 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, they both meet at 1 + (12/11) = 2.06 pm.</p>','Medium'),(185,2,'4','','<p>In a race of 200 meters, A beats S by 25 meters and N by 50 metres. If S and N are running a race of 100 metres with exactly the same speed as before, then by how many metres will S beat N?</p>','<p>13.34</p>','<p>14.28</p>','<p>13.67</p>','<p>14.56</p>','2','<p>By the time S could run 175 m, N could only run 150 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, by the time S will run 100 metres, N would run (150/175) &times; 100 = 85.714 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, S will beat N by 14.286 meters.</p>','Medium'),(186,2,'4','','<p>In a race of 200 meters, A beats S by 40 meters and gets beaten by N by 40 metres. If S and N are running a race of 100 metres with exactly the same speed as before, then by how many metres will S get beaten by N?</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>36</p>','<p>24</p>','<p>27</p>','2','<p>By the time S could run 160 m, A could run 200 m.</p>\r\n<p>By the time A could run 160 m, N could run 200 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, by the time N could run 200 m, then S could run (160/200) &times; 160 = 128 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, by the time N will run 100 metres, S would run (128/2) = 64 m.</p>\r\n<p>So, N will beat S by 36 meters.</p>','Medium'),(187,2,'4','','<p>In a stream, B lies in between A and C such that it is equidistant from both A and C. A boat can go from A to B and back in 6 h while it goes from A to C in 10 h. How long would it take to go from C to A?</p>','<p>2 hours</p>','<p>1 &frac12; hours</p>','<p>2 &frac12; hours</p>','<p>1 hours.</p>','1','<p>Since C is exactly equidistant, the total time that is required to go from A to C and return back is twice the time taken to go from A to B and return back.</p>\r\n<p>If the time taken to go from C to A is x, we can say that x + 10 = 2(6) =&gt; x = 2 hours.</p>','Medium'),(188,2,'4','','<p>Two trains pass each other on parallel lines. Each train is 100 metres long. When they are going in the same direction, the faster one takes 40 seconds to pass the other completely. If they are going in opposite directions they pass each other completely in 8 seconds. Find the speed of the faster train in km/h</p>','<p>54</p>','<p>48</p>','<p>36</p>','<p>50</p>','1','<p>Let the speeds be x and y. The relative speed when going in opposite directions is (x + y) and in same direction is (x - y).</p>\r\n<p>The times taken will be in inverse ratio of the speeds.</p>\r\n<p>So <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.27.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"172\" height=\"32\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x = 3y/2.</p>\r\n<p>Distance taken to cross each other is the length of the two trains which is 100 + 100 = 200 m.</p>\r\n<p>When going in opposite directions, time taken is 8 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>So, x + y = 200/8 = 25 m/s</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 5y/2 = 25</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; y = 10 m/s</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; y = 36 kmph</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x = 54 kmph</p>','Medium'),(189,2,'4','','<p>A boat can be rowed 12 km upstream or 18 km downstream in a period of 2 hrs. What is the speed of the boat in still water in kmph?</p>','<p>1.5</p>','<p>4.5</p>','<p>7.5</p>','<p>6</p>','3','<p>Let the velocity of the boat be u kmph and that of the stream be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken to go 9 km upstream is same as time taken to go 18 km downstream which is 2 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, 2(u - v) = 12; 2(u + v) = 18 =&gt; 4u = 30 =&gt; u = 7.5 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The speed of the boat in still water is 7.5 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(190,2,'4','','<p>A boat can be rowed 10 km upstream or 15 km downstream in a period of 90 minutes. What is the speed of water stream in kmph?</p>','<p>1.66</p>','<p>1</p>','<p>1.5</p>','<p>2</p>','1','<p>Let the velocity of the boat be u kmph and that of the stream be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Time taken to go 10 km upstream is same as time taken to go 15 km downstream which is 3/2 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, 3/2(u - v) = 10; 3/2(u + v) = 15 =&gt; 3v = 5 =&gt; v = 1.66 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The speed of the boat in still water is 1.66 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(191,2,'4','','<p>Two motorists met at 12 a.m. at the Mumbai railway station. After their meeting, one of them proceeded in the East direction while the other proceeded in the North direction. Exactly at 2 PM, they were 120 km apart. Find the speed of the faster motorist if the difference of their speeds is 12 km/h.</p>','<p>48</p>','<p>36</p>','<p>24</p>','<p>30</p>','1','<p>Since they are moving in perpendicular directions, distance between them increases as &radic;(v<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup> + v<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup> ).</p>\r\n<p>The distance increased by 120 km in 2 hours and one of the speeds is 12 km/hr. higher than the other.</p>\r\n<p>So, &radic;(v<sup>2</sup> + (12 + v)<sup>2</sup> ) = 60 =&radic;(36<sup>2</sup> + 48<sup>2</sup> ) =&gt; v = 48 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(192,2,'4','','<p>Two cyclists start simultaneously towards each other from Aurangabad and Ellora, which are 30 km apart. 72 minutes later, they meet and keep pedalling with the same speed without stopping. The second cyclist arrives at Ellora 1 hour later than the first arrives at Aurangabad. Find the speed of the cyclist who stated from Aurangabad.</p>','<p>12 kmph</p>','<p>10 kmph</p>','<p>15 kmph</p>','<p>18 kmph</p>','2','<p>Let the respective speeds be u kmph and v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Since they take 6/5 hours to meet each other, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.31.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"69\" height=\"42\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; u + v = 25.</p>\r\n<p>Since the difference in times of journey is 1 hour, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.31.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"84\" height=\"41\" />&nbsp;= 1</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 30(2u - 25) = 25u - u<sup>2</sup>.</p>\r\n<p>So, u<sup>2</sup> - 35u - 750 = 0 =&gt; u = 15 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, the speeds are 10 kmph and 15 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The cyclist who started at Aurangabad is the slower one and so his speed is 10 kmph.</p>','Medium'),(193,2,'4','','<p>Two trains A and B start simultaneously in the opposite direction from two points A and B and arrive at their destinations 1 and 4 hours respectively after their meeting each other. At what rate does the second train B travel if the first train travels at 80 km per km?</p>','<p>75 kmph</p>','<p>60 kmph</p>','<p>40 kmph</p>','<p>50 kmph</p>','3','<p>Ratio of the speeds if they take u hours and v hours to reach the destination after meeting is &radic;v : &radic;u.</p>\r\n<p>Here u = 1, v = 4.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of the second train is 80 &times; &radic;(1/4) = 40 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(194,2,'4','','<p>Two trains A and B start simultaneously in the opposite direction from two points A and B and arrive at their destinations 16 and 4 hours respectively after their meeting each other. At what rate does the second train B travel if the first train travels at 45 km per km?</p>','<p>60 kmph</p>','<p>22.5 kmph</p>','<p>90 kmph</p>','<p>105 kmph</p>','3','<p>Ratio of the speeds if they take u hours and v hours to reach the destination after meeting is &radic;v : &radic;u.</p>\r\n<p>Here u = 16, v = 4.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of the second train is 45 &times; &radic;(16/4) = 90 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(195,2,'4','','<p>Two trains A and B start simultaneously in the opposite direction from two points A and B and arrive at their destinations 6 and 1.5 hours respectively after their meeting each other. At what rate does the first train A travel if the second train travels at 60 km per km?</p>','<p>30 kmph</p>','<p>90 kmph</p>','<p>120 kmph</p>','<p>45 kmph</p>','3','<p>Ratio of the speeds if they take u hours and v hours to reach the destination after meeting is &radic;v : &radic;u.</p>\r\n<p>Here u = 6, v = 1.5.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of the first train is 60 &times; &radic;(1.5/6) = 120 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(196,2,'4','','<p>Every day a cyclist meets a train at a particular crossing. The road is straight before the crossing and both are travelling in the same direction. The cyclist travels with a speed of 10 Kmph. One day the cyclist comes late by 30 min and meets the train 7 km before the crossing. What is the speed of the train in km/h?</p>','<p>30</p>','<p>40</p>','<p>35</p>','<p>48</p>','3','<p>Since the cyclist comes late by 30 minutes, by the time the train reaches their usual meeting place, the cyclist will be behind by 30/60 &times; 10 = 5 km.</p>\r\n<p>The cyclist meets the train 7 km before the meeting point.</p>\r\n<p>So, by the time the cyclist travels the 2 km distance, the train will reach the meeting point and so has travelled 7 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, speed of the train is (7/2) &times; 10 = 35 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(197,2,'4','','<p>Boat A leaves shore P and Boat B leaves shore Q. (P and Q are opposite shores of a river.) A and B travel at constant speed. But the speeds are not same. Both boats meet at 1.2 Km from P for the first time. In their return journeys (i.e. after touching the shores), they meet again at 1.6 Km from P. Find distance between P and Q.</p>','<p>2.6 km</p>','<p>2 km</p>','<p>2.4 km</p>','<p>1.6 km</p>','1','<p>Let the distance between P and Q be x km.</p>\r\n<p>By the first starting time:</p>\r\n<p>Distance travelled by the two boats are 1.2 and (x - 1.2) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>By the second starting time:</p>\r\n<p>Distance travelled by the two boats are (2x - 1.6) and (x + 1.6) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>Since the speeds of the two boats remain constant, we can say that the ratios of distance d for same times will be constant.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.36.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"127\" height=\"43\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 0.6x + 0.96 = x<sup>2</sup> - 2x + 0.96</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x<sup>2</sup> = 2.6x</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x = 2.6 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance between P and Q is 2.6 km.</p>','Hard'),(198,2,'4','','<p>Boat A leaves shore P and Boat B leaves shore Q. (P and Q are opposite shores of a river.) A and B travel at constant speed. But the speeds are not same. Both boats meet at 1.2 Km from P for the first time. In their return journeys (i.e. after touching the shores), they meet again at 1.6 Km from Q. Find distance between P and Q.</p>','<p>2.6 km</p>','<p>2 km</p>','<p>2.4 km</p>','<p>1.6 km</p>','2','<p>Let the distance between P and Q be x km.</p>\r\n<p>By the first starting time:</p>\r\n<p>Distance travelled by the two boats are 1.2 and (x - 1.2) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>By the second starting time:</p>\r\n<p>Distance travelled by the two boats are (x + 1.6) and (2x - 1.6) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>Since the speeds of the two boats remain constant, we can say that the ratios of distance d for same times will be constant.</p>\r\n<p>So,&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.37.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"126\" height=\"43\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 2.4x - 1.92 = x<sup>2</sup> + 0.4x - 1.92</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x<sup>2</sup> = 2x</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; x = 2 km.</p>\r\n<p>So, the distance between P and Q is 2 km.</p>','Hard'),(199,2,'4','','<p>The metro service has a train going from Mumbai to Pune and Pune to Mumbai every hour. The first one starts at 6 a.m. The trip from one city to another takes 9 hours, and all trains travel at the same speed. How many trains will pass while going from Mumbai to Pune, if you start at 12 noon?</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>15</p>','<p>13</p>','<p>18</p>','2','<p>The first train that this train will encounter is the one that started at 6 AM.</p>\r\n<p>Since this train reaches its destination at 9 PM, the last train it encounters is the train that is ready to start its journey at 9 PM.</p>\r\n<p>The train will also encounter all the trains that have started in between these times at some point in its journey.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total number of trains it encounters is 6 + 9 = 15.</p>','Hard'),(200,2,'4','','<p>Ganesh and Sarah walk up an escalator which moves up with a constant speed. For every three steps that Ganesh takes, Sarah takes two steps. Ganesh gets to the top of the escalator after having taken 40 steps, while Sarah takes only 30 steps to reach the top. If the escalator were turned off, how many steps should each of them take to reach the top?</p>','<p>80</p>','<p>60</p>','<p>120</p>','<p>90</p>','3','<p>Let us assume that the speed of escalator is n steps for every step of Ganesh.</p>\r\n<p>So, we can say that the total distance travelled by Ganesh is 40 + 40n.</p>\r\n<p>Since 2 steps of Sarah is equal to 3 steps of Ganesh, 3n steps of the escalator is equal to 2 steps of Sarah.</p>\r\n<p>So, the total distance travelled by Sarah is 30 + 45n.</p>\r\n<p>Since both travel the same distance up, we can say that 40 + 40n = 30 + 45n =&gt; n = 2.</p>\r\n<p>So, total number of steps to be taken, if the escalator is turned off is 120.</p>','Hard'),(201,2,'4','','<p>Ronaldo had to cover a distance of 120 km. However, he stated 1 hour later than his scheduled time and raced on the car at a speed 10 km/h higher than his originally planned speed and reached the finish at the time he would reach it if he began at the appointed time and travelled with the assumed speed. Find the speed at which he initially planned to complete the journey.</p>','<p>24 kmph</p>','<p>30 kmph</p>','<p>35 kmph</p>','<p>40 kmph</p>','2','<p>Let his normal speed be v kmph. So, his speed during the journey is (v + 10) kmph.</p>\r\n<p>The distance to be covered is 120 km.</p>\r\n<p>The time difference in both the cases is 1 hour.</p>\r\n<p>So, <img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.40.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"93\" height=\"41\" />&nbsp;= 1</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v<sup>2</sup> - 10v = 1200</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v<sup>2</sup> - 10v - 1200 = 0</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v = 30 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>So, his initial planned speed during the journey is 30 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(202,2,'4','','<p>Two trains start from the same point simultaneously and in the same direction. The first train travels at 36 km/h. and the speed of the second train is 33.33 per cent more than the speed of the first train. One hour later, a third train stats from the same point and in the same direction. It overtakes the second train 150 minutes later than it overtook the first train. What is the speed of the third train?</p>','<p>60 kmph</p>','<p>55 kmph</p>','<p>75 kmph</p>','<p>70 kmph</p>','1','<p>The speed of the first train is 36 kmph and that of the second train is 4/3 &times; 36 = 48 kmph.</p>\r\n<p>Let the third train speed be v kmph.</p>\r\n<p>It starts 1 hour later. So, the distance from the first train is 36 km and from the second train is 48 km at the starting point.</p>\r\n<p>Since they are travelling in the same direction, relative speed of the third train is (v - 36) for the first and (v - 48) for the second.</p>\r\n<p>So, according to the question,&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.41.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"141\" height=\"47\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; v = 60 kmph.</p>','Hard'),(203,2,'4','','<p>Ram and Raju stat together from the same point on a circular path and walk around, each at his own pace, until both arrive together at the starting point. If Ram performs the circuit in 2 minutes 34 seconds and Raju in 3 minutes 2 seconds, how many times does Raju go around the path?</p>','<p>11</p>','<p>12</p>','<p>13</p>','<p>10</p>','1','<p>Ratio of their speeds is 182/154 = 11/13.</p>\r\n<p>Since they complete integral number of rounds, the minimum number of round that Ram should complete is 13, by which time Raju will have completed exactly 11 rounds.</p>','Hard'),(204,2,'4','','<p>A bus left point X for point Y. Two hours later a car left point X for Y and arrived at Y at the same time as the bus. If the car and the bus left simultaneously from the opposite ends X and Y towards each other, they would meet 144 minutes after the start. How much time, in hours, did it take the car to travel rom X to Y?</p>','<p>2</p>','<p>4</p>','<p>6</p>','<p>8</p>','2','<p>Let the bus take t hours for the journey. So, the car takes (t - 2) hours for the journey.</p>\r\n<p>If the total distance is d km, then the respective speeds are d/t and d/(t - 2) respectively.</p>\r\n<p>When they travel in opposite directions, the velocities will add up and so, the time taken to meet is&nbsp;<img src=\"tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/125.43.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"257\" height=\"66\" /></p>\r\n<p>=&gt; 5t<sup>2</sup> - 34t + 24 = 0</p>\r\n<p>=&gt; t = 6 hours.</p>\r\n<p>So, the car will take 6 - 2 = 4 hours for the journey.</p>','Hard'),(205,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Raju can do 10% of a work in one day. How many days will he take to complete the work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;He can do 1/10 of the work in one day. So, the number of days required is 10.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(206,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;6 men can do the work in 15 days. How many men are needed to do it in 5 days?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total man days required are 6 &amp;times; 15 = 90.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 5 men can complete it in 90/5 = 18 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(207,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Ramesh alone does a piece of work in 4 days and Suresh does it in 12 days. In how many days will the two do it together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 1/2 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 days&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by Ramesh in a day is 1/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by Suresh in a day be 1/12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work together, work done in a day will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;79&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days required to complete the work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.3.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;35&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 3 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(208,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Pranesh and Sumesh can finish a work in 16 days while Pranesh can do the same work in 24 days. In how many days can Sumesh alone finish the same work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20 days&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Work done by Pranesh in a day is 1/24.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let work done by Sumesh in a day be 1/x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Both worked and completed the job in 16 days. So, they completed 1/16 of the work in one day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;230&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Sumesh can complete it alone in &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;49&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 48 days&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(209,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A can do a piece of work in 10 days and B can do it in 20 days. How much money among the Rs. 90 given for the entire work is to be paid to B if they work together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 60&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 20&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;A can do 1/10 of the work in 1 day and B can do 1/20 of the work in one day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Ratio of the works done is 1/10 : 1/20 = 2 : 1.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the share of B is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;45&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 90 = Rs. 30.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(210,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;6 men and 6 women finish a job in 8 days, while 3 men and 7 women finish it in 10 days. How many days will 10 women take to finish the job?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 2/3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by man be x and a woman be y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So if (6x + 6y) work is done in one day, time taken for completion is 8 and if (3x + 7y) work is done in one day, time taken for completion is 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since work done per day is inversely proportional to the time taken to get the work done&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.6.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;208&quot; height=&quot;51&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 9x = 11y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by 6 men and 6 women in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.6.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;208&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount of time that 10 women take to complete the work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.6.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;129&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(211,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Vinod can do a work in 15 days, Vijay in 25 days and Vinay in 30 days. How long will they take to do the work if they work together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 1/7 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 5/7 days&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by the three in a day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.7.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;198&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days required to do the work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.7.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;102&quot; height=&quot;37&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(212,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Two pipes A and B can fill a tank in 20 and 24 minutes respectively and a third pipe can empty 3 gallons per minute. If A, B and C working together can fill the tank in 15 minutes, the capacity of the tank in gallons is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;180&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one minute is 1/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in one minute is 1/24.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by C in one minute is (-1/x) (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Given that A, B and C working together will complete the work in 15 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;305&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 40.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, C can empty the tank in 40 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, capacity of the tank is 40 &amp;times; 3 = 120 gallons.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(213,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If x men can do a piece of work in 8 days and (x +4) men can do the same work in 6 days. Then x is equal to&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;x men can do work in 8 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;(x+4) men can complete the work in 6 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since no. of persons is inversely proportional to the time taken to get the work done x/(x+4) = 6/8 =&amp;gt; x = 12.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(214,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A plans to complete the work in 150 days and employs 15 persons for the purpose. If they can complete only 40% of the work in 100 days, how many more men should be employed?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;15 persons complete 40% of the work in 100 days. So, they can complete only another 20% in the remaining 50 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In order to complete the remaining 60% of the work in 50 days, 15 &amp;times; (60/20) = 45 men are needed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, extra men required is 45 - 15 = 30.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(215,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Rao can complete the work in 15 days. He and Raju worked together to complete the work and are paid Rs. 100 and Rs. 200 respectively. In how many days can Raju finish the work alone?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 1/3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 1/2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 1/4&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Since Raju is paid double the amount of Rao, he can work twice as fast.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time taken for him to do alone is 15/2 = 7.5 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(216,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If 12 men and 16 women can complete the work in same number of days as 15 men and 12 women, then the ratio of work done by a man and a woman is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:1&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let a man do x work and a woman do y work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since work is completed in same time in both cases, work done is same.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 12x + 16y = 15x + 12y&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 3x = 4y&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x : y = 4 : 3.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(217,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Ashok and Mohan can do a piece of work in 12 days. Mohan and Vinod can do it in 15 days. If Ashok is twice as good as Vinod, then in how many days can Ashok do it alone?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let Vinod take x days t do it alone and so, Ashok will take x/2 days. Let Mohan take y days to complete the work alone.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;273&quot; height=&quot;35&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 60.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Ashok requires 30 days to do the work alone.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(218,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Two pipes can fill a tank in 9 hours and 12 hours respectively. In how much time will they fill the tank when opened together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 1/2 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 1/7 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 2/3 hours&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The work done by C in one hour is 1/12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If A, B are working together, then the work done in one hour is A + B = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.14.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;85&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.14.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;116&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(219,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A tap can fill a tank in 8 hours and another can empty it in 16 hours. If both the taps are opened simultaneously, the time (in hours) to fill the tank is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/8.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The work done by C in one hour is (-1/16) (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If A, B are working together, then the work done in one hour is A + B = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;93&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.15.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;42&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;= 16 hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(220,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;25 persons working 8 hours a day can complete a work in 10 days. In how many days can 40 persons each working 5 hours a day complete it?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total man hour days requited t complete the job is 25 &amp;times; 8 &amp;times; 10 = 2000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, in the second case, man hours per day is 40 &amp;times; 5 = 200.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days taken is 2000/200 = 10.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(221,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A cistern can be filled by a pipe in 15 hours. But due to a leak in the bottom the cistern is just full in 20 hours. When the cistern is full, the leak can empty it in:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30 hours&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/15.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by B in one hour is (-1/x) (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Given that A and B working together, work done in one hour is A + B = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;51&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;It is given that A + B = 1/20 =&amp;gt; &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.17.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;170&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, B on working alone will empty a full tank in 60 hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(222,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A tap can fill a tank in 6 hours and another can empty it in 12 hours. If both the taps are opened simultaneously, the time (in hours) to fill the half-filled tank is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/6.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The work done by C in one hour is (-1/12) (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If A, B are working together, then the work done in one hour is A + B = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.18.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;88&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The tank is already half filled. So, total work to be done is 1/2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.18.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;37&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;= 6 hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(223,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A cistern can be filled by pipes A and B in 20 hours and 30 hours respectively. When full, the tank can be emptied by pipe C in 60 hours. If all the taps be turned on at the same time the cistern will be full in&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30 hours&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/20. Work done by B in one hour is 1/30.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The work done by C in one hour is (-1/60) (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If A, B and C working together, then the work done in one hour is A + B + C = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.19.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;131&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/132.19.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;41&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;= 15 hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(224,3,'1','','&lt;p&gt;32 persons working 10 hours a day can complete a work in 6 days. In how many days can 60 persons each working 4 hours a day complete it?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total man hour days requited to complete the job is 32 &amp;times; 6 &amp;times; 10 = 1920.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, in the second case, man hours per day is 60 &amp;times; 4 = 240.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days taken is 1920/240 = 8.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(225,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A can do a piece of work in 25 days and B can do the same work in 30 days. They work together for 5 days and then A leaves. B will finish the remaining work in&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;19 days&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one day is 1/25.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in one day is 1/30.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work together, work done in 5 days is 5(A + B) =&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;95&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work remaining that is to be completed by B is 1 -&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;74&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days B will work alone is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.1.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;55&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 19 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(226,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Twenty persons can finish the job in 30 days. After how many days should five of them leave so that work is completed in 35 days?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total man days needed to complete the work is 20 &amp;times; 30 = 600.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;20 persons worked for x days and 15 persons worked for (35 - x) days to complete the work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 20x + 15(35 - x) = 600 =&amp;gt; 5x = 75 =&amp;gt; x = 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the 5 members will leave after 5 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(227,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Manoj takes 3 times as much time as Ajay and 2 times as much as Vijay to complete the work. If the three combine to complete it in 1 day, in how many days can Ajay do it alone in?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If Ajay completes x work in a day, then Ajay will complete 3x and Vijay will complete 2x work in a day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The three complete the work in 1 day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + 3x + 2x = 1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 1/6.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Ajay requires 1/3x = 2 days to complete the work alone.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(228,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Rao can complete the work in 15 days. He and Raju worked together to complete the work and are paid Rs. 100 and Rs. 200 respectively. How many days did they work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since Raju is paid twice that of Rao, he works two times faster than Rao.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total work done in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;77&quot; height=&quot;36&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, both will complete the work in 5 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(229,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A work has to be done and Rs. 529 will be paid in direct compensation. If A and B do 18/29 of the work and B and C do &amp;frac34; of the work, what amount will B be paid?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 196&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 210&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 225&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 170&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;It is given that A + B = 18/29 and B + C = 3/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, B = (A + B) + (B + C) - (A + B + C) = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount paid to B is 529 &amp;times; (43/116) = Rs.196.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(230,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A and B can do a piece of work in 6 days. B and C in 4 days and A and C in 5 days. How long will they take to complete the work if they work together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 9/27 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 23/27 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 9/37 days&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A + B in one day is A + B = 1/6.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B + C in one day is C + B = 1/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by A + C in one day is A + C = 1/5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Adding all three, 2(A + B + C) =&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.6.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;103&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt;(A + B + C) = 37/120.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.6.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;130&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(231,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A takes 5 days more than B and 9 days more than C to do a work. If A and B work together, it will take the same time as C does it alone. A completes the work alone in how many days?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let A complete it in x days. So, B will complete it in (x - 5) days and C in (x - 9) days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;According to question,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;126&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 5x = (2x - 5)(x - 9)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 5x = 2x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 23x - 45&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 18x + 45 = 0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 15 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(232,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A can do some work in 24 days. B can do it in 32 days and C can do it in 60 days. They start working together. A left after 6 days and B left after working for 8 days. How many more days are required to complete the whole work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;22&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total work done by A is 6/24 = 1/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total work done by B is 8/32 = 1/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by C is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;97&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of days that C works is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.8.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;45&quot; height=&quot;54&quot; /&gt;= 30 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the work will be completed in another 30 - 8 = 22 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(233,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Two pipes A and B can fill a cistern in 24 minutes and 32 minutes respectively. If both the pipes are opened together, then after how many minutes B should be closed so that the tank is full in 18 minutes?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one minute is 1/24.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in one minute is 1/32.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work together, work done in one minute is A + B =&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;94&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let us assume that tap B is closed after x minutes. Work is completed in 18 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done in first x minutes is 7x/96.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done in the next (18 - x) minutes is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.9.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;118&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since the work is completed in 18 minutes, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.9.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;97&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 3x = 96 - 72 = 24.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, tap B should be closed after 8 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(234,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Deva and Turku can do a piece of work in 45 and 40 days respectively. They began the work together, but Deva leaves after some days and Turku finished the remaining work in 23 days. After how many days did Deva leave?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let Deva work for x days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Turku worked for x + 23 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, we can say that &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;85&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 85x = 17 &amp;times; 45&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 9 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(235,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A pipe having a radius r can fill a tank in 10 hours. How many hours will a pipe having a radius 2r take to fill the tank?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7.5&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If the radius is doubled, flow rate will become four fold and so, the time taken will become one-fourth.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(236,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A completes 2/3 of a certain job in 6 days. B can complete 1/3 of the same job in 8 days and C can complete &amp;frac34; of the work in 12 days. All of them work together for 4 days and then A and C quit. How long will it take for B to complete the remaining work alone?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 1/3 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 2/3 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 days&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Time taken for A to do the work alone is (3/2) &amp;times; 6 = 9 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Time taken for B to do the work alone is 3 &amp;times; 8 = 24 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Time taken for C to do the work alone is (4/3) &amp;times; 12 = 16 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by A and C in 4 days is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.12.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;137&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, B can complete the remaining work in &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.12.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;55&quot; height=&quot;52&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;He worked for 4 days along with A and C.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, he will complete the remaining work in &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.12.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;28&quot; height=&quot;34&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(237,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A and B completed a work together in 5 days. Had A worked at twice the speed and B at half the speed, it would have taken them four days to complete the job. How much time would it take for A alone to do the work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by A and B in one day normally be x and y respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + y = (1/5) = (4/20); 2x + (y/2) = (1/4) = (5/20)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 3x = (6/20)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 1/10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, A can complete the work in 10 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(238,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Two typists of varying skills can do a job in 6 minutes if they work together. If the first typist typed alone for 4 minutes and then the second typist typed alone for 6 minutes, they would be left with 1/5 of the whole work. How many minutes would it take the slower typist to complete the typing job working alone?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since the difference in two situations is that the first typist worked for 2 minutes less, we can say that the typist would take 2 minutes to complete 1/5th of the work or 10 minutes to do complete work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required for the second typist is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;129&quot; height=&quot;57&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;minutes.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(239,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;It takes six days for three women and two men working together to complete a work. Three men would do the same work five days sooner than nine women. How many times does the output of a man exceed that of a woman?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:6&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Let the output of a man per day be x and of a woman be y. So, total work involved is 6(2x + 3y) = 12x + 18y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;3 men will do the same work 5 days faster than 9 women.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;162&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 5&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; (4x + 6y)(x - 3y) = 15xy&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 4x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 21xy - 18y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 6y.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(240,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A tank can be filled by one tap in 20 minutes and by another in 25 minutes. Both the taps are kept open for 5 minutes and then the second is turned off. In how many minutes more is the tank completely filled?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17 1/2&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one minute is 1/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in one minute is 1/25.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work together, work done in one minute is A + B = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.16.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;107&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done in five minutes by both the taps will be (9/100) &amp;times; 5 = 9/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work left is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.16.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;98&quot; height=&quot;38&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the extra time taken by A to fill the tap is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.16.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;45&quot; height=&quot;35&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 11 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(241,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;If 12 men or 18 women can reap a field in 14 days; then the number of days that 8 men and 16 women will take to reap the same field is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;12 men complete the work in 14 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by a man in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;112&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;18 women complete the work in 14 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by a woman in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.17.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;103&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by 8 men and 16 women in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.17.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;143&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Time taken to complete the work will be 63/7 = 9 days&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(242,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;9 men have finished one-third of the work in 10 days. The number of additional men required for finishing the remaining work in 2 more days will be&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;81&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;78&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;55&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Time required for 9 men to complete the work is 20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, if 180 men work at the same time, then the work will be completed in one day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;For the work to be completed in 2 days, number of men required is 180/2 = 90 men.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of additional men required is 90 - 9 = 81.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(243,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A man, a woman or a boy can do a piece of work in 3, 4 and 12 days respectively. How many boys must assist 1 man and 1 women to do the work in 1 day?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by a man in one day is 1/3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by a woman in one day is 1/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by a boy in one day is 1/12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If x boys work with 1 man and 1 woman, then the work will be completed in 1 day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.19.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;188&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 5 boys are required.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(244,3,'2','','&lt;p&gt;If A, B and C together can finish a piece of work in 4 days, A alone in 12 days and B in 18 days, then C alone can do it in&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 days&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in a day is 1/12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in a day is 1/18.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by C in a day be 1/x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the three work together, work will be completed in 4 days. So, the amount of work done in a day is equal to 1/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/133.20.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;242&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days required for C to complete the work is 9 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(245,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Abbot can do some work in 10 days. Bill can do it in 20 days and Clinton can do it in 40 days. They start working in turns with Abbot stating to work on the first day followed by Bill on the second day and by Clinton on the third day and again by Abbot on the fourth day and so on till the work is completed fully. Find the time taken, in days, to complete the work fully?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16 1/2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17 1/7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by Abbott in one day is 1/10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by Bill in one day is 1/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by Clinton in one day is 1/40.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by all the three in one such shift is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.1.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;133&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of such shifts required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.1.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;65&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;5 shifts take 15 days and the work done by then is 5 &amp;times; (7/40) = 35/40 = 7/8.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done on 16th day by Abbot is 1/10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work remaining after the end of 16 days is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.1.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;112&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time taken on 17th day to complete the work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.1.6.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;58&quot; height=&quot;70&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work is completed in &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.1.7.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;35&quot; height=&quot;37&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(246,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;There are three Taps A, B and C in a tank. They can fill the tank in 10 hours, 20 hours and 25 hours respectively. At first, all of them are opened simultaneously. Then after 2 hours, tap C is closed and A and B are kept running. After the 4th hour, tap B is also closed. The remaining work is done by Tap A alone. Find the percentage of the work done by Tap A by itself&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;72%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;68%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;54%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Tap B worked for 4 hours. So, the work done by Tap B is 4/20 = 1/5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Tap C worked for 2 hours. So, work done by Tap C is 2/25.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by Tap A is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;121&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, percentage of work done by Tap A is (18/25) &amp;times; 100% = 72%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(247,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Two taps are running continuously to fill a tank. The 1st tap could have filled it in 5 hours by itself and the second one by itself could have filled it in 20 hours. But the operator failed to realize that there was a leak in the tank from the beginning which caused a delay of one hour in the filling of the tank. Find the time in which the leak would empty a filled tank.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 hours&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Time taken for both the taps to fill the tank is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;114&quot; height=&quot;58&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;hours.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since the time taken is 1 hour more, time taken to fill the tank is 4 + 1 = 5 hours.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by the leak in one hour is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;77&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the leak will empty the filled tank in &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.3.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;76&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(248,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Two pipes A and B can separately fill a cistern in 18 minutes and 24 minutes respectively. If they are turned alternatively for one minute each, how long will it take to fill the cistern?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21 min&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24 min&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25 min&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20 1/2 min&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one minute is 1/18.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in one minute is 1/24.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work alternatively for 1 minute each, work done in two minutes is A + B = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;99&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the number of such shifts required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;134&quot; height=&quot;52&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now after 10 shifts, or 20 minutes, work remaining is 1 - [10 &amp;times; (7/72)) = 2/72.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now, tap A is switched on.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Time taken to complete the work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.4.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;49&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1/2 minute.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total time required is 20 + (1/2) = 20 1/2 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(249,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Two forest officials in their respective divisions were involved in the harvesting of tobacco leaves. One division had an average output of 18 tons from a hectare and the other division, which had 10 hectares less land, dedicated to tobacco leaves, got 21 tons of tobacco from a hectare. As a result, the second division harvested 120 tons of tobacco leaves more than the first. How many tons of tobacco leaves did the first division harvest?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1980&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2100&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1860&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1740&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the first division have x acres of land. So, the total product they got is 18x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The second division has (x - 10) acres of land and the total produce they got is 21(x - 10).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The second division produced 120 tons more than the first.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, according to the question, 21x - 210 = 18x + 120 =&amp;gt; 3x = 330 =&amp;gt; x = 110.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total production from the first division is 18x = 18 &amp;times; 110 = 1980 tons.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(250,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Three diggers dug a ditch of 324 m deep in six days working simultaneously. During one shift, the third digger digs as many metres more than the second as the second digs more than the first. The third digger&amp;rsquo;s work in 10 days is equal to the first digger&amp;rsquo;s work in 14 days. How many metres does the first digger dig per shift?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the metres that they dig for A, B, C per shift be x, y, z.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, z - y = y - x and 10z = 14x&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x : z = 5 : 7&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; y = 6.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the metres dug be 5k, 6k, 7k per day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work per shift is 5k + 6k + 7k = 18k = 324/6&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; k = 3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the first digger digs 15m per day.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(251,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Two girls Rama and Asha are working on an embroidery design. If Asha worked alone, she would need eight hours more to complete the design than if they both worked together. Now if Rama worked alone, it would need 4.5 hours more to complete the design than they both working together. What time, in hours, would it take Rama alone to complete the design?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;13.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let us assume Asha takes x hours and Rama takes y hours to do the work alone.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time taken by both working together is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;101&quot; height=&quot;55&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + 8 =&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.7.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;43&quot; height=&quot;38&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 8x + 8y = 0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;And y + 4.5 =&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.7.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;47&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 4.5(x + y) = 0.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.7.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;68&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;=&amp;gt; x:y = 4:3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let x = 4k =&amp;gt; 4(k + 2) = 12k/7 =&amp;gt; 28k + 56 = 12k =&amp;gt; k = 3.5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time taken by Rama to do it alone is 3 &amp;times; 3.5 = 10.5 hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(252,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A can do a piece of work in 12 days and B can do it in 18 days. They started the work together but A left 3 days before the completion of work. The total number of days to complete the work is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 3/5 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 1/5 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 1/5 days&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one day is 1/12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in one day is 1/18.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work completed in one day if both work together is A + B = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.8.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;98&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A left 3 days before the completion of work. So, only B worked for the last 3 days. So, work done by B alone is (3/18) = (1/6).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, A and B combined to complete of the &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.8.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;71&quot; height=&quot;35&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of days they worked together is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.8.6.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;41&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 6 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total time taken for completion of project is 6 + 3 = 9 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(253,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Vinod can do a work in 15 days, Vijay in 25 days and Vinay in 30 days. How long will they take to do the work if they work together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 1/7 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;70 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20 days&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by Vinod in a day is 1/15.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by Vijay in a day is 1/25.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by Vinay in a day is 1/30.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the three work together, work done in a day will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.9.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;179&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days required to complete the work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.9.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;129&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(254,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Ashok and Mohan can do a piece of work in 12 days. Mohan and Raju can do it in 15 days. If Ashok is twice as good as Raju, then in how many days can Ashok do it alone?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by Raju per day be x, then the work done by Ashok per day is 2x. Let the work done by Mohan in a day be y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 2x + y = (1/12) = (5/60); x + y = (1/15) = (4/60) =&amp;gt; x = 1/60 =&amp;gt; 2x = 1/30.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Ashok can do it alone in 30 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(255,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;In a factory, there are three shifts of work on a day comprising eight hours each. During the three shifts, the average work efficiency of workers is 80%, 70% and 50% respectively. A work is completed in 60 days by working in first shift only. If the work is done during all the three shifts, then how many less days are required to complete the work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If 80% is completed in the morning shift, then the work completed in all 3 shifts is 80% + 70% + 50% = 200% because each shift is of equal time.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, ratio of work done in the two cases is 80:200 = 2:5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio of times taken is 5:2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time taken in the second case is (2/5) &amp;times; 60 = 24 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 60 - 24 = 36 less days are required to complete the work.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(256,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A takes 4 days to do a work. B takes twice as long as A. C takes twice as long as B and D takes twice as long as C. They are made in groups of two. The first pair takes two third of the time taken by the second pair. What is the combination of the first pair?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;A, D&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;B, C&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;A, C&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;B, D&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Time taken by A is 4 days. Time taken by B is 2 &amp;times; 4 = 8 days. Time taken by C is 2 &amp;times; 8 = 16 days and time taken by D is 2 &amp;times; 16 = 32 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since the time taken by the two groups are in the ratio 2:3, work done by each pair should be in the ratio 3:2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by A, B, C and D in a day is 1/4, 1/8, 1/16, 1/32 respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If work done by the two pairs are 3x and 2x per day, then 5x = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;268&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the first pair does work &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.12.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;142&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(257,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;In NutsAndBolts factory, one machine produces only nuts at the rate of 100 nuts per minute and needs to be cleaned for 5 minutes after production of every 1000 nuts. Another machine produces only bolts at the rate of 75 bolts per minute and needs to be cleaned for 10 minutes after production of every 1500 bolts. If both the machines start production at the same time, what is the minimum duration required for producing 9000 pairs of nuts and bolts?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 hours, 10 minutes&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 hours 10 minutes&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 hours 15 minutes&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total time taken for the first machine to produce 9000 nuts is the time the machine takes for producing 9000 nuts and the cleaning of the machine for 9000/1000 - 1 = 8 times. The cleaning done after the 9th shift need not be counted as the nuts are already produced.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time required is T1 = (9000/100) + (8 &amp;times; 5) = 90 + 40 = 130 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total time taken for the second machine to produce 9000 bolts is the time the machine takes for producing 9000 bolts and the cleaning of the machine for 9000/1500 - 1 = 5 times. The cleaning done after the 6th shift need not be counted as the bolts are already produced.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time required is T2 = (9000/75) + (6 &amp;times; 10) = 120 + 60 = 180 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time taken is max [T1, T2] = 180 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(258,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A company manufactures two products X and Y. One unit of X requires 3 units of material A and 2 units of material B while one unit of Y requires 2 units of material A and 5 units of material B. If 25 units of each product were to be produced, calculate the requirement of material B.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;175&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;25 units of X and 25 units of Y are produced.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total amount of material B required is (25 &amp;times; 2) + (25 &amp;times; 5) = 175 units.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(259,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A painter needs 3 days to paint the walls of a room. How long would it take working at the same rate, to paint a room twice as long, twice as wide and twice as high?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 days&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since he is painting, the area of 4 walls is of interest in this case. The area of the 4 walls is 2h(l + b).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the length, breadth and height are all doubled, the area becomes 4 times.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, he requires 4 &amp;times; 3 = 12 days to do the entire work.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(260,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Each of A, B and C need a certain unique time to do a certain work. C needs 2 hours more than A to complete the work. Working together, they require 30 minutes to complete 25% of the job. The work also gets completed if A and B stat working together and A leaves after 2 hours and B works for a further 4 hours. How much work does C do per hour?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33.33%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the times taken by A,B,C to do the work completely be x, y, (x + 2) hours completely.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;All 3 finish the work in 2 hours.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;124&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A works for 2 hours and B for 6 hours to complete the work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.16.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;147&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 2x + 4 = y&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.16.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;47&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.16.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;241&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt;10y - 24 = y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 4y&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 14y + 24 = 0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; y = 12 hours.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required by C to complete the work is x + 2 = (y/2) = 6 hours and work done per hour is 100/6% = 16.67%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(261,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A tank has four inlets. Through the first three inlets, the tank can be filled in 24 minutes; through the second, the third and the fourth inlet, it can be filled in 30 minutes: and through the first and the fourth inlet, in 40 minutes. How much time, in minutes, will it take all the four inlets to fill up the tank?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the inlets do x, y, z, w work per minute.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + y + z = (1/24), y + z + w = (1/30), x + w = (1/40).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Adding all three, 2(x + y + w + z) =&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;213&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x + y + w + z = (1/20).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, all the four inlets require 20 minutes to fill the tank.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(262,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A tank of capacity 50 litres has an inlet and an outlet tap. If both are opened simultaneously, the tank is filled in 5 minutes. But if the outlet flow rate is doubled and taps opened the tank never gets filled up. Which of the following can be outlet flow rate in litres/min?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the capacity of the inlet pipe be x litre/min. If the outlet rate is doubled, it will be greater than the inlet flow and then the tank will never fill up. So, the outlet capacity is greater than x/2 litre/min. Let it be y litre/min. So y &amp;ge; x/2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both are opened simultaneously, the tank is filled in 5 minutes. So, the volume filled in 1 minute is 50/5 = 10 litres.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x - y = 10&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; y = x - 10 &amp;ge; x/2&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x &amp;ge; 20&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; y &amp;ge; 10 litres/min.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(263,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;According to a plan, a drilling team had to drill to a depth of 600 metres below the ground level. For the first four days, the team drilled as per the plan. However, subsequently finding that their resources were getting underutilised according to the plan, it stated to drill 5 metres more than the plan every day. Therefore, a day before the planned date they had drilled to a depth of 610 metres. How many days did they drill altogether?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the number of days initially required be x. So, they worked for (x - 1) days and the initial plan is to drill 600/x metres per day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Drilling done in 4 days will be 2400/x metres. The remaining amount is 600 - (2400/x) = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.19.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;93&quot; height=&quot;38&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, according to the question, they dug an extra 10 metres and the time taken is (x - 1 - 4) = (x - 5) days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the work per day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.19.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;138&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;. It is 5 m more than normal.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.19.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;132&quot; height=&quot;38&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 5&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 610x - 2400 - 600x + 3000 = 5x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 25x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 5x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 35x - 600 = 0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 7x - 120 = 0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 15 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, they actually worked for 15 - 1 = 14 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(264,3,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Gopal is four times as good a workman as Ramu and therefore is able to finish the job in 45 days less than Ramu. In how many days will they finish the job working together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since Gopal is 4 times as good as Ramu, the times taken to finish a work are in the ratio 1:4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the times be x and 4x days respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 3x = 45 =&amp;gt; x = 15.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Gopal finishes the work in 15 days and Ramu takes 60 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work together, work done in a day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/134.20.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;126&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, both working together will finish the work in 12 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(265,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Chris is three times as good a workman as Robert and therefore is able to finish the job in 30 days. In how many days will they finish the job working together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since Chris is three times as good a workman as Robert, the times taken to finish a work are in the ratio 1 : 3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the number of days taken by Chris and Robert are x and 3x respectively, then x = 30 =&amp;gt; 3x = 90.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time taken for both of them to complete the work together is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/135.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;141&quot; height=&quot;56&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(266,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A tank has four inlets. Through the first two inlets, the tank can be filled in 6 minutes; through the last two inlets, it can be filled in 12 minutes: and through the first, second and the fourth inlets, in 5 minutes. How much time, in minutes, will it take the third inlet to fill up the tank?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the inlets do x, y, z, w work per minute respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + y = (1/6), z + w = (1/12), x + y + w = (1/5).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/135.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;219&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/135.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;106&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the third inlet requires 20 minutes to fill the tank.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(267,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A company manufactures two products X and Y. One unit of X requires 2 units of material A and 1 units of material B while one unit of Y requires 4 units of material A and 3 units of material B. If 40 units of each product were to be produced, calculate the requirement of material B.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;160&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;40 units of X and 25 units of Y are produced.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total amount of material B required is (40 &amp;times; 1) + (40 &amp;times; 3) = 160 units.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(268,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Ashok and Mohan can do a piece of work in 12 days. Mohan and Raju can do it in 15 days. If Ashok is three times as good as Raju, then in how many days can Ashok do it alone?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by Raju per day be x, then the work done by Ashok per day is 3x. Let the work done by Mohan in a day be y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;406&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Ashok can do it alone in 3x = 3/120 = 40 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(269,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A and B can do a piece of work in 15 days. B and C can do it in 20 days. If A is twice as good as C, then in how many days can A and C complete the work together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by C per day be x, then the work done by A per day is 2x. Let the work done by B in a day be y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;393&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, A and C can complete the work together in &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.5.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;136&quot; height=&quot;54&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(270,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A can do a work in 10 days, B in 12 days and C in 15 days. How long will they take to do the work if they work together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7.5 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 days&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in a day is 1/10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in a day is 1/12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by C in a day is 1/15.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the three work together, work done in a day will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.6.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;248&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time required is 5 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(271,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Ramesh alone does a piece of work in 20 days and Suresh does it in 30 days. In how many days will the two do it together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 days&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by Ramesh in a day is 1/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by Suresh in a day be 1/30.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work together, work done in a day will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;99&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days required to complete the work is 12 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(272,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A can do a piece of work in 15 days and B can do it in 30 days. They started the work together but A left 6 days before the completion of work. The total number of days to complete the work is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 days&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A and B in one day is 1/15 and 1/30 respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the work be completed in x days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A left 6 days before the completion of work. So, A worked for (x - 6) days and B worked for x days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;402&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total time taken for completion of project is 14 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(273,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Two pipes A and B can separately fill a cistern in 10 minutes and 8 minutes respectively. If they are turned alternatively for one minute each, how long will it take to fill the cistern?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 minutes&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8.5 minutes&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40/9 minutes&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 minutes&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one minute is 1/10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in one minute is 1/8.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If both work alternatively for 1 minute each, work done in two minutes is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;145&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the number of such shifts required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.9.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;136&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now after 4 shifts, or 8 minutes, work remaining is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.9.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;124&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now, tap A is switched on.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Time taken to complete the work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.9.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;81&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;minute.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total time required is 8 + 1 = 9 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(274,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;There are three Taps A, B and C in a tank. They can fill the tank in 12 hours, 15 hours and 20 hours respectively. At first, all of them are opened simultaneously. Then after 1 hour, tap C is closed and A and B are kept running. After the 3rd hour, tap B is also closed. The remaining work is done by Tap A alone. Find the percentage of the work done by Tap A by itself&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;70%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;72%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Tap B worked for 3 hours. So, the work done by Tap B is 3/15 = 1/5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Tap C worked for 1 hour. So, work done by Tap C is 1/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by Tap A is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;153&quot; height=&quot;38&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, percentage of work done by Tap A is (3/4) x 100% = 75%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(275,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If A, B and C together can finish a piece of work in 5 days, A alone in 15 days and B in 20 days, then C alone can do it in&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 days&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 days&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in a day is 1/15.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by B in a day is 1/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by C in a day be 1/x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the three work together, work will be completed in 5 days. So, the amount of work done in a day is equal to 1/5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;328&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days required for C to complete the work is 12 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(276,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;9 men have finished half the work in 13 days. The number of men required for finishing the entire work in 3 days will be&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;81&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;78&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;55&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Time required for 9 men to complete the work is 26.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, if 26 x 9 = 234 men work at the same time, then the work will be completed in one day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;For the work to be completed in 3 days, number of men required is 234/3 = 78 men.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(277,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If 10 men or 15 women can reap a field in 10 days; then the number of days that 5 men and 30 women will take to reap the same field is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;10 men complete the work in 10 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by a man in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;109&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;15 women complete the work in 10 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, work done by a woman in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.13.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;109&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work done by 5 men and 30 women in one day is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.13.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;172&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Time taken to complete the work will be 4 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(278,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;It takes 10 days for 5 women and 2 men working together to complete a work. 5 men would do the same work two days sooner than 10 women. Find the ratio of the work done by a man to that of a woman?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4: 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3: 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5: 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5: 1&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the output of a man per day be x and of a woman be y. So, total work involved is 10(5y + 2x) = 50y + 20x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;5 men would do the same work two days sooner than 10 women.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;415&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.14.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;345&quot; height=&quot;33&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(279,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A and B completed a work together in 12 days. Had A worked at half the speed and B at three times the speed, it would have taken them 8 days to complete the job. How much time would it take for A alone to do the work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the work done by A and B in one day normally be x and y respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;611&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, A can complete the work in 20 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(280,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A and B can do a piece of work in 50 and 40 days respectively. They began the work together, but A leaves after some days and B finished the remaining work in 22 days. After how many days did A leave?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let A work for x days. So, B worked for (x + 22) days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, we can say that &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;428&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, A leaves after 10 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(281,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Two pipes A and B can fill a cistern in 20 minutes and 40 minutes respectively. If both the pipes are opened together, then after how many minutes B should be closed so that the tank is full in 15 minutes?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A and B in one minute is 1/20 and 1/40 respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let us assume that tap B is closed before x minutes from the completion of work. Work is completed in 15 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, A worked for 15 minutes and B worked for (15 - x) minutes to complete the work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;438&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;minutes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, tap B should be closed before 5 minutes or after 10 minutes from the start.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(282,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A work has to be done and Rs. 567 will be paid in direct compensation. If A and B do 10/21 of the work and A and C do 2/3 of the work, what amount will B be paid?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;189&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;81&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;297&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;It is given that &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.18.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;83&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.18.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;106&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.18.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;416&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.18.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;151&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount paid to B is 567 x (1/3) = Rs.189.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(283,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;65 persons working 8 hours a day can complete a work in 6 days. In how many days can 39 persons each working 10 hours a day complete it?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total man hour days requited to complete the job is 65 x 6 x 8 = 3120.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, in the second case, man hours per day is 39 x 10 = 390.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of days taken is 3120/390 = 8.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(284,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A cistern can be filled by pipes A and B in 30 hours and 40 hours respectively. When full, the tank can be emptied by pipe C in 60 hours. If all the taps be turned on at the same time the cistern will be full in&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30 hours&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/30. Work done by B in one hour is 1/40.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The work done by C in one hour is -1/60 (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If A, B and C working together, then the work done in one hour is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.20.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;286&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.20.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;79&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(285,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A tap can fill a tank in 9 hours and another can empty it in 12 hours. If both the taps are opened simultaneously, the time (in hours) to fill one third filled tank is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The work done by C in one hour is -1/12 (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If A, B are working together, then the work done in one hour is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.21.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;141&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The tank is already one third full. So, total work to be done is 2/3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.21.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;77&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(286,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A cistern can be filled by a pipe in 12 hours. But due to a leak in the bottom the cistern is just full in 15 hours. When the cistern is full, the leak can empty it in:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45 hours&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30 hours&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Work done by A in one hour is 1/12. Let the work done by B in one hour is -1/x (negative because it empties the tank).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Given that A and B working together, work done in one hour is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.22.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;109&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;It is given that &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.22.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;223&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, B on working alone will empty a full tank in 60 hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(287,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Vani and Rani can do a piece of work in 24 days. Vani and Mani can do it in 30 days. If Rani is twice as good as Mani, then in how many days can Mani do it alone?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;90&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let Mani take x days to do it alone and so, Rani will take x/2 days. Let Vani take y days to complete the work alone.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.23.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;77&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.23.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;311&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Mani requires 120 days to do the work alone.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(288,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If 13 men and 19 women can complete the work in same number of days as 16 men and 13 women, then the ratio of work done by a man and a woman is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3: 4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4: 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2: 1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3: 2&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let a man do x work and a woman do y work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since work is completed in same time in both cases, work done is same.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.24.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;339&quot; height=&quot;24&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(289,3,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A plans to complete the work in 60 days and employs 60 persons for the purpose. If they can complete only 24% of the work in 30 days, how many more men should be employed?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;115&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;130&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;190&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;60 persons complete 24% of the work in 30 days. So, they can complete only another 24% in the remaining 30 days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In order to complete the total remaining 76% of the work in 30 days, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/missed%20images/135.25.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;117&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;men are needed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, extra men required is 190 - 60 = 130.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(290,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Ratio between two numbers is 3:2 and their difference is 225, then the smaller number is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;450&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;675&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;900&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;225&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If the numbers are 3x and 2x, then the difference is 3x - 2x =&amp;gt; x =225.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the smaller number is 2x = 225 &amp;times; 2 = 450.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(291,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The speeds of three cars are in the ratio 3:4:5. The ratio between the times taken by these cars to travel the same distance is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:4:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:3:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20:15:12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20:12:15&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the distance is d, then the times taken are in the ratio &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;53&quot; height=&quot;37&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 20 : 15 : 12&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(292,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The mean proportion between 9 and 36 is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;27&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The mean proportion between two numbers a and b is &amp;radic;(ab).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here a = 9, b = 36.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, mean proportional is &amp;radic;(9 &amp;times; 36) = 3 &amp;times; 6 = 18.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(293,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Two numbers are in the ratio 7:9. If 12 is subtracted from each of them, the ratio becomes 3:5. The product of the numbers is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;63&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;252&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;567&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;240&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the numbers be 7x and 9x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;91&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 35x - 60 = 27x - 36&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 8x = 24&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the numbers are 21 and 27. Their product is 21 &amp;times; 27 = 567.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(294,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A total amount of Rs. 1800 is to be divided among A,B and C in such a way that half of A&#039;s part, one third of B&#039;s part and one fourth of C&#039;s part is equal. The A&#039;s part is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1200&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the divisions be x, y, z.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;64&quot; height=&quot;36&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= k(let)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 2k; y=3k ; z=4k&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x:y:z = 2:3:4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;x + y + z = 1800.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 9k = 1800&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; k = 200.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A&amp;rsquo;s part is 2k = Rs.400.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(295,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If the ratio of the areas of two squares is 1:4, the ratio of their perimeters is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2:1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:4&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of perimeters of two squares if their areas are known is p&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;:p&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = &amp;radic;(A&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; ) : &amp;radic;(A&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; ).&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(296,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;15 litres of a mixture contains 20% alcohol and the rest is water. If 3 litres of water is mixed in it, the percentage of alcohol in the new mixture will be&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Amount of alcohol initially is 20 &amp;times; (15/100) = 3 litres. The remaining 12 litres is water.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since alcohol is not being added, it will remain at 3 litres. But the amount of water will become 12 + 3 = 15 litres.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the new concentration of alcohol is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;51&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100% = 16.67%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(297,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;In what proportion must water be mixed with spirit to gain 16 2/3% by selling it at cost price?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:3&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;To gain 50/3%, let us assume x% of water is mixed, so, for every 1 liter of spirit, there is only (1 - x) litres of pure spirit. So, selling price is C but the original cost price is (1 - x)C.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, profit percentage is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.8.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;344&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Ratio of water to spirit is (1/6):(5/6) = 1:5.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(298,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A and B are two alloys of gold and copper prepared by mixing metals in the ratio 7:2 and 7:11 respectively. If equal quantities of alloys are melted to form a third alloy C. Find the ratio of gold and copper in C.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14:13&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7:6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11:7&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Equal quantities of alloys of gold and copper are mixed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, if x kg of A are mixed, then the gold and copper are 7x/9 and 2x/9 kgs respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, if x kg of B are mixed, then the gold and copper are 7x/18 and 11x/18 kgs respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, final ratio is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;156&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 21x:15x = 7:5&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(299,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The incomes of two people are in the ratio 4:5 and expenditures in the ratio 7:8 respectively. The total savings between the two of them is Rs.3000 and that is split in the ratio 1:2. Find their total income.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 15,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 18,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 27,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 20,000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The savings of the two persons are in the ratio 1:2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;90&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 8x - 14y = 5x - 8y&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 3x = 6y&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 2y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Saving of the first person is 4x - 7y = 4x - (7/2x) = (x/2) = 1000&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = Rs.2000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total earning of two persons is 4x + 5x = 9x = Rs.18,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(300,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If x:y = 2:3 then what is the value of (x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 2y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;):(x + 3y)&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2:1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4:1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data Insufficient&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;In this case, the degree of numerator is 2 and that of denominator is 1. So, we cannot uniquely determine the value because the degrees are not same.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;x = 2k; y = 3k&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; (x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 2y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;):(x + 3y) = 22k&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;:11k = 2k:1.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the value depends on the variable k, which is not given here.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(301,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The students in three batches at NIT Rourkela are in the ratio 2:3:5. If 20 students are increased in each batch, the ratio changes to 4:5:7. The total number of students in the three batches before the increases were&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;160&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;(2x + 20):(3x + 20):(5x + 20) = 4:5:7&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 10x + 100 = 12x + 80&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of students before the increase is 2x + 3x + 5x = 10x = 100.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(302,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A cat takes 5 leaps for every 4 leaps of a dog, but 3 leaps of the dog are equal to 4 leaps of the cat. What is the ratio of the speed of the cat to that of the dog?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15:16&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16:15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Ratio of the length of each leap for dog and cat are &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;38&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;=&amp;gt; 4 : 3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, ratio of speeds of cat and dog is 3 &amp;times; 5:4 &amp;times; 4 = 15 : 16&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(303,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Three men rent a farm for Rs. 15000 per annum. A puts 100 cows in the farm for 3 months. B puts 50 cows for 6 months and C puts 400 cows for 3 months. What percentage of the total expenditure should A pay?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Ratio of their usage is (100 &amp;times; 3):(50 &amp;times; 6):(400 &amp;times; 3) = 1:1:4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, percentage of share paid by A is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;70&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100% = 100/6% = 16.67%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(304,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If the ratio of the ages of Robert and Roger is 6:5 at present, and fifteen years from now, the ratio will get changed to 9:8, then find Robert&amp;rsquo;s present age in years.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;42&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the present ages be 6x and 5x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;85&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 48x + 120 = 45x + 135&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, present age of Robert is 6x = 30 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(305,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;At constant temperature, pressure of a definite mass of gas is inversely proportional to the volume. If the pressure is reduced by 20%, find the respective change in volume&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33.33%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The product will remain constant.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 100 &amp;times; 100 = 120 &amp;times; V&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; V = 10000/120.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Percentage change in volume is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;83&quot; height=&quot;59&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100% = 100 - 83.33% = 16.67%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(306,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If the work done by (x - 1) men in (x + 1) days is to the work done by (x + 2) men in (x - 1) days is in the ratio 9 : 10, then the value of x is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total ratio of work done in both cases is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;142&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;=&amp;gt; x = 8.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(307,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A mixture contains milk and water in the ratio 5:1. On adding 5 litres of water, the ratio of milk to water becomes 5:2. The quantity of milk in the mixture, in litres, is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;5 litres of water is added. The amount of milk will remain the same.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let there be x litres of mixture initially, so, the amount of milk is 5x/(5 + 1) = 5x/6&amp;nbsp;and the amount of water is x/6.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Finally, the amount of milk is still 5x/6 but the amount of water is (x/6) + 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.18.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;174&quot; height=&quot;65&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 30 litres.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the initial amount of milk in the mixture is 5 &amp;times; (30/6) = 25 litres.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(308,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If 2x = 3y = 4z, then x:y:z is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15:16&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16:15&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Let 2x = 3y = 4z = k&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x:y:z = (1/2):(1/3):(1/4) = 6:4:3&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(309,4,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If 30 oxen can plough 1/7th of a field in 2 days, how many days will 18 oxen take to do the remaining work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;30 oxen plough 1/7th in 2 days. So, 1 oxen in one day will do &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.20.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;87&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are 18 oxen and the work to be completed is 6/7.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time taken is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/142.20.2_1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;97&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 20 days.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(310,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of Rs. 53 is divided among A, B, C in such a way that A gets Rs. 7 more than B and B to gets Rs. 8 more than C. Then the ratio of their shares is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10:18:25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25:18:10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25:10:!8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10:25:18&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If C gets x, then B gets (x + 8) and A gets (x + 8 + 7) = (x + 15).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + x + 8 + x + 15 = 3x + 23 = 53 =&amp;gt; 3x = 30 =&amp;gt; x = 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, ratio of their shares is 25:18:10.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(311,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Two equal glasses are 1/2 and 2/3 full of milk respectively. The two are completely filled up with water. The contents of the two glasses are then mixed in another vessel. The ratio of milk and water in the vessel is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4:3&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total milk is (x/2) + (2x/3) = (7x/6).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total amount of water will be (2x) - (7x/6) = (5x/6).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Ratio required is 7:5.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(312,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;An amount is to be distributed among A, B and C in the ratio 3:7:5 respectively. If the difference in the shares of A and B is Rs. 7,600/ - what will be the share of C?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 7500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 8500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 9500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6500&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the shares be 3x, 7x, 5x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 7x - 3x = 4x = 7600&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 1900.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, share of C is 5x = Rs.9500.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(313,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of the number of gents to ladies in a party was 2:3. When 20 more gents joined the group, the ratio was reversed. The number of ladies in the party was&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the initial number of gents and ladies be 2x and 3x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;72&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 4x + 40 = 9x&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 8.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the number of ladies in the party is 3x = 24.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(314,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Two numbers are such that their difference, their sum and their product are in the ratio of 1:7:24. The product of the numbers is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;96&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;192&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the sum is 7 times the difference, the numbers will be in the ratio 4 : 3. Let them be 4x and 3x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now (4x - 3x) : (4x &amp;times; 3x) = 1 : 24&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; (1/12x) = 1/24&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the product required is 12 x 2 = 48.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(315,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 180 contained in a box is made up of one rupee, 50 paise, and 25 paise coins in the proportion of 2:3:4. What is the number of 50 paise coins?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;180&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;2 (1rupee) coins, 3 (50p) coins and 4 (25p) coins give a total of Rs. 4.50.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of such sets present is 180/4.50 = 40.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of 50p coins is 40 &amp;times; 3 = 120.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(316,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;81 is divided into three parts, such that half of the first part, one-third of the second part and one-fourth of the third part are equal. The third part is more than the first by&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;54&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the divisions be x, y, z.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;72&quot; height=&quot;35&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= k(let)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 2k; y = 3k; z = 4k&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x : y : z = 2 : 3 : 4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;It is given that x + y + z = 9k = 81 =&amp;gt; k = 9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, difference between the third and first parts is 2k = 18.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(317,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of number of boys and girls in a school is 3 : 2. If 20% of the boys and 30% of the girls are scholarship holders, the percentage of students who do not get scholarship is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.75&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.8334&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.6667&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If the number of boys are 3x and the total number of girls are 2x, then the total number of students who get a scholarship is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;191&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1.2 x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage of students who do not get a scholarship is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.8.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;72&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100% = 80%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(318,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;In what ratio must 25% alcohol be mixed with 60% alcohol to get a mixture of 40% alcohol strength?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:5&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the ratio be x:y. So, the total amount of alcohol in part 1 is x/4 and in part 2 is 3y/5. The amount of water in part 1 is 3x/4 and in part 2 is 2y/5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;201&quot; height=&quot;70&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 15x + 36y = 30x + 16y =&amp;gt; 15x = 20y =&amp;gt; x : y = 4 : 3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 4 : 3.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(319,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;An employer reduces the number of his employees in the ratio of 9 : 8 and increases their wages in the ratio 14 : 15. In what ratio the wages bill is increased or decreased.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;increases 21:20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;decreases 20:21&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;increases 6:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;decreases 5:6&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of two wage bills is (9 &amp;times; 14) : (8 &amp;times; 15) = 21 : 20.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(320,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Eight people enter a partnership. Six of them bring in Rs.30 each. The seventh brings in Rs.10 more than the average of all eight and the eighth brings in Rs.55. What is the total sum brought in?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 245&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 280&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 320&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 300&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the average of the group be x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total amount is (6 &amp;times; 30) + (x + 10) + 55 = 8x =&amp;gt; 7x = 245 =&amp;gt; x = 35.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total money is 8x = 8 &amp;times; 35 = Rs.280.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(321,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A combo pack having a bulb and a tube light costs Rs. 52. If the cost of the bulb drops by 20% and the cost of the tube light escalates by 50%, the pack would cost Rs. 50. Find the price of a tube light?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 18&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the bulb cost x and the light cost y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + y = 52; 0.8x + 1.5y = 50 =&amp;gt; 4x + 7.5y = 250; 4x + 4y = 208 =&amp;gt; 3.5y = 42 =&amp;gt; y = 12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the cost of a tube light is Rs. 12.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(322,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A telephone company charges a rental of Rs.500 per month and allows 250 free calls per month. Calls are charged at Rs.1.00 per call when number of calls exceeds 250 and the per call charge increase by Rs.0.25 every time number of calls is greater than the next multiple of 250. Find the ratio of cost per call to the customer when the number of calls made is 175 and 350 per month.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2:1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6:5&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since 175 calls fall within the 250 free call range, cost for 175 calls is Rs.500.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Cost per call in this case is 500/175 = 20/7.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;For 350 calls, it is 100 calls more than the 250 call slab. So, the total cost is 500 + 100 = Rs.600.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Cost per call in this case is 600/350 = 12/7.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 20/7 : 12/7 = 5:3.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(323,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Divide Rs. 2000 among A, B, C and D so that A and B together get thrice as much as C and D together. B gets four times of what C gets and C gets 1.5 times as much as D. Now the value of what B gets is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,250&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the amount C and D get be x and y respectively. So, the amount that A and B get together is 3(x + y).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total amount is 4(x + y) = 2000 =&amp;gt; x + y = 500.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;x = 1.5y =&amp;gt; y = 500/2.5 = 200 =&amp;gt; x = 1.5y = 300.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the value obtained by B is 4x = 4 &amp;times; 300 = Rs.1200.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(324,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;If 4 examiners can examine a certain number of answer books in 8 days by working 5 hours a day, for how many hours a day would 2 examiners have to work in order to examine twice the number of answer books in 20 days?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Work done by 1 examiner in 1 hour is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;108&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Work is doubled. Number of hours required now will be (work)/(work done in 1 hour).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of hours required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.15.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;127&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 8 hours.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(325,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A, B, C enter into a partnership. A contributes one-third of the whole capital while B contributes as much as A and C together contribute. If the profit at the end of the year is Rs. 84,000, how much would C receive?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 14,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 28,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 42,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 7,000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;B contributes exactly half of the capital. A contributes 1/3rd of the capital.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the contribution of C is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;95&quot; height=&quot;35&quot; /&gt;of the capital.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the share of C is 84000/6 = Rs.14000&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(326,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Vijay has coins of the denomination of Re. 1, 50 p and 25 p in the ratio of 12: 10: 7. The total worth of the coins he has is Rs. 600. Find the number of 25 p coins that Vijay has&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;224&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;448&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;112&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;12 (1 rupee) coins, 10 (50p) coins and 7 (25p) coins give a total of Rs. 18.75.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of such sets present is 600/18.75 = 32.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of 25p coins is 32 &amp;times; 7 = 224.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(327,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A varies jointly as B and C and A = 8 when B = 3, C = 2: find A when B = 5, C = 8.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since A varies jointly as B and C, then A = kBC where k is a constant.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, k = BC/A = 2 &amp;times; (3/8) = 3/4 =&amp;gt; B = 5; C = 8 =&amp;gt; A = (3/4) &amp;times; 5 &amp;times; 8 = 30.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(328,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A cask contains 12 gallons of mixture of wine and water in the ratio 3:1. How much of the mixture must be drawn off and water substituted, so that wine and water in the cask may become half and half?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If we replace x litres of the mixture, then the amount of wine that remains is (12 - x) &amp;times; (3/4) litres and the amount of water remaining is (12 - x) &amp;times; (1/4) + x because the mixture is replaced by pure water.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, ratio of wine to water is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.19.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;115&quot; height=&quot;63&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 36 - 3x = 12 + 3x&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 24/6 = 4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 4 litres of the mixture should be replaced.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(329,4,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Concentrations of three wines A, B and C are 10%, 20% and 30% respectively. They are mixed in the ratio 2: 3: x resulting in a 23% concentration solution. Find x.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Final percentage of concentration is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/143.20.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;211&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 23&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 80 + 30x = 23x + 115.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 7x = 35&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 5.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(330,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Two varieties of oil are mixed in the ratio 4:3 to produce first quality and if they are mixed in the ratio 2:3, second quality is obtained. How many kg. of the first quality be mixed with 20 kg of the second quality so that a third quality having the two varieties in the ratio 5 : 4 may be produced?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;98&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;196&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;294&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;392&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let x kgs of the first type be mixed with 20 kg of the second type.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total amount of first variety of oil is (4x/7) + [(2/5) &amp;times; 20] = (4x/7) + 8 and the total amount of first variety of oil is (3x/7) + [(3/5) &amp;times; 20] = (3x/7) + 12.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio of the two varieties is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;90&quot; height=&quot;72&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 16x + 224 = 15x + 420&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 196 kgs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(331,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Ten years ago, the ages of the members of a joint family of eight people added up to 231 years. Three years later, one member died at the age of 60 years and a child was born during the same year. After another three years, one more member died, again at 60, and a child was born during the same year. The current average age of this eight-member joint family is nearest to&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;39&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If there are no changes, then the average age at present is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;110&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Seven years back, there is a replacement which decreased total age by 60 years. Four years back, there is a similar replacement again of reaction of 60 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total age change is 60 + 60 = 120.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, actual average is (311/8) - (120/8) = 191/8 ~24 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(332,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A certain amount of money is divided among nine students. The second student gets Rs. 2 more than twice the amount given to the first student. The third student gets Rs. 3 more than thrice the amount given to the first student, and so on till the ninth student. If the ratio of the amount with the ninth student to the amount with the first student is 10: 1, how much did the fifth student get (in rupees)?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;47&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the amount given to first student is x. So, the amount of money given to nth student is nx + n.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Given (T&lt;sub&gt;9&lt;/sub&gt;/T) - 1 = 10:1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; (9x + 9)/x = 10/1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; x = 9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount of money the fifth student got is 5x + 5 = Rs. 50.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(333,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;At the time of the birth of twins, the average age of a couple was 24 years. When the twins attained the mother&amp;rsquo;s age, the average age of this family of four was 35 years. What was the father&amp;rsquo;s age when the twins attained the mother&amp;rsquo;s age?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;42&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the age of mother at the time of birth of twins be M. so, the age of father then will be 48 - M.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;When the twins attained mothers age, the ages of the twins is M, the mothers age is M + M = 2M and that of the father is 48 - M + M = 48.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(334,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Two-fifths of the voters promise to vote for P and the rest promise to vote for Q. Of these, on the last day, 15% of the voters went back on their promise to vote for P and 25% of voters went back of their promise to vote for Q, and P lost by 2 votes. Then the total number of voters is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;300&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;250&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the total number of persons that voted be x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of persons voting for P is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;305&quot; height=&quot;35&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So 51x/100 voted for Q. The difference is 2x/100 = 2 =&amp;gt; x = 100.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(335,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Stefani and Paul have got a certain number of red and black marbles with them. The ratio of number of red marbles and black marbles with Stefani and Paul is 7: 1 and 1: 9 respectively. If in all they have 90 marbles, then how many black marbles could Paul have?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 or 45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18 or 54&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18 or 36&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 or 36&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let there be 8x red marbles and 10y black marbles. So, 8x + 10y = 90.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now, since the sum should be a multiple of 10 and 10y is already a multiple of 10, the value of 8x should also be a multiple of 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the value of x can be either 5 or 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If x = 10 =&amp;gt; y = 1. If x = 5 =&amp;gt; y = 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total number of black marbles that Paul can have is 9y which can be either 9 &amp;times; 1 = 9 or 9 &amp;times; 5 = 45 only.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(336,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A boy spends Rs. 81 in buying some pens and pencils. If a pen costs Rs.7 and a pencil Rs 3, what is the ratio of pens to pencils when the maximum number of pens are purchased such that no extra money is given to the shopkeeper?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:4&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let us assume that he bought x pens and y pencils. So, 7x + 3y = 81.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since 3y and 81 are multiples of 3, in order that the value os x be integral, it should also be a multiple of 3. So, possible values of x are x = 3 or 6 or 9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Maximum value possible for x is 9 and when x = 9; y = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;64&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 6.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So the required ratio is 3 : 2.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(337,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;The duration of a railway journey varies as the distance and inversely as the velocity: the velocity varies directly as the square root of the quantity of coal used, and inversely as the number carriages in the train. In a journey of 50 km in half an hour with 18 carriages, 100 kg of coal is required, how much coal will be consumed in a journey of 42 km in 28 minutes with 16 carriages&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;64&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;121&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Duration is given by t = k&lt;sub&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/sub&gt;x&amp;nbsp;(d/v) and v = (k&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; &amp;radic;q)/n where k&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, k&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; are constants, q is the quantity of coal and n is the number of compartments.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, t = kdn/&amp;radic;q where k=k&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;/k&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;208&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &amp;radic;q = kdn/t = (1/180) &amp;times; 42 &amp;times; (16/28) &amp;times; 60 = 8 =&amp;gt; q = 64.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 64 kg of coal is required.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(338,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A factory employs skilled workers, unskilled workers and clerks in the proportion 8:5: 1 and the wages of a skilled worker, an unskilled worker and a clerk are in the ratio 5:2:3. When 20 unskilled workers are employed, the total daily wages of all amount to Rs. 318000. The wages paid to each clerk is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4,500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 7,500&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of skilled, unskilled and clerks is 8 : 5 : 1. Let their numbers be 8k, 5k, k respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are 20 unskilled labour. So, 5k = 20 =&amp;gt; k = 5 =&amp;gt; 8k = 32.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let their ratios be 5x, 2x, 3x respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total wage bill is given to be Rs. 3,18,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, (32 &amp;times; 5x) + (20 &amp;times; 2x) + (4 &amp;times; 3x) = 318000 =&amp;gt; x = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;170&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1500.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the salary of each clerk is Rs.1500 &amp;times; 3 = Rs.4,500.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(339,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Brass is an alloy of copper and zinc, bronze is an alloy containing 80% of copper, 4 % of zinc and 16% of tin. A fused mass of brass and bronze is found to contain 74% of copper, 16% of zinc, and 10% of tin. The ratio of copper to zinc in Brass is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16:9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9:16&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2:3&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Brass does not contain tin. So, the entire tin in the alloy is because of bronze only.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the bronze and brass be mixed in the ratio x:y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total amount of tin is 16x + 0 = 10(x + y) =&amp;gt; x : y = 5 : 3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, for copper, (5 &amp;times; 80) + (3 &amp;times; z) = (8 &amp;times; 74) =&amp;gt; z = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;134&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 192/3 = 64%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, brass contains 64% copper and 36% zinc.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, required ratio is 64/36 = 16 : 9.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(340,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A contractor employs 200 men to build a bund. They finish 5/6 of the work in 10 weeks. Then rain sets in and not only does the work remain suspended for 4 weeks but also half of the work already done is washed away. After the rain, when the work is resumed, only 140 men turn up. The total time (in weeks) in which the contractor is able to complete the work assuming that there are no further disruptions in the schedule is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;1 man can build &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;110&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the work in 1 week.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Half of the 5/6th work has washed out. So, remaining work is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.11.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;79&quot; height=&quot;58&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;140 men work each week. So, work completed each week is 140/2400.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of weeks is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/144.11.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;98&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total time taken is 10 + 4 + 10 = 24 weeks.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(341,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A bag contains 25 paise, 50 paise and 1 Re coins. There are 440 coins in all and the total amount in the bag is Rs. 320. If there are thrice as many 1 Re. coins as there are 25 paise coins, then what is the number of 50 paise coins?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;160&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;240&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Let there be x 25p coins. So, there are 3x 1 rupee coins. Let there be y 50p coins.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 4x + y = 440 and (3x) + (x/4) + (y/2) = 320 =&amp;gt; 13x + 2y = 1280.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 5x = 1280 - 880 = 400 =&amp;gt; x = 80 =&amp;gt; y = 440 - 320 = 120.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, there are 120 50p coins.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(342,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;The cost of an article (which is composed of raw materials and wages) was 4 times the value of the raw materials used. The cost of raw materials increased in the ratio 4: 7 and wages increased in the ratio 4: 9. Find the present cost of the article if its original cost was Rs. 32.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 56&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 72&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 68&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 60&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;If the cost of the raw materials is x, then the cost of the article is 4x which implies that the cost of wages is 3x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, new cost is (x &amp;times; 7/4) + (3x &amp;times; 9/4) = 34x/4 = 17x/2 = (17/2) &amp;times; (32/4) = 68.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the new cost of the product is Rs.68.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(343,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Total expenses of running the hostel at Harvard Business School are partly fixed and partly varying linearly with the number of boarders. The average expense per boarder is $70 when there are 25 boarders and $60 when there are 50 boarders. What is the average expense per boarder when there are 100 boarders?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;55&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;There will be a fixed cost for all the students combined. Let it be a. There will be variable cost per student which will change with the number of students. Let the cost per student be b.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Initially when there are 25 boarders, total cost is a + 25b = (75 &amp;times; 25) = 1725.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;When there are 50 boarders, total cost is a + 50b = (60 &amp;times; 50) = 3000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 25b = 1225 =&amp;gt; b = 45 =&amp;gt; a = 500.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, when there are 100 boarders, total cost is a + 100b = 500 + (45 &amp;times; 100) = 5000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, average charge required is 5000/100 = 50.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(344,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A mother divided an amount of 61,000 between her two daughters aged 18 years and 16 years respectively and deposited their shares in a bond. If the interest rate is 20% compounded annually and if each received the same amount as the other when she attained the age of 20 years, share of the elder daughter is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 30,500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 25,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 36,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30,000&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Since both of them receive the amount with a gap of 2 years, the money should be arranged so that the principal of one daughter is equal to the total sum after 2 years of compound interest for the second daughter.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio of division is A : [A(1 + 20/100)&lt;sup&gt;2]&lt;/sup&gt; = A : [25A/36] = 36:25.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the share of the elder daughter is (36/61) &amp;times; 61000 = 36000.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(345,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A mixture of cement, sand and gravel in the ratio of 1: 2: 4 by volume is required. A person wishes to measure out quantities by weight. He finds that the weight of one cubic foot of cement is 94 kg, of sand 100 kg and of gravel is 110 kg. What should be the ratio of cement, sand and gravel by weight in order to give a proper mixture?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;47:100:220&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;47:50:50&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;47:50:220&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;94:50:55&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If 1 cubic foot of cement is used, then 2 cubic foots of sand and 4 cubic foots of gravel are to be used.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, weight of cement used is 1 &amp;times; 94 = 94 kg.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The weight of sand used is 2 &amp;times; 100 = 200 kg.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Weight of gravel used is 4 &amp;times; 110 = 440 kg.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 94 : 200 : 440 = 47 : 100 : 220.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(346,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;The speed of a railway engine is 42 Km per hour when no compartment is attached, and the reduction in speed is directly proportional to the square root of the number of compartments attached. If the speed of the train carried by this engine is 24 Km per hour when 9 compartments are attached, the maximum number of compartments that can be carried by the engine is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;49&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;51&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Reduction in speed is directly proportional to the square root of the number of compartments attached.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, if the reduction in speed with the addition of one number to the square root of number of compartments is x, then, when there are 9 compartments, reduction will be 3x = (42 - 24) = 18 =&amp;gt; x = 6 kmph. The maximum number of compartments will be when the speed almost becomes zero.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, square root of maximum number of compartments is 42/6 = 7. When there are 49 compartments, the train will finally stop.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, maximum number of compartments that can be carried by the engine is 48.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(347,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A milkman mixes 20 litres of water with 80 litres of milk. After selling one-fourth of this mixture, he adds water to replenish the quantity that he has sold. What is the current proportion of water to milk?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2:3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3:2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4:5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:4&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Initial ratio of milk and water is 4 : 1. So, after selling (1/4) &amp;times; 100 = 25 litres, the amount of milk and water is (4/5) &amp;times; 75 = 60 litres and 15 litres respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now, another 25 litres of water is added.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount of water now is 15 + 25 = 40 litres and the amount of milk is 60 litres.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio of water to milk is 40/60 = 2 : 3.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(348,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;The cost of a diamond varies directly as the square of its weight. Once, this diamond broke into four pieces with weights in the ratio 1: 2: 3: 4. When the pieces were sold, the merchant got Rs. 70,000 less. Find the original price of the diamond.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2.0 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.0 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2.1 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the weights of the pieces be 1, 2, 3, 4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the original weight of the diamond is 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 = 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the original weight of the diamond is proportional to (10)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 100. Let it be 100k.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the costs of the pieces are k, 4k, 9k, 16k.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 100k - 30k = 70000 =&amp;gt; 100k = 100000.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(349,4,'3','','&lt;p&gt;An artist has a canvas of length 10 inches and breadth 7 inches. He divides the canvas into 70 squares of area 1 inch by drawing lines parallel to the edges. He paints a corner square with green colour. He then paints the two adjacent squares that share the side with the existing green square with blue colour. He continues to paint the entire canvas in such a way that no green square is adjacent (i.e. share the same side) to another green and no blue square adjacent to another blue. What is the ratio of number of blue squares on the canvas to the number of green squares?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10:7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5:7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1:1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7:10&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Every alternate square is painted green and the other one will be painted blue.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 1 : 1.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(350,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If the ratio between two numbers is 5: 8 and their difference is 183, then the smaller number is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;305&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;275&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;385&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;325&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If the numbers are 5x and 8x, then the difference is 8x - 5x = 3x = 183.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the smaller number is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;138&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(351,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If the ratio between two numbers is 7: 5 and their difference is 316, then the sum of the two numbers is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1738&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1896&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;948&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1422&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the numbers are 7x and 5x, then the difference is 7x - 5x = 2x = 316 =&amp;gt; x = 158.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the sum of the two numbers is 7x + 5x = 12x = 12 x 158 = 1896.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(352,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Two numbers are in the ratio 6: 5. If 6 is subtracted from each of them, the ratio becomes 11: 9. The ratio of the two numbers if 12 is subtracted from each of the numbers is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11: 8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5: 4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10: 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4: 3&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the numbers be 6x and 5x. So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The new ratio required is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;194&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(353,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;The mean proportion between 12 and 27 is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;27&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;19.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The mean proportion between two numbers a and b is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;38&quot; height=&quot;31&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here a = 12, b = 27. So, mean proportional is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;156&quot; height=&quot;30&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(354,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Two numbers are in the ratio 4: 3. If 8 is subtracted from each of them, the ratio becomes 7: 5. The sum of the numbers is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;63&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;112&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;224&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;168&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the numbers be 4x and 3x. So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the numbers are 64 and 48. Their sum is 64 + 48 = 112.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(355,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A total amount of Rs. 2700 is to be divided among A,B and C in such a way that one fifth of A&#039;s part, one third of B&#039;s part and total C&#039;s part is equal. The A&#039;s part is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;900&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1200&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the divisions be x, y, z. So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.6.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;420&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;x + y + z = 2700. So, 9k = 2700 =&amp;gt; k = 300.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A&amp;rsquo;s part is 5k = Rs.1500.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(356,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;20 litres of a mixture contains 25% alcohol and the rest is water. If 5 litres of water is mixed in it, the percentage of alcohol in the new mixture will be&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Amount of alcohol initially is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;104&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;litres. The remaining 15 litres is water.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since alcohol is not being added, it will remain at 5 litres. But the amount of water will become 15 + 5 = 20 litres.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the new concentration of alcohol is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.7.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;162&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(357,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;In what proportion must water be mixed with spirit to gain 20 % by selling it at cost price?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1: 6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1: 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1: 4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1: 3&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;To gain 20%, let us assume x% of water is mixed, so, for every 1 liter of spirit, there is only (1 - x) litres of pure spirit. So, selling price is C but the original cost price is (1 - x)C.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, profit percentage is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;340&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Ratio of water to spirit is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.8.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;79&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(358,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A and B are two alloys of gold and copper prepared by mixing metals in the ratio 3:4 and 9:5 respectively. If equal quantities of alloys are melted to form a third alloy C. Find the ratio of gold and copper in C.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15: 13&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7: 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7: 6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11: 7&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Equal quantities of alloys of gold and copper are mixed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, if x kg of A are mixed, then the gold and copper are 3x/7 and 4x/7 kgs respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, if x kg of B are mixed, then the gold and copper are 9x/14 and 5x/14 kgs respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, final ratio is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.9.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;279&quot; height=&quot;49&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(359,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;The incomes of two people are in the ratio 11: 9 and expenditures in the ratio 1:1 respectively. The total savings between the two of them is Rs. 24000 and that is split in the ratio 2: 1. Find the sum of their incomes.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the incomes be 11x, 9x and the expenditures be y, y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The savings of the two persons are in the ratio 2:1.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;161&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Saving of the first person is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.10.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;356&quot; height=&quot;52&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total earning of two persons is 9x + 11x = 20x = Rs.80,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(360,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If x: y = 4: 3, then what is the value of (x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 2y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;):(x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4: 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;34: 25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;41: 25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data insufficient&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.11.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;408&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here the ratio is always fixed because the degree of both the numerator and the denominator is the same.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(361,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A cat takes 6 leaps for every 5 leaps of a dog, but 3 leaps of the dog are equal to 2 leaps of the cat. What is the ratio of the speed of the cat to that of the dog?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4: 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9: 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5: 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5: 4&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Ratio of the length of each leap for dog and cat are &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;78&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, ratio of speeds of cat and dog is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.12.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;148&quot; height=&quot;27&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(362,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Three men rent a farm for Rs. 20000 per annum. A puts 300 cows in the farm for 3 months. B puts 200 cows for 6 months and C puts 500 cows for 3 months. What percentage of the total expenditure should C pay?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33.33%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;41.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Ratio of their usage is (300 x 3): (200 x 6): (500 x 3) = 9: 12: 15 = 3: 4: 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, percentage of share paid by C is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;261&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(363,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If the ratio of the ages of Ravi and Raju is 9: 7 before six years and 6: 5 after three years from now, then find the present ratio of their ages.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5: 4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11: 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10: 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4: 3&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the present ages are x and y, then &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;213&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.14.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;211&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Solving these two equations, we get x = 33, y = 27.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 33/27 = 11: 9.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(364,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If the ratio of the ages of Robert and Roger is 4: 3 at present, and 20 years from now, the ratio will get changed to 9: 8, then find Roger&amp;rsquo;s present age in years.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the present ages be 4x and 3x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;417&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, present age of Roger is 3x = 12 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(365,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;At constant temperature, pressure of a definite mass of gas is inversely proportional to the volume. If the pressure is increased by 25%, find the respective change in volume.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33.33%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The product will remain constant. So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;321&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Percentage change in volume is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.16.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;267&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(366,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If the work done by (x + 1) men in (x + 2) days to the work done by (x &amp;ndash; 2) men in (x + 4) days is in the ratio 5: 4, then the value of x is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total ratio of work done in both cases is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;577&quot; height=&quot;49&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required value of x is 8.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(367,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A mixture contains milk and water in the ratio 3:1. On adding 6 litres of water, the ratio of milk to water becomes 3: 2. The quantity of milk in the mixture, in litres, is:&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;5 litres of water is added. The amount of milk will remain the same.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let there be x litres of mixture initially, so, the amount of milk is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.18.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;82&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the amount of water is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.18.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;19&quot; height=&quot;33&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Finally, the amount of milk is still &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.18.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;28&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;but the amount of water is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.18.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;44&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.18.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;352&quot; height=&quot;73&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;litres.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the initial amount of milk in the mixture is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.18.6.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;83&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;litres.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(368,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;If 10 oxen can plough 1/5th of a field in 12 days, how many days will 20 oxen take to do the remaining work?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;10 oxen plough 1/5th in 12 days. So, 1 oxen in one day will do &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.19.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;135&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are 20 oxen and the work to be completed is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.19.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;72&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, time taken is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.19.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;97&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;days.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(369,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of Rs. 848 is divided among A, B, C in such a way that A gets Rs. 32 less than B and B gets Rs. 64 less than C. Then the ratio of their shares is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15: 17: 21&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21: 17: 15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15: 21: 17&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17: 15: 21&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If C gets x, then B gets (x - 64) and A gets (x - 64 - 32) = (x - 96).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + x - 64 + x - 96 = 3x - 160 = 848 =&amp;gt; 3x = 1008 =&amp;gt; x = 336.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, ratio of their shares is 240: 272: 336 = 15: 17: 21.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(370,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;An amount is to be distributed among A, B and C in the ratio 1:2:3 respectively. If the difference in the shares of A and C is Rs. 3000, what will be the sum of shares of A and B?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the shares be x, 2x, 3x. So, 3x - x = 2x = 3000 =&amp;gt; x = 1500.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, share of A is x = Rs.1500 and that of B is 2x = Rs.3000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required sum is 1500 + 3000 = Rs.4500.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(371,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of the number of gents to ladies in a party was 3: 4. When 28 more gents joined the group, the ratio was reversed. The number of gents initially in the party was&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the initial number of gents and ladies be 3x and 4x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.22.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;366&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the number of gents initially in the party is 3x = 36.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(372,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Two numbers are such that their difference, their sum and their product are in the ratio of 1: 5: 24. The difference between the sum and the difference of the numbers is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the sum is 5 times the difference, the numbers will be in the ratio 2: 3. Let them be 2x and 3x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Now, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.23.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;340&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required difference is 5x - x = 4x = 16.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(373,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 350 contained in a box is made up of one rupee, 50 paise, and 25 paise coins in the proportion of 1:3:4. What is the total value of all the 50 paise coins?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;1 rupee coins, 3 50p coins and 4 25p coins give a total of Rs. 3.50.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, number of such sets present is (350/3.50) = 100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of 50p coins is 100 x 3 = 300.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required value is (300/2) = Rs.150&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(374,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of number of boys and girls in a school is 1:2. If 40% of the boys and 25% of the girls are scholarship holders, the percentage of students who do not get scholarship is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;70%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;66.67%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;If the number of boys are x and the total number of girls are 2x, then the total number of students who get a scholarship is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.25.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;235&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage of students who do not get a scholarship is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.25.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;173&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(375,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;The cost of a cup and saucer is Rs. 100. If the cost of the cup is doubled and the cost of the saucer is halved, then the overall cost is Rs. 130. Find the price of the cup finally?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the cup cost x and saucer cost y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.26.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;26&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the final cost of the cup is 2x = Rs.80.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(376,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A combo pack has a brush and a paste. If the cost of the brush drops by 25% and the cost of the paste increases by 50%, the pack would cost Rs. 135. If the cost of the brush increases by 25% and the cost of the paste decreases by 50%, the pack would cost Rs. 125. Find the original price of the combo pack.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;130&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;125&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;140&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;135&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the brush cost x and the paste cost y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 0.75x + 1.5y = 135 and 1.25x + 0.5y = 125.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Adding both the terms, 2(x + y) = 260 =&amp;gt; x + y = 130.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the cost of the combo pack is Rs. 130&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(377,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A, B, C enter into a partnership. A contributes one-fifth of the whole capital while B contributes half as much as A and C together contribute. If the profit at the end of the year is Rs. 90,000, how much would C receive?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;42000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If A contributes x and C contributes y, then B will contribute &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.28.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;46&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total amount is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.28.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;190&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;We know that &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.28.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;389&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio of the partnership is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.28.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;142&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount that is given to C is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.28.5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;166&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(378,4,'4','','&lt;p&gt;A varies jointly as B and C and inversely as D. If A = 9 when B = 3, C = 2, D = 2, then find A when B = 5, C = 8, D = 4.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since A varies jointly as B and C and inversely as D, then &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.29.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;64&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;where k is a constant.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.29.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;138&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If B = 5, C = 8, D = 4, then &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/ratio%20and%20proportion%20dpps-tpps/145.29.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;175&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(379,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Ravi lends Rs. 3600 on simple interest to Harsh for a period of 5 years. He lends a part of the amount at 4% interest and the rest at 6% and receives Rs. 960 as the amount of interest. How much money did he lend on 4% interest rate?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 2000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2400&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let us assume he lent x on 4% interest and (3600 - x) on 6% interest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, interest will be 5 &amp;times; &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;139&quot; height=&quot;56&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 960&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 2x = 21600 - 19200 = 2400 =&amp;gt; x = 1200 .&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, money given on 4% interest is Rs. 1200.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(380,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;At what rate percent per annum will a sum of Rs. 3,600 become Rs. 4,500 in 10 years at simple interest?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6.75%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the principal is P, then the simple interest at the end of x years at a rate of r% per annum is Pxr/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here P = 3600, I = 900, x = 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 3600 &amp;times; 10 &amp;times; (r/100) = 900 =&amp;gt; r = 2.5 %.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(381,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The simple interest on a sum of money is 1/9th of the principal and the number of years is equal to the rate percent per annum. The rate of interest per annum is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10/3 %&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Let the principal be P. Simple interest at the end of x years at r% per annum is I = Pxr/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here, x = r and I = P/9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, px&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;/100 = P/9 =&amp;gt; x = 10/3.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(382,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A sum doubles in 20 years at simple interest. How much is the rate per annum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20/3 %&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the principal be P. Simple interest at the end of x years at r% per annum is I = Pxr/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here x = 20 years and I = P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 20Pr/100 = P =&amp;gt; r = 5%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(383,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Ram borrowed Rs. 5,000 from Sanjay with simple interest. After 2 years, Sanjay got Rs. 1,000 more than what he had given to Ram. What was the percentage of interest per annum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the principal be P = 5000. Simple interest at the end of x years at r% per annum is I = Pxr/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here x = 2 years and I = 1000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 2 &amp;times; 5000 &amp;times; (r/100) = 1000 =&amp;gt; r = 10%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(384,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;What sum of money lent out at compound interest will amount to Rs. 968 in 2 years at 10% per annum, interest being charged annually?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 900&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 825&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 780&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 800&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Let the sum be A. So, after 2 years, the amount will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.6.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;89&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= A &amp;times; (121/100) = 968&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; A = 968/1.21 = 800.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(385,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2000 is lent at compound interest of 5% per annum for 2 years. Find the amount after two years.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2205&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2250&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2225&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the principal is A, then the total amount with compound interest for 2 years will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;92&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here, A = 2000, r = 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So amount is 2000 &amp;times; (21/20) &amp;times; (21/20) = Rs. 2205.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(386,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The difference in simple interest on a certain sum of money for 3 years and 5 years at 18% per annum is Rs. 2,160. Then the sum is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 7500&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;If the two time periods are x&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; and x&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;, then the difference in simple interest at rate of r % is Pr(x&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;-x&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;)/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, given that P &amp;times; 18 &amp;times; (2/100) = 2160 =&amp;gt; P = Rs.6000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(387,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of Rs. 1600 lent at simple interest at 12.5% per annum will become double in&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 years&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 1/2 years&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 Years&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 1/4 years&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;If the principal is P, then the simple interest at the end of x years at a rate of r% per annum is Pxr/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here r = 12.5 % and I = P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, P &amp;times; (12.5) &amp;times; (x/100) = P =&amp;gt; x = 100/12.5 = 8.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(388,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the simple interest on a principal of Rs. 1500 being calculated at 5% per annum for 3 years and 4% per annum for 4 years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. .60&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If the two rate of interest are r&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;% and r&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;% and the length of periods is n&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; and n&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;, then the difference in simple interest over one year is P&amp;nbsp;&amp;times;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;85&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the difference is 1500 &amp;times; &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.10.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;118&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= Rs.15&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(389,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between compound interest and simple interest for the sum of Rs. 20,000 over a 2 year period if the compound interest is calculated at 20% and simple interest is calculated at 23%?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 800&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Simple interest at 23% for two years will be 20000 &amp;times; 2 &amp;times; (23/100) = Rs.9200&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Compound interest at 20% for two years will be 20000&amp;nbsp;&amp;times;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;81&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt; - 20000 = 20000 &amp;times; (11/25) = Rs.8800.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required difference is Rs. 400.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(390,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Vinay deposited Rs. 8000 in ICICI Bank, which pays him 12% interest per annum compounded quarterly. What is the amount that he receives after 9 months?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 8742&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 8900&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 8500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 9124&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the time is quarter an year, the effective rate is 12/4 = 3%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are three such periods.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Amount after 9 months is P(1 + r/100)&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; = 8000 &amp;times; [103/100]&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; = 8000 &amp;times; 1.093 = Rs.8742.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(391,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of money invested at simple interest triples itself in 8 years. How many times will it become in 20 years&amp;rsquo; time?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The time it takes for the interest to be equal to the amount is 8/2 = 4 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, in 20 years&amp;rsquo; time, the interest will be 20/4 = 5 times the principal.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, in 20 years&amp;rsquo; time, the sum will become six times.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(392,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;If Rs. 1000 is obtained after lending out Rs.x at 5% per annum for 2 years and Rs. 1600 is obtained after lending out Rs.y at 10% per annum for 2 years, find x+y.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 16,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 18,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 20,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 24,000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Interest in the first case is 5 &amp;times; (2x/100) = 1000 =&amp;gt; x = 10,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest in the second case is 10 &amp;times; (2y/100) = 1600 =&amp;gt; y = 8,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x + y = 18,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(393,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of Rs. 3000 amounts to Rs. 3600 in 4 years at simple interest. What will it amount to if the rate of interest is increased by 2%?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3700&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3840&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4000&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;If the two rate of interest are r&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;% and r&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;%, then the difference in simple interest over n years is Pn &amp;times;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;50&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the difference in the two cases is 3000 &amp;times; 4 &amp;times; (2/100) = Rs.240.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount in second case is Rs.3600 + 240 = Rs.3840.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(394,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of money becomes 7/4 of itself in 6 years at a certain rate of simple interest. Find the rate of interest.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The interest applied is (7P/4) - P = (3P/4).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 6P &amp;times; (R/100) = 3P/4&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; R = 100/8% = 12.5%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(395,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;In how many years will the simple interest on Rs. 1750 at 9% per annum be the same as that on Rs. 2500 at 10.5% per annum in 3 years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;13.33&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the time required in the first case be n.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So 1750 &amp;times; (9/100) &amp;times; n = 2500 &amp;times; (21/200) &amp;times; 3 =&amp;gt; n = 10 &amp;times; (63/63) = 10 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(396,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The difference in simple interest at 13% and 12% p.a. of a sum in one year is Rs. 110. Then the sum is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 13,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 15,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 10,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 11,000&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;If the two rate of interest are r&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;% and r&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;%, then the difference in simple interest over one year is P &amp;times;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.18.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;47&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, given that P &amp;times; &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.18.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;47&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt; = 110 =&amp;gt; P = 110 &amp;times; 100/(13 - 12) = Rs.11000&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(397,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;At what rate percent per annum compound interest will a sum of money double itself in 4 years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The amount in compound interest will double itself in approximately 72/r years where r% is the rate of interest for annum.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(398,5,'1','','&lt;p&gt;By how much will the compound interest on a sum of Rs. 20000 be more than the simple interest after 2 years if the rate of interest is the same at 10% in both the cases?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 100&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 500&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The compound interest after 2 years is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/152.20.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;98&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;- P = P &amp;times;&amp;nbsp;(1.21 - 1) = 0.21 &amp;times; P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The simple interest after 2 years is P &amp;times; 2 &amp;times; (10/100) = 0.2 &amp;times; P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the difference in the two cases is 0.01P = Rs.200.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(399,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;If the amounts for a fixed principal after 3 and 2 years at a certain rate of compound interest are in the ratio 21 : 20. The rate of interest is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;If the principal is P and the rate of interest is r%, then the amount after n years will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;98&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, after two years, the amount is A&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;89&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After three years, the amount is A&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.1.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;92&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.1.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;108&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 21/20 =&amp;gt; r = 5%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(400,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A man borrows Rs. 4,000 from a bank at 7 1/2 % interest. At the end of every year, he pays Rs. 1,500 as part repayment of loan and interest. How much does he still owe to the Bank after 3 such annual payments?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 123.25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 124.25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 125&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Initial principal is P = 4000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest after the first year is 4000 &amp;times; (7.5/100) = Rs.300.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total principal after first year is 4000 - 1500 + 300 = Rs.2800.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest after the second year is 2800 &amp;times; (7.5/100) = Rs.210.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total principal after second year is 2800 - 1500 + 210 = Rs.1510.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest after the third year is 1510 &amp;times; (7.5/100) = Rs.113.25.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total principal after third year is 1510 - 1500 + 113.25 = Rs.123.25.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(401,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;The simple interest on a certain sum of money for 4 years at 4 percent per annum exceeds the compound interest on the same sum for 3 years at 5 percent per annum by Rs. 57. Find the sum.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 24,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 12,500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 26,700&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 23,050&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the principal be P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Simple interest at the end of 4 years at 4% per annum is I&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = P &amp;times; 4 &amp;times; (4/100) = 16P/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Compound interest at the end of 3 years at 5% per annum is I&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;89&quot; height=&quot;42&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;- P = 0.157625P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Given that I&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; - I&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = 57&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 0.002375P = 57 =&amp;gt; P = 57/0.002375 = 24,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(402,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of money doubles itself at compound interest in 15 years. It will become 8 times in&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40 years&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30 Years&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60 years&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45 years&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;In compound interest, if it doubles in 15 years, then it will be four times the original value in another 15 years. So, after another 15 years, that is 45 years, the sum will become eight times.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(403,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;The cost of a machine is estimated to be decreasing at the rate of 15% every year. If it costs Rs. 6,000 now, what will be the estimated value of the machine after 2 years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 3,750&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4,335&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3,225&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 5,000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The decrease in cost of the machine is equivalent to compound interest because the decrease is proportional to the present amount instead of initial amount.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, after 2 years, the amount of water left will be 6000.&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;171&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt; = Rs.4335&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(404,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;The difference between compound interest and simple interest on certain sum of money in 2 years at 4% per annum is Rs. 50. Find the sum&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30,550&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 31,250&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 25,670&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 35,400&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the principal be P. Simple interest at the end of 2 years at 4% per annum is I&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = P &amp;times; 2 &amp;times; (4/100) = 8P/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Compound interest at the end of 2 years at 4% per annum is I&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.6.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;90&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 0.0816P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Given that I&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; - I&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = 50 =&amp;gt; 0.0016P = 50 =&amp;gt; P = 50/0.0016 = Rs.31250.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(405,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Find out the capital required to earn a monthly interest of Rs. 600 at 6% simple interest.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.2 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.1 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.3 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Rate of interest per month is 6/12 = 0.5 %.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest is Rs. 600.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, P &amp;times; (0.5/100) = 600 =&amp;gt; P = Rs.120000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(406,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;What is the simple interest on a sum of Rs. 1500 if the rate of interest for the first 3 years is 8% per annum and for the last 2 years is 7.5% per annum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 585&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 630&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 645&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total interest is the sum of the two interests because this is simple interest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total interest is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;372&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 15 &amp;times; 39 = Rs.585.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(407,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Find the compound interest on Rs. 2000 at the rate of 20% per annum for 18 months when interest is compounded half yearly.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 662&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 420&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 540&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the money is compounded half yearly, the effective rate is 20/2 = 10%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are 3 such periods in 18 months.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, compound interest is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;247&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 2000 &amp;times; 0.331 = Rs. 662.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(408,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;The SBI lent Rs. 133100 to the Tata group at a compound interest and got Rs. 172800 after three years. What is the rate of interest charged if the interest is compounded annually?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11.11%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9.09%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the rate of interest be r%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The total period is 3 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio of final amount to the principal is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;251&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 1 + (r/100) = (12/11) =&amp;gt; r = 100/11 = 9.09%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(409,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;In what time will Rs. 3300 become Rs. 3399 at 6% per annum interest compounded half-yearly?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 months&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 year&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18 months&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 months&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the money is compounded half yearly, the effective rate is 6/2% = 3%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let there be n such periods.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio of final amount to the principal is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;253&quot; height=&quot;58&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1.03 =&amp;gt; n = 1.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the time required is 6 months.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(410,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;What is the rate of simple interest for the first 4 years if the sum of Rs. 3600 becomes Rs. 5400 in 9 years and the rate of interest for the last 5 years is 6%?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the rate of interest be r%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total interest is the sum of the two interests because this is simple interest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total interest is [3600 &amp;times; (r/100) &amp;times; 4] + [3600 &amp;times; (6/100) &amp;times; 5] = 1800 =&amp;gt; 36 &amp;times; (30 + 4r) = 1800 =&amp;gt; r = 5%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(411,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Ajay borrows Rs. 15000 from two money lenders. He pays interest at the rate of 12% per annum for one loan and at the rate of 14% per annum for the other. The total interest he pays for the entire year is Rs. 1860. How much does he borrow at the rate of 12%?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 12,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 10,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 75,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3,000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let us assume he borrowed x on 12% interest and (15000 - x) on 14% interest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, interest will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;158&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1860 =&amp;gt; 2x = 210000 - 186000 = 24000 =&amp;gt; x = 12000 .&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, money borrowed on 12% interest is Rs. 12000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(412,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of money invested at simple interest triples itself in 8 years at simple interest. Find in how many more years will it become 8 times itself at the same rate?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the money is tripled, the interest will be double that of principal. So, the interest will become equal to the principal in 8/2 = 4 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;It will become 8 times if the interest becomes 7 times the principal. So, the time required is 4 &amp;times; 7 = 28 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 20 more years are required.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(413,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Divide Rs. 6000 into two parts so that simple interest on the first part for 2 years at 6% p.a. may be equal to the simple interest on the second part for 3 years at 8% p.a. the value of the first part is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4500&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the two parts be x and (6000 - x) respectively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The interest in both the cases is equal.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 2x &amp;times; (6/100) = [3(6000 - x)] &amp;times; 8/100 =&amp;gt; 36x = 24 &amp;times; 6000 =&amp;gt; x = 4000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the first part is Rs. 4000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(414,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;If the compound interest on a certain sum for 2 years is Rs.2100. What could be the simple interest at the same rate?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 2250&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2150&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2125&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Over a period of more than one computing periods, if the rate of interest is the same, then always, CI &amp;gt; SI.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(415,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Sanjay borrowed Rs. 2700 at 4% p.a. and Rs. 3300 at 5% p.a. for the same duration. He had to pay Rs. 1092 in all as interest. What is the time period in years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the time period be n years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total interest will be [n &amp;times; 2700 &amp;times; (4/100)] + [n &amp;times; 3300 &amp;times; (5/100)] = 1092 =&amp;gt; n = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;71&quot; height=&quot;45&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1092/273 = 4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required time period is 4 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(416,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Ravi derives an annual income of Rs. 688.25 from Rs.10000, invested partly at 8% p.a. and partly at 5% p.a. simple interest. How much of his money is invested at 5%?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6,275&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3,775&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6,225&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3,725&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let us assume he lent x on 8% interest and (10000 - x) on 5% interest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, interest will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.18.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;146&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 688.25 =&amp;gt; 3x = 18825 =&amp;gt; x = Rs.6275 .&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, money given on 5% interest is Rs.10,000 - Rs.6275 = Rs.3775.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(417,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;The difference between CI and SI on a certain sum of money at 10% per annum for 3 years is Rs. 620. Find the principal if it is known that the interest is compounded annually.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 10,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 20,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 25,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30,000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;CI for 3 years at 10% anum is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.19.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;129&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= P[1.331-1] = 0.331P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;SI for 3 years at 10% annum is P &amp;times; 3 &amp;times; (10/100) = 0.3P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the difference between the two is 0.331P - 0.3P = 0.031P = 620 =&amp;gt; P = Rs.20,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the principal is Rs.20,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(418,5,'2','','&lt;p&gt;Some amount was lent at 6% per annum simple interest. After one year, Rs. 6800 is repaid and the rest of the amount is repaid at 5% per annum. If the second year&amp;rsquo;s interest is 11/20 of the first year&amp;rsquo;s interest, find what amount of money was lent out.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 10,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 12,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 15,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 20,000&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Let the amount lent be x. Then the principal for second year is (x - 6800).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest for the second year is 11/20 of the interest for the first year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/153.20.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;87&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 11/20 =&amp;gt; 100x - 680,000 = 66x =&amp;gt; x = 680,000/34 = Rs.20,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(419,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of money lent at compound interest amounts to Rs. 1210 in two years and to Rs. 1464.10 in 4 years. Find the rate of interest.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the principal is P and the rate of interest is r%, then the amount after n years will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;84&quot; height=&quot;35&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, after two years, the amount is A&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;93&quot; height=&quot;43&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After four years, the amount is A&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.1.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;92&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.1.4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;117&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1464.1/1210 =&amp;gt; = 121/110 = 11/10 =&amp;gt; r = 10%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(420,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A man invested 1/3rd of the sum at 7%, 1/4th at 8% and the remaining at 10% for one year. If the annual interest is Rs. 408, then the investment is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs.8,400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4,800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 5,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 7,200&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the principal is P, then the annual interest will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;240&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 8.5 &amp;times;&amp;nbsp;(P/100).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 8.5P/100 = 408 =&amp;gt; P = 408 &amp;times; 100/8.5 = Rs.4800.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(421,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Surya makes a deposit of Rs. 50,000 in the Punjab National Bank for a period of 27 months. If the rate of interest is 12% per annum compounded once in nine months, find the maturity value of the money deposited by him.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 64,703&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 64,751&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 64,831&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 64,801&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The period for compounding is &amp;frac34; year. So, the effective rate of interest is (12 &amp;times; 3)/4 = 9% per term.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In the period of 2 1/4 years, there are 3 terms.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the maturity value is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;201&quot; height=&quot;37&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= Rs.64751.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(422,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;What will be the simple interest on Rs. 1000 at 9% per annum for the period from February 5, 1994 to April 18, 1994?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 16&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The total time period is 24 + 31 + 18 = 73 days since 1994 is a non-leap year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Rate of interest is 9% per annum.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the simple interest will be 1000 &amp;times; (73/365) &amp;times; (9/100) = Rs.18.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(423,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A tank contains 18,000 litres of water. If it decreases at the rate of 5% a day, what will be the quantity of water after 2 days?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16,245 litres&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15,234 litres&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17,225 litres&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18,200 litres&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The decrease in water is equivalent to compound interest because the amount of water is proportional to the amount of water left in the tank.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, after 2 days, the amount of water left will be 18000.&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;76&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; /&gt;= 18000 &amp;times; (361/400) = 16245 liters.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(424,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Three persons Amar, Akbar and Anthony invested different amounts in a fixed deposit scheme for one year at the rate of 11% per annum and earned a total interest of Rs. 4510 at the end of the year. If the amount invested by Anthony is Rs. 3000 more than the amount invested by Amar and the amount invested by Amar is Rs. 4000 more than the amount invested by Akbar. What is the amount invested by Amar?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 10,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 14,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 17,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 15,000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since rate of interest is same for everyone, the total investment is P &amp;times; (11/100) = 4510 = &amp;gt;P = 41000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the money invested by Akbar be x. Then the money invested by Amar is (x + 4000) and that invested by Antony will be (x + 7000).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 3x + 11000 = 41000 =&amp;gt; x = 10000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, amount invested by Amar is 10,000 + 4,000 = Rs. 14,000&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(425,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;Divide Rs. 3903 between Amar and Akbar such that Amar&amp;rsquo;s share at the end of 7 years is equal to Akbar&amp;rsquo;s share at the end of 9 years at 4% p.a. rate of compound interest. Find the share of Amar&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2,028&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,875&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,952&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2,000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the values be x and y. The values should be such that the value of x is the value of the total amount if y is given for compound interest for 2 years. So, x = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;94&quot; height=&quot;38&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, x : y = &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.7.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;208&quot; height=&quot;37&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the amount of money that Amar gets is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.7.3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;85&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 3903 = 3 &amp;times; 676 = Rs. 2,028.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(426,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of money placed at compound interest doubles itself in 3 years. In how many years will it amount to 8 times itself?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;It will take another 3 years to become 4 times the value and another 3 years to become 8 times the value.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total time taken is 9 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(427,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;What annual payment will discharge a debt of Rs. 808 due in 2 years at 2% per annum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 395&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 405&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 404&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 808 is due after two years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the value of each instalment be Rs.x. The first instalment earns compound interest for 1 year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 808 = x&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;44&quot; height=&quot;31&quot; /&gt; + x =&amp;gt; 808 = x &amp;times; (101/50) =&amp;gt; x = 8 &amp;times; 50 = Rs.400.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(428,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of money is borrowed and paid back in two equal annual instalments of 882, allowing 5% compound interest. The sum borrowed was&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,640&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,750&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,560&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,670&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the value taken for loan be Rs.x. It will earn compound interest for 2 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The first instalment earns compound interest for 1 year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;247&quot; height=&quot;51&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;=&amp;gt; 441x/400 = 882 &amp;times; (41/20) =&amp;gt; x = 41 &amp;times; 40 = Rs. 1,640.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(429,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;The population of a city is 200,000. If the annual birth rate and the annual death rate are 6% and 3% respectively, then calculate the population of the city after 2 years.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;212180&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;224720&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;217680&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;219340&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The actual growth rate will be 6% - 3% = 3%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, population of the city after 2 years will be 200000&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;76&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt; = 20 &amp;times; 10609 = 212,180.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(430,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A part of Rs. 38,800 is lent out at 6% per six months. The rest of the amount is lent out at 5% per annum after one year. The ratio of interest after 3 years from the time when first amount was lent out is 5: 4. Find the second part that was lent out at 5%.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 25,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 28,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 28,800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30,000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the part of money lent out initially be x and so, the money lent after one year is 38,800-x. The rate for the first case is 6% half yearly or 12% annually.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The first part earn interest for 3 years and the second part earns interest for 2 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, according to question, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;121&quot; height=&quot;48&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 5/4 =&amp;gt; 72x = 970000 - 25x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 97x = 970000 =&amp;gt; x = 10,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The second part lent at 5% is 38800 - 10000 = 28,800.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(431,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of Rs. 1000 after 3 years at compound interest becomes a certain amount that is equal to the amount that is the result of a 3 year depreciation from Rs. 1728. Find the difference between the rates of CI and depreciation. (Given CI is 10% p.a.). (Approximately)&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.83%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If the rate of CI is r&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;% = 10% and the rate of depreciation is r&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;%, then we can say that &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;369&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.13.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;101&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;=&amp;gt; 12r&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = 1200 - 1100 = 100 =&amp;gt; r&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = 100/12% = 8.33%&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(432,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;The RBI lends a certain amount to the SBI on simple interest for two years at 20%. The SBI gives this entire amount to Bharti Telecom on compound interest for two years at the same rate annually. Find the percentage earning of the SBI at the end of two years on the entire amount.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3.86%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4.04%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4.12%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the rate is same in both cases, the principal P becomes &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;106&quot; height=&quot;33&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1.4P in the first case and &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.14.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;74&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 1.44P in the second case.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage earning is 0.04P/P &amp;times; 100 = 4%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(433,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;If a principal P becomes Q in 2 years when interest R% is compounded half-yearly. And if the same principal P becomes Q in 2 years when interest S% is compound annually, then which of the following is true?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;R = S&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;R &amp;gt; S&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;R &amp;lt; S&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data insufficient&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;There are 4 time periods involved in the first case and only 2 time periods in the second case. The value of compound interest will increase with each instalment. So, we can say that in this case, R &amp;lt; S. Otherwise, the value in the first case will be greater than in the second case.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If it is a case of simple interest then R = S.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(434,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;David borrows a certain sum of money from the SBI Bank at 10% per annum at compound interest. The entire debt is discharged in full by David on payment of two equal amounts of Rs. 1000 each, one at the end of the first year and the other at the end of the second year. What is the approximate value of the amount borrowed by him?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 2,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,836&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1,736&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 1,636&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the value taken for loan be Rs. x. it will earn compound interest for 2 years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The first instalment earns compound interest for 1 year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;518&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;= Rs. 1,736&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(435,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A sum of Rs. 8000 is borrowed at 5% p.a. compound interest and paid back in 3 equal annual instalments. What is the amount of each instalment?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2,334&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2,875&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2,938&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3,500&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;let each instalment be Rs.x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The first instalment earns compound interest for 2 years and the second instalment earns interest for 1 year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;524&quot; height=&quot;41&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.17.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;410&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the value of each instalment is Rs. 2,938.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(436,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;An amount of Rs. 12820 due 3 years hence, is fully repaid in three annual instalments stating after 1 year. The first instalment is 1/2 the second instalment and the second instalment is 2/3 of the third instalment. If the rate of interest is 10% per annum, find the first instalment.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 300&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the third instalment be Rs.x. then the second instalment is Rs. 2x/3 and the first instalment is Rs. (2x/3)/2 = Rs. x/3.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The first instalment earns compound interest for 2 years and the second instalment earns interest for 1 year. Total money due is Rs. 12,820.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.18.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;578&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, 641x/600 = 12820 =&amp;gt; x = 600 &amp;times; 2 = 1200.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the first instalment is Rs.1200/3 = Rs.400.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(437,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A mother divided an amount of 61.000 between her two daughters aged 18 years and 16 years respectively and deposited their shares in a bond. If the interest rate is 20% compounded annually and if each received the same amount as the other when she attained the age of 20 years, their shares are&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 30,500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 25,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;RS. 36,000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 30,000&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since both of them receive the amount with a gap of 2 years, the money should be arranged so that the principal of one daughter is equal to the total sum after 2 years of compound interest for the second daughter.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio of division is &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/154.19.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;170&quot; height=&quot;44&quot; /&gt; = 36 : 25.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the share of the younger daughter is (25/61) &amp;times; 61,000 = 25,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(438,5,'3','','&lt;p&gt;A man borrows Rs. 4,000 at 8% per annum on compound interest. At the end of every year he pays Rs. 1,500 as part payment of loan and interest. How much does he still owe to the bank after 3 such annual payments?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 179&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 170&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 231&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Initial principal is P = 4000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest after the first year is 4000 &amp;times; (8/100) = Rs. 320.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total principal after first year is 4000 - 1500 + 320 = Rs. 2820.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest after the second year is 2820 &amp;times; (8/100) = Rs.225.6.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total principal after second year is 2820 - 1500 + 225 = Rs.1545.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Interest after the third year is 1545 &amp;times; (8/100) = Rs.125.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total principal after third year is 1545 - 1500 + 125 = Rs.170.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(439,5,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Ravi lends Rs. 10,000 on simple interest to Harsh for a period of 5 years. He lends a part of the amount at 6% interest and the rest at 8% and receives Rs. 3500 as the amount of interest. How much money did he lend on 6% interest rate?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let us assume he lent x on 6% interest and (10000 - x) on 8% interest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, interest will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/155.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;544&quot; height=&quot;47&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, money given on 6% interest is Rs. 5000.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(440,5,'4','','&lt;p&gt;Satish lends Rs. 3600 on simple interest to Harsh for a period of 5 years. He lends a part of the amount at 4% interest and the rest at 6% and receives Rs. 960 as the amount of interest. How much money did he lend on 4% interest rate?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2400&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let us assume he lent x on 4% interest and (3600 - x) on 6% interest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, interest will be &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/155.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;518&quot; height=&quot;52&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, money given on 4% interest is Rs. 1200.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(441,5,'4','','&lt;p&gt;At what rate percent per annum will a sum of Rs. 4280 become Rs. 5564 in 5 years at simple interest?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6.25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6.75%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;If the principle is P, then the simple interest at the end of t years at a rate of r% per annum is Ptr/100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here P = 4280, I = 5564 - 4280 = 1284, t = 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/Question%20Images/155.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;326&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(442,5,'4','','&lt;p&gt;The simple interest on a sum of money is 1/25th of the principle and the number of years is equal to the rate percent per annum. The rate of interest per annum is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2%