entage of unsold items of type D over all the years? (approx.)&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;22%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of items of type D manufactured is 134 + 270 + 466 + 632 = 1502. Number of items of type D sold is 88 + 212 + 382 + 612 = 1194. So, the number of items unsold is 1502 &amp;ndash; 1194 = 308. So, the percentage required is 308/1592 x 100% = 19.34% = 20%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(945,10,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following tables carefully to answer the questions that follow. The first table shows the number of each type of items that the company produces over the years. There are 4 varieties of items. The second table lists the number of items that the company was able to sell during the same period.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.1A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;184&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.2A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;183&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference in the percentage of unsold items of type B in 2014 and unsold items of type A goods in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.7%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.30%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of unsold items of type B in 2014 is 252 &amp;ndash; 206 = 46. So, percentage of unsold items of type B in 2014 is 46/252 x 100% = 18.25%. Number of unsold items of type A in 2013 is 153 &amp;ndash; 124 = 29. So, percentage of unsold items of type A in 2013 is 29/153 x 100% = 18.95%. So, the difference required is 18.95 &amp;ndash; 18.25 = 0.7%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(946,10,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following tables carefully to answer the questions that follow. The first table shows the number of each type of items that the company produces over the years. There are 4 varieties of items. The second table lists the number of items that the company was able to sell during the same period.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.1A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;184&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.2A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;183&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage of all the items sold in the year 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;90.25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;91.32%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;88.74%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;93.45%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of items produced in 2012 is 164 + 138 + 516 + 270 = 1088. Total number of items sold in 2012 is 150 + 112 + 508 + 212 = 982. So, the percentage required is 982/1088 x 100% = 90.25%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(947,10,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following tables carefully to answer the questions that follow. The first table shows the number of each type of items that the company produces over the years. There are 4 varieties of items. The second table lists the number of items that the company was able to sell during the same period.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.1A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;184&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.2A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;183&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The percentage of items sold is greatest for which type of item over all the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;A&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;B&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;C&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;D&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of items of type A manufactured is 186 + 164 + 153 + 192 = 695 and number of items sold is 162 + 150 + 124 + 156 = 592. So, the percentage required is 592/695 x 100% = 85.17%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of items of type B manufactured is 174 + 138 + 304 + 252 = 868 and number of items sold is 152 + 112 + 286 + 206 = 756. So, the percentage required is 756/868 x 100% = 87.09%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of items of type C manufactured is 324 + 516 + 432 + 318 = 1590 and number of items sold is 286 + 508 + 404 + 283 = 1481. So, the percentage required is 1481/1590 x 100% = 93.14%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of items of type D manufactured is 134 + 270 + 466 + 632 = 1502 and number of items sold is 88 + 212 + 382 + 612 = 1194. So, the percentage required is 1194/1502 x 100% = 79.49%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required type of item is C.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(948,10,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following tables carefully to answer the questions that follow. The first table shows the number of each type of items that the company produces over the years. There are 4 varieties of items. The second table lists the number of items that the company was able to sell during the same period.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.1A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;184&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%202%20-%20Ex%202/213.4.2A.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;271&quot; height=&quot;183&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the inverse ratio of the number of items sold by A in 2011 and manufactured by D in 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 : 7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 : 6&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The required ratio is 162: 270 = 9: 15 = 3: 5. So, the required inverse ratio is 5: 3.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(949,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following table shows the production and sale (in thousands) of tires of six different companies A, B, C, D, E and F during the period 2009 to 2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/214.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;631&quot; height=&quot;195&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which year is the number of tires sold for Company E the minimum percentage of its tires produced?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2013&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2009&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The maximum difference between the tires produced and tires sold is in the year 2011. Compared to this value, all the other values are very small. So, the answer is 2011.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(950,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following table shows the production and sale (in thousands) of tires of six different companies A, B, C, D, E and F during the period 2009 to 2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/214.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;631&quot; height=&quot;195&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the total tires produced in all six companies in 2012 and the total tires sold in 2013 (answer in thousands)?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;41&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;39&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;42&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total tires produced in 2012 is 88 + 48 + 64 + 43 + 59 + 60 = 362 thousand. Total tires sold in 2013 is 75 + 45 + 53 + 36 + 60 + 54 = 323 thousand. So, the required difference, in thousands, is 362 &amp;ndash; 323 = 39&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(951,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following table shows the production and sale (in thousands) of tires of six different companies A, B, C, D, E and F during the period 2009 to 2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/214.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;631&quot; height=&quot;195&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the approximate percentage increase/decrease in the number of tires sold by Company D from 2011 to 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;38.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;42.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35.5%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of tires sold by company D in 2011 is 26,000 Number of tires sold by company D in 2013 is 36,000 So, the required percentage is [36000 &amp;ndash; 26000]/26000 x 100% = 10/26 x 100% = 38.46%&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(952,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following table shows the production and sale (in thousands) of tires of six different companies A, B, C, D, E and F during the period 2009 to 2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/214.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;631&quot; height=&quot;195&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of the total tires sold by Company B and Company F together in the year 2010 to that in the year 2014?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 : 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 : 8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 : 6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 : 7&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of tires sold together by company B and F in 2010 is 46 + 50 = 96,000. Total number of tires sold together by company B and F in 2014 is 53 + 55 = 108,000. So, the required ratio is 96: 108 = 8: 9.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(953,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following table shows the production and sale (in thousands) of tires of six different companies A, B, C, D, E and F during the period 2009 to 2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%201%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/214.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;631&quot; height=&quot;195&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage of tires sold by company C during all the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;87.6%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;90.3%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;85.4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;85.7%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The total number of tires produced by company C is 56 + 49 + 52 + 64 + 62 + 65 = 348,000. The total number of tires sold by company C is 52 + 43 + 42 + 55 + 53 + 60 = 305,000. The required percentage is 305/348 x 100% = 87.64%&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(954,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table carefully and answer these questions. The first table gives the number of students appearing for UPSC exam in different centers across the country. The second table gives the percentage of students who are selected for the next round in the process.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/214.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;586&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/214.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;588&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is total number of candidates qualified from Pune, Chennai and Jaipur in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14514&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14544&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14524&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14634&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of candidates qualified from Pune in 2013 is 93500 x 9/100 = 8415.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of candidates qualified from Chennai in 2013 is 72000 x 7/100 = 5040.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of candidates qualified from Jaipur in 2013 is 35300 x 3/100 = 1059.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the number of required members is 8415 + 5040 + 1059 = 14514.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(955,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table carefully and answer these questions. The first table gives the number of students appearing for UPSC exam in different centers across the country. The second table gives the percentage of students who are selected for the next round in the process.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/table%20charts%20-%20ex3/214.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;586&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/table%20charts%20-%20ex3/214.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;588&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of average number of students appeared in 2009 and 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28575 : 49044&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28775 : 49084&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28675 : 49044&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28575 : 49084&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Since the number of centers remain the same for both the years, the ratio will be same for average number of students and total number of students.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of students appearing in 2009 is 45700 + 70100 + 38300 + 10100 + 76200 + 20050 + 25300 = 285750.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of students appearing in 2012 is 48400 + 89600 + 73540 + 84000 + 76500 + 93600 + 24800 = 490440.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The ratio required is 28575: 49044&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(956,10,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table carefully and answer these questions. The first table gives the number of students appearing for UPSC exam in different centers across the country. The second table gives the percentage of students who are selected for the next round in the process.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/table%20charts%20-%20ex3/214.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;586&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/table%20charts%20-%20ex3/214.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;588&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Approximately what is the average number of candidate qualified from Delhi from all the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3757&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3737&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3777&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3797&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of candidates qualified from Delhi in 2009 is 70100 x 9/100 = 6309.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of candidates qualified from Delhi in 2010 is 68400 x 6/100 = 4104.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of candidates qualified from Delhi in 2011 is 79400 x 5/100 = 3970.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of candidates qualifie