er the questions given below&amp;mdash; Number of Bales of Wool Processed by 5 Woollen Mills&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;591&quot; height=&quot;225&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The total of wool processing done by Kiwi during the given period is approximately what percent of that done by Shephered?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;87&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The required % = 4900/4100 &amp;times; 100 = 120% (Approx.)&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1013,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the table given below to answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;247&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How much tax is due on an income of Rs. 7500?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 80&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 125&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 150&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 225&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Tax due is 80 + 3% of 1500 = 80 + [1500 x 3]/100 = 80 + 45 = Rs. 125&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1014,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the table given below to answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;247&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If your income for a year is Rs. 26&amp;sbquo;000. You receive a raise so that next year your income will be Rs. 29&amp;sbquo;000. How much more will you pay in taxes next year if the tax remains the same?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 70&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 180&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 210&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;7% of 3000 = 7/100 &amp;times;3000 = Rs. 210&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1015,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the table given below to answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;247&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Vibhav paid Rs. 100 as tax. If X is his income, then which of the following statements in true ?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0 &amp;lt; X &amp;lt; 4000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4000 &amp;lt; X &amp;lt; 6000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6000 &amp;lt; X &amp;lt; 8000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8000 &amp;lt; X &amp;lt; 10&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Highest Tax for 0 - 4000 slab is Rs. 40. Highest Tax for slab&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1016,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the table given below to answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;247&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Town X has a population of 50&amp;sbquo;000. The average income of a person who lives in the town X is Rs. 3&amp;sbquo;700 per year. What is the total amount paid in taxes by the people of town X? (Assume that each person pays tax on Rs. 3&amp;sbquo;700)&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 37&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3&amp;sbquo;700&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1&amp;sbquo;85&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 18&amp;sbquo;50&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;50&amp;sbquo;000 &amp;times; (1% of 3700) = 50&amp;sbquo;000 &amp;times;37 = Rs. 18&amp;sbquo;50&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1017,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the table given below to answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;247&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;A person, whose income is Rs. 10&amp;sbquo;000, pays what per cent of his or her income on taxes approximately?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Income tax paid on Rs. 10&amp;sbquo;000 = Rs. 220, which is 220/10&amp;sbquo;000 &amp;times;100 = 2&amp;middot;2% of the income ~ 2%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1018,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table care-fully to answer the questions that follow. Distribution of Marks Obtained by 100 Students in Papers I, II and III Out of 50&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many students have secured less than 30 marks in paper II?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;65&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;27&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;38&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;38 + 17 + 10 = 65&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1019,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table care-fully to answer the questions that follow. Distribution of Marks Obtained by 100 Students in Papers I, II and III Out of 50&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many students will pass if they one required to obtain minimum 60% only as average marks of three papers?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Passing marks = 60% of 50 = 60/100 &amp;times;50 = 30 &amp;there4;Number of students who got more than 30 average marks of three papers = 20 + 14 = 34&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1020,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table care-fully to answer the questions that follow. Distribution of Marks Obtained by 100 Students in Papers I, II and III Out of 50&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many students will definitely pass if it is compulsory to obtain minimum 20% marks in each paper?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;92&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;94&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;90&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;90 because 10 students failed in paper-II.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1021,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table care-fully to answer the questions that follow. Distribution of Marks Obtained by 100 Students in Papers I, II and III Out of 50&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Minimum how many students will pass if they are required to obtain minimum 40% marks either in paper-I or in paper-III?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;72&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;73&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;77&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;79&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Minimum passing marks = 50/100 &amp;times;40 = 20. &amp;there4;For the paper I, Number of students = 12 + 18 + 42 = 72. For the paper-III, Number of students = 11 + 24 + 44 = 79. &amp;there4;Minimum number = 72.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1022,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following table care-fully to answer the questions that follow. Distribution of Marks Obtained by 100 Students in Papers I, II and III Out of 50&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many students will pass if it is compulsory to pass only in paper II with minimum 40% marks?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;38&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;73&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;100 - 17 - 10 = 73.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1023,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following table shows the percentage population of six states below poverty line and the proportion of male and female. Study the table carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;561&quot; height=&quot;226&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The total population of state A is 3000, then what is the approximate number of females above poverty line in the state?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1200&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2112&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Number of females above poverty line = 3000 &amp;times; (100 &amp;ndash; 12)% &amp;times; 3/7 = 3000 x 88/100 x 3/7 = 1131.42.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1024,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following table shows the percentage population of six states below poverty line and the proportion of male and female. Study the table carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;561&quot; height=&quot;226&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The total population of the state C and the State D together is 18000, what is the total number of females below poverty line in the above states ?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data Inadequate&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Since we cannot find the population of states C and D separately, therefore we cannot find the required value.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1025,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following table shows the percentage population of six states below poverty line and the proportion of male and female. Study the table carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;561&quot; height=&quot;226&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The population of males below poverty line in state A is 3000 and that in state E is 6000, then what is the ratio of the total population of state A and E ?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Population of the state A below poverty line = 3000 &amp;times; 5/3 = 5000. &amp;there4;Total population of the state A = 5000 x 100/12. The population of the state E below poverty line = 6000 &amp;times; 11/6 = 11,000. &amp;there4;Total population of state E = 11000/10 &amp;times;100. &amp;there4;Required Ratio = 5/11 x 10/12 = 50/132 = 25: 66.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1026,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following table shows the percentage population of six states below poverty line and the proportion of male and female. Study the table carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;561&quot; height=&quot;226&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the population of males below poverty line in state B is 500, what is the total population of that state?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7600&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total population of the state B = 500 &amp;times; 12/5 x 100/15 = 8000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1027,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following table shows the percentage population of six states below poverty line and the proportion of male and female. Study the table carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;561&quot; height=&quot;226&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If in state E population of females above poverty line is 19,800, what is the population of males below poverty line in that states?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2970&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data inadequate&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Population of state E = 19800 &amp;times; 5/2 x 100/[100-10] = 55000. &amp;there4;Population of males below poverty line is [10/100] x 55000 x 6/11 = 3000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1028,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: These questions are based on the table given below. Number of items produced (in lakhs) and percentage of items rejected of the units of 6 companies over the years 2008 to 2013&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;623&quot; height=&quot;200&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If all the items except rejected items were sold in the year 2009, what was the total number of items sold by Units B and D?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21418400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2141840&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;541184&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24118400&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Total number of items sold by B will be 99.3/100 x 64 lakhs = 6355200. Total number of items sold by D will be 97.6/100 x 182 lakh = 17763200. So, total number of items that are sold by B and D is 6355200 + 17763200 = 24118400.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1029,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: These questions are based on the table given below. Number of items produced (in lakhs) and percentage of items rejected of the units of 6 companies over the years 2008 to 2013&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;623&quot; height=&quot;200&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of rejected items by Unit A in the year 2008 is approximately what per cent of the rejected items of Unit D in the same year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;65&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;155&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;135&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of rejected items by Unit A in 2008 is 131 x 1.5/100 = 1.965 lakh. Number of rejected items by D in 2008 is 169 x 1.8/100 = 3.042 lakh. So, the required percentage is 1.965/3.042 x 100 = 65%&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1030,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: These questions are based on the table given below. Number of items produced (in lakhs) and percentage of items rejected of the units of 6 companies over the years 2008 to 2013&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;623&quot; height=&quot;200&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which year was the number of items rejected by Unit C the maximum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2012&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2013&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Number of items rejected for C in 2008 is 1.3/100 x 39 lakhs = 0.507 lakhs. Number of items rejected for C in 2009 is 0.8/100 x 48 lakhs = 0.384 lakhs. Number of items rejected for C in 2010 is 1.1/100 x 56 lakhs = 0.616 lakhs. Number of items rejected for C in 2011 is 1.4/100 x 52 lakhs = 0.728 lakhs. Number of items rejected for C in 2012 is 0.9/100 x 63 lakhs = 0.567 lakhs. Number of items rejected for C in 2013 is 71/100 x 1.25 lakhs = 0.8875 lakhs. So, maximum number of items are rejected for C in the year 2013.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1031,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: These questions are based on the table given below. Number of items produced (in lakhs) and percentage of items rejected of the units of 6 companies over the years 2008 to 2013&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;623&quot; height=&quot;200&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;For the given years, what was the total number of items rejected by Company A?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1169500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1165900&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;116950&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;116590&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Number of items rejected for A in 2008 is 1.5/100 x 124 lakhs = 1.965 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of items rejected for A in 2009 is 2.2/100 x 149 lakhs = 3.278 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of items rejected for A in 2010 is 1.2/100 x 107 lakhs = 1.284 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of items rejected for A in 2011 is 0.8/100 x 112 lakhs = 0.896 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of items rejected for A in 2012 is 1.8/100 x 142 lakhs = 2.556 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of items rejected for A in 2013 is 1.4/100 x 120 lakhs = 1.68 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of items are rejected for A is 1.965 + 3.278 + 1.284 + 0.896 + 2.556 + 1.68 = 11.659 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1032,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: These questions are based on the table given below. Number of items produced (in lakhs) and percentage of items rejected of the units of 6 companies over the years 2008 to 2013&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;623&quot; height=&quot;200&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the approximate percentage of items rejected by all the units in the year 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2.4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.5&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Total items produced in 2011 is 112 + 101 + 52 + 142 + 179 + 80 = 666 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total items that are rejected are (112 x 0.8/100) + (101 x 1.2/100) + (52 x 1.4/100) + (142 x 2.5/100) + (179 x 1.8/100) + (80 x 0.7/100) = 0.896 + 1.212 + 0.728 + 3.55 + 3.222 + 0.56 = 10.168 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 10.168/666 = 1.5% approximately&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1033,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Direction: The following table gives the percentage of population of Five States UP, MP, Rajasthan, Bihar and Punjab which are below poverty line and also the ratio of male to female among them. Study the table and answer the questions based on it.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;523&quot; height=&quot;158&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What will be the number of females below poverty line in state AP if the total population of state is 20 million?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 million&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;If the total population is 20 million, then the population below poverty line is 20 x 35/100 = 7 million. The ratio of male to female population below poverty line is 2: 5. So, the female population blow poverty line is 5/7 x 7 million = 5 million.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1034,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Direction: The following table gives the percentage of population of Five States UP, MP, Rajasthan, Bihar and Punjab which are below poverty line and also the ratio of male to female among them. Study the table and answer the questions based on it.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;523&quot; height=&quot;158&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the male population above poverty line in the state Orissa is 42 million, then find the total population of the state.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;88 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;77 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;66 million&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The male population above poverty line is 42 million. So, the total population above poverty line is 42 x 11/7 = 66 million which is 75% of the total population. So, total population of Orissa would be 66 x 100/75 = 88 million.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1035,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Direction: The following table gives the percentage of population of Five States UP, MP, Rajasthan, Bihar and Punjab which are below poverty line and also the ratio of male to female among them. Study the table and answer the questions based on it.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;523&quot; height=&quot;158&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the population of males below poverty line for state TN is 15 million and that for state AP is 17.5 million, then the ratio of total population of state TN to AP is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;15% of the population in TN is 15 million. So, total population of TN is 100 million. 35% of population of AP is17.5 million. So, total population of AP is 17.5 x 100/35 = 50 million. So, the ratio required is 100: 50 = 2: 1&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1036,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Direction: The following table gives the percentage of population of Five States UP, MP, Rajasthan, Bihar and Punjab which are below poverty line and also the ratio of male to female among them. Study the table and answer the questions based on it.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;523&quot; height=&quot;158&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the below poverty line population of Karnataka is 35 million, then find the number of males in Rajasthan, who are above poverty line&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;38.11 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;37.11 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36.11 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;39.11 million&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Below poverty line population in Karnataka is 30%, which means that the total population is 35 x 100/30 million and population above the poverty line will be 35 x 100/30 x 70/100 = 81.67 million. The number of above poverty line males in Karnataka will be 7/15 x 81.67 million = 38.11 million.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1037,10,'4','&lt;p&gt;Direction: The following table gives the percentage of population of Five States UP, MP, Rajasthan, Bihar and Punjab which are below poverty line and also the ratio of male to female among them. Study the table and answer the questions based on it.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/1/215.14.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;523&quot; height=&quot;158&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the above poverty line population of state Orissa is 75 million, find the below poverty line population of females in the state.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;13.63 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;13.33 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;13.93 million&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;13 million&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;25% of the population are below poverty line and so 25% are above the poverty line. So, 75% of the population is 75 million, which means that the total population is 75 x 100/75 = 100 million. So, total population below poverty line is 25 million. So, female population below poverty line will be 6/11 x 25 million = 150/11 million = 13.63 million.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1038,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following bar graph shows number of goods produced (in thousand) by companies P and Q in different years and the table will give us the percentage of goods sold by each company in each year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;268&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many units of goods was sold by both the companies in the year 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;27500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of goods sold by P in 2012 is 40 x 50/100 = 20,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of goods sold by Q in 2012 is 25 x 40/100 = 10,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of items sold is 30,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1039,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following bar graph shows number of goods produced (in thousand) by companies P and Q in different years and the table will give us the percentage of goods sold by each company in each year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;268&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The goods sold by company Q in 2011 is approximately what percent of the goods sold by company P in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;161.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;165%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;163.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;162.5%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total goods sold by Q in 2011 is 70/100 x 30,000 = 70 x 300 = 21,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total goods sold by P in 2013 is 65/100 x 20,000 = 65 x 200 = 13,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio required is 21/13 x 100% = 161.5%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1040,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following bar graph shows number of goods produced (in thousand) by companies P and Q in different years and the table will give us the percentage of goods sold by each company in each year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;268&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the average number of goods produced by company P and that of company Q over the entire period under consideration?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1500&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of goods produced by P over the years is 25 + 35 + 40 + 20 + 30 = 150 thousand.&lt;br /&gt;Average number of goods produced by company P is 150/5 = 30,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of goods produced by Q over the years is 20 + 30 + 25 + 40 + 15 = 130 thousand.&lt;br /&gt;Average number of goods produced by company Q is 130/5 = 28,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required difference is 30,000 &amp;ndash; 28,000 = 2000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1041,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following bar graph shows number of goods produced (in thousand) by companies P and Q in different years and the table will give us the percentage of goods sold by each company in each year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;268&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between number of goods produced by company P in 2014 and number of goods sold by company Q in 2010?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of goods produced by company P in 2014 is 30,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of goods sold by Q in 2010 is 20 x 50/100 = 10,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the difference required is 30,000 &amp;ndash; 10,000 = 20,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1042,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The following bar graph shows number of goods produced (in thousand) by companies P and Q in different years and the table will give us the percentage of goods sold by each company in each year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.1.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;268&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage of goods sold by &#039;P&amp;rsquo; in all these years?&#039;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;41.83%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40.83%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;42.83%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;44.83%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total goods that are produced by P is 25 + 35 + 40 + 20 + 30 = 150,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of goods sold by P in these years is (25 x 40/100) + (35 x 25/100) + (40 x 50/100) + (20 x 65/100) + (30 x 35/100) = 10 + 8.75 + 20 + 13.5 + 10.5 = 62,750.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the overall percentage required is 62750/150000 x 100% = 41.83%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1043,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. The bar graphs gives details about three different products (in thousands) produced by a company in five different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Number of motherboards produced in year 2011 was what percentage of total number of Motherboards produced in all the years together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20.6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18.5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15.5&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total motherboards produced in 2011 is 25,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of motherboards produced is 20 + 10 + 35 + 25 + 45 = 135,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage required is 25/135 x 100% = 18.5%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1044,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. The bar graphs gives details about three different products (in thousands) produced by a company in five different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the respective ratio between the number of Pen drives produced by company in the year 2010 and number of mice produced by the company in the year 2009?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 : 8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 8&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Total number of pen drives produced by the company in 2010 is 15,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of mice produced in 2009 is 40,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio is 15: 40 = 3: 8.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1045,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. The bar graphs gives details about three different products (in thousands) produced by a company in five different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the total number of mice and Pen drives produced by company together in the year 2012 and number of mice and motherboards produced by the company in 2008?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30 thousand&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75 thousand&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45 thousand&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50 thousand&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Number of mice and motherboards produced by the company in 2008 is 15 + 20 = 35,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of mice and Pen drives produced by the company in the year 2012 is 45 + 35 = 80,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required difference is 80,000 &amp;ndash; 35,000 = 45,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1046,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. The bar graphs gives details about three different products (in thousands) produced by a company in five different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the respective ratio between the number of mice produced by the company in year 2009, motherboards produced in 2011 and pen drives produced in 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 5 : 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 9 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 : 2 : 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 : 9 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of mice produced by the company in year 2009 is 10,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of motherboards produced by the company in year 2011 is 25,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of pen drives produced by the company in year 2012 is 45,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio required is 2: 5: 9.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1047,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. The bar graphs gives details about three different products (in thousands) produced by a company in five different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percent increase in production of A in year 2011 from the previous year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21.42%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20.56%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18.36%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total production of A in 2010 is 35 + 20 + 15 = 70,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total production of A in 2011 is 25 + 35 + 25 = 85,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage increase required is [85000 &amp;ndash; 70000]/70000 x 100% = 300/14% = 21.42%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1048,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The following bar graph shows income of a company A over 5 years (in Rs. Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profit earned by company A (in Rs. Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which year was the profit percentage highest?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2012&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2014&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Both I and II&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage is equal to Profit/Expenditure x 100%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In this case, if profit is P and income is I, the, the profit percentage will be P/(I-P) &amp;times; 100%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2010 will be 15/9 x 100% = 166.67%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2011 will be 18/8 x 100% = 225%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2012 will be 18/12 x 100% = 150%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2013 will be 10/8 x 100% = 125%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2014 will be 14/9 x 100% = 156.66%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage is highest in 2011.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1049,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The following bar graph shows income of a company A over 5 years (in Rs. Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profit earned by company A (in Rs. Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between profit percent of 2010 and that of 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14.6%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.6%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.3%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15.6%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2010 will be 15/9 x 100% = 166.67%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2012 will be 18/12 x 100% = 150%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required difference is 16.67%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1050,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The following bar graph shows income of a company A over 5 years (in Rs. Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profit earned by company A (in Rs. Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Profit earned in 2011 is what percent more than Expenditure in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;125%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;175%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Profit earned in 2011 is Rs. 18 lakh and the expenditure in 2013 is 18 &amp;ndash; 10 = Rs. 8 lakhs. So, the required percentage is [18-8]/8 x 100% = 1000/8 = 125%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1051,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The following bar graph shows income of a company A over 5 years (in Rs. Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profit earned by company A (in Rs. Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the average expenditure of company A in all the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9.2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9.6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8.6&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The total expenditure will be the difference between total income and total profit. So, total expenditure will be [24 + 26 + 30 + 18 + 23] &amp;ndash; [15 + 18 + 18 + 10 + 14] = 121 &amp;ndash; 75 = 46 lakhs. So, average expenditure of A in all the years is 46/5 = 9.2 lakh rupees.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1052,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The following bar graph shows income of a company A over 5 years (in Rs. Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profit earned by company A (in Rs. Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of expenditure in 2014 and income in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Income in 2013 is Rs. 18 lakh and expenditure in 2014 is 23 &amp;ndash; 14 = Rs. 9 lakh. So, the required ratio will be 9: 18 = 1: 2.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1053,11,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives us the data about the production (in Lacks) of Company A over the years. The table that follows gives us the ratio of production for A and B during these years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%201%20-%20Ex%201/222.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;