t;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The following bar graph shows the exports and imports of a company from 2002-2013 in crore rupees. Trade balance is defined as the difference between Exports and Imports.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In how many years there was a fall in imports, but a rise in exports compared to the previous year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;There is a fall in imports in 7 years. But it is accompanied with a rise in exports only in 4 years.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1060,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Refer to the following information for the following questions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The following bar graph shows the exports and imports of a company from 2002-2013 in crore rupees. Trade balance is defined as the difference between Exports and Imports.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which year is the trade balance maximum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2008&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2006&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2007&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2009&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Trade balance is the difference between the exports and imports. From the graph, we can see that the year is 2009 with a trade balance of +20 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1061,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Refer to the following information for the following questions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The following bar graph shows the exports and imports of a company from 2002-2013 in crore rupees. Trade balance is defined as the difference between Exports and Imports.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Trade Balance for the whole period, shown in the graph is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20 crore&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total exports is 60 + 65 + 70 + 60 + 60 + 80 + 80 + 85 + 40 + 45 + 70 + 65 = Rs. 780 crore.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total imports is 65 + 70 + 60 + 50 + 90 + 80 + 70 + 65 + 50 + 60 + 55 + 60 = Rs. 775 crore.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the overall trade balance is Rs. 5 crore&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1062,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Refer to the following information for the following questions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The following bar graph shows the exports and imports of a company from 2002-2013 in crore rupees. Trade balance is defined as the difference between Exports and Imports.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many years is the trade balance negative?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;For the trade balance to be negative, imports should be greater than exports. This happened in 5 years as can be seen from the graph.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1063,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following sub-divided graph shows the population of six cities (in lakhs) and the percentage of literate people in each city. Answer the following questions based on these graphs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the number of people in Hyderabad who are literate and in government jobs?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1038600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1238600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1248600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1128600&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;30% of literates in Hyderabad are in government jobs. So, the required number of people is (54/100) x (30/100) x 64 lakhs = 1036800.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1064,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following sub-divided graph shows the population of six cities (in lakhs) and the percentage of literate people in each city. Answer the following questions based on these graphs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of the total literate people who are not in government jobs in Mumbai and the number of literate people in Kolkata who are in government jobs?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;637 : 180&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;627 : 180&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;180 : 637&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;180 : 627&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are not in government jobs in Mumbai is (56/100) x (78/100) x 56 lakh = 2446080.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are in government jobs in Kolkata is (64/100) x (18/100) x 60 lakhs = 691200.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 637: 180.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1065,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following sub-divided graph shows the population of six cities (in lakhs) and the percentage of literate people in each city. Answer the following questions based on these graphs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the number of people in Bangalore who are literate but not in government jobs?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1896960&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1896690&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1996690&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1996960&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are not in government jobs in Bangalore is (48/100) x (76/100) x 52 lakhs = 1896960.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1066,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following sub-divided graph shows the population of six cities (in lakhs) and the percentage of literate people in each city. Answer the following questions based on these graphs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of literate people in all six cities who are in government jobs (in lakhs)?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;51.15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50.25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;52.35&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50.75&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are in government jobs in Hyderabad is (54/100) x (30/100) x 64 lakhs = 1036800.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are in government jobs in Bangalore is (48/100) x (24/100) x 52 lakhs = 599040.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are in government jobs in Chennai is (60/100) x (35/100) x 44 lakhs = 924000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are in government jobs in Delhi is (42/100) x (40/100) x 70 lakhs = 1176000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are in government jobs in Mumbai is (56/100) x (22/100) x 56 lakh = 689920.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of total literate people who are in government jobs in Kolkata is (64/100) x (18/100) x 60 lakhs = 691200.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total Number of total literate people who are in government jobs is 1036800 + 599040 + 924000 + 1176000 + 689920 + 691200 = 5116960 = 51.15 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1067,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following sub-divided graph shows the population of six cities (in lakhs) and the percentage of literate people in each city. Answer the following questions based on these graphs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage of people in Delhi who are in government jobs (It is given that no illiterate person is in govt. jobs)?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8.4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9.2%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8.8%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9.6%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;All the government job workers are literate. So, percentage of Delhi population who are in government jobs is 42/100 x 40 = 8.4%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1068,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below. The bar graph gives the percentage of failed student in different colleges and the table gives the ratio of failed and passed boys to girls in each college.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;368&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If total number of students passed in college D is 3600, find the number of Girls failed in same college?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;900&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2900&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;850&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total number of students who passed in D college is 3600. so, total number of students who filed is 3600 x 4/6 = 2400. So, the number of girls who failed in the exam in college D is 2400 x 3/8 = 900.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1069,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below. The bar graph gives the percentage of failed student in different colleges and the table gives the ratio of failed and passed boys to girls in each college.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;368&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If total number of students in college F is 8000, what will be the number of passed Boys in college F?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3560&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of students who passed in college F is 80/100 x 8000 = 6400. So, number of boys who passed in college F is 9/16 x 6400 = 3600.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1070,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below. The bar graph gives the percentage of failed student in different colleges and the table gives the ratio of failed and passed boys to girls in each college.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;368&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If total number of students in college A and C is 4200, how many students failed in both the college together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1450&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2750&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2250&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Can&#039;t be determined&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Cannot be determined because we do not know the individual strengths of each college.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1071,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below. The bar graph gives the percentage of failed student in different colleges and the table gives the ratio of failed and passed boys to girls in each college.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;368&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If number of failed students in college E is 5400, find total number of students in college E?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12300&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;45% of the students in college E is equal to 5400. So, the total strength of the college is 5400 x 100/45 = 12000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1072,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below. The bar graph gives the percentage of failed student in different colleges and the table gives the ratio of failed and passed boys to girls in each college.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;368&quot; height=&quot;159&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If failed students in college B is 9000 and failed students in college A is 15000, what is the total number of passed Girls in college A and B together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;31500&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Number of students who passed in college B will be 9000 x (70/30) = 21,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of passed girls in college B is (4/7) x 21,000 = 12,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of students who passed in college A will be 15000 x (75/25) = 45,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of passed girls in college A is (7/15) x 45,000 = 21,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of passed girls in the two colleges is 12000 + 21000 = 33000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1073,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the graph carefully answer the question that follow. Number of players participating in three different games from six different countries is given in the bar graph below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of players participating in Cricket from country 4 and country 2 is what percentage of the number of players participating in Badminton from countries 1 and 3?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;110.70%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;115.30%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;112.40%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;108.60%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The number of players participating in Cricket from country 4 and country 2 is 75 + 80 = 155. The number of players participating in Badminton from country 13and country 2 is 45 + 95 = 140. So, the percentage required is 155/140 x 100% = 110.7%&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1074,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the graph carefully answer the question that follow. Number of players participating in three different games from six different countries is given in the bar graph below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the sum of the number of players participating in Cricket from country 4, 5 and 6 and the number of players participating in Football from country 1, 2 and 3?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;405&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;455&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;435&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;445&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of players participating in Cricket from country 4, 5 and 6 is 80 + 70 + 60 = 210. Total number of players participating in Football from country 1, 2 and 3 is 65 + 70 + 90 = 225. So, total number of players required is 210 + 225 = 435.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1075,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the graph carefully answer the question that follow. Number of players participating in three different games from six different countries is given in the bar graph below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which country in the number of players participating in Football is the highest and number of player participating in Cricket is the lowest?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Country 3 and 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Country 4 and 6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Country 3 and 1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Country 5 and 1&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Football has highest number of players from country 3 and Cricket has lowest number of players from country 1.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1076,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the graph carefully answer the question that follow. Number of players participating in three different games from six different countries is given in the bar graph below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of player participating in Badminton from all the countries is what percent of total number of players participating in all games from country 3?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;134%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;164%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;126%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;157%&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Total number of players participating in badminton is 45 + 40 + 95 + 85 + 95 + 65 = 425. Total number of players participating from country 3 is 90 + 85 + 95 = 270. So, the percentage required is 425/270 x 100% = 157.4% = 157%&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1077,11,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the graph carefully answer the question that follow. Number of players participating in three different games from six different countries is given in the bar graph below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%202-%20Ex%202/223.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60% of players participating in all game from country 5 is male and 30% players participating in all game from country 3 is female. What will be their ratio?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;127 : 70&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;13 : 7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;49 : 27&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;87 : 55&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of male players from country 5 is [80 + 70 + 95] x 60/100 = 245 x 60/100 = 147. Total number of female players from country 3 is [90 + 85 + 95] x 30/100 = 270 x 30/100 = 81. So, the ratio required is 147: 81 = 49: 27.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1078,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar graph shows the income of two companies A and B over 5 years (in Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profits of the two companies A and B over those years (in Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the profit percent of company B over the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;139.4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;140.8%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;157.1%&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The total income for company B over the years is 18 + 20 + 12 + 24 + 16 = Rs. 90 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The total profit for company B over the years is 9 + 11 + 7 + 17 + 11 = Rs. 55 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total expenditure for company B will be 90 &amp;ndash; 55 = Rs. 35 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the profit percentage is (55/35) x 100% = 1100/7% = 157.14%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1079,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar graph shows the income of two companies A and B over 5 years (in Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profits of the two companies A and B over those years (in Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between profit percent of A in 2009 and B in 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;250%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;240%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;260%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The expenditure for company A during 2009 is (20 &amp;ndash; 16) = 4 lakhs and the profit is Rs. 16 lakh.&lt;br /&gt;So, the profit percentage for company A in 2009 is 16/4 x 100% = 400%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The expenditure for company B during 2011 is (12 &amp;ndash; 7) = Rs. 5 lakhs and the profit is Rs. 7 lakh.&lt;br /&gt;So, the profit percentage for company B in 2011 is 7/5 x 100% = 140%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the difference is 400 &amp;ndash; 140 = 260%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1080,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar graph shows the income of two companies A and B over 5 years (in Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profits of the two companies A and B over those years (in Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which year does A have maximum profit percent?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2009&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2012&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;As we can clearly see, the difference between the total income and profit is lowest in 2 years, 2009 and 2011.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit in 2009 is Rs. 16 lakh and the expenses during that year are 20 &amp;ndash; 16 = Rs. 4 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the profit percentage for that year is 16/4 x 100% = 400%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Profit in 2011 is Rs. 10 lakh and the expenses during that year are 14 &amp;ndash; 10 = Rs. 4 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the profit percentage for that year is 10/4 x 100% = 250%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the profit is maximum in the year 2009.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1081,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar graph shows the income of two companies A and B over 5 years (in Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profits of the two companies A and B over those years (in Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between total profit of A and B in 2012 and that of A and B in 2010?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The total profit in 2012 for A and B combines is 15 + 17 = Rs. 32 lakhs. The total profit in 2010 for A and B combines is 13 + 9 = Rs. 22 lakhs. So, the difference required is Rs. 10 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1082,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar graph shows the income of two companies A and B over 5 years (in Lakhs) and the line graph shows the profits of the two companies A and B over those years (in Lakhs).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference of the average incomes of A and B over the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.5 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.2 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;There is no difference&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The total income for company A over the years is 20 + 15 + 14 + 22 + 25 = Rs. 96 lakhs. So, the average income will be 96/5 = Rs. 19.2 lakh. The total income for company B over the years is 18 + 20 + 12 + 24 + 16 = Rs. 90 lakhs. So, the average income will be 90/5 = Rs. 18 lakh. So, the required difference is Rs. 1.2 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1083,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. In the following bar-chart the information about total population of five cities (A, B, C, D and E) and the percentage distribution of non-graduates, graduates and post graduates is given. Answer the questions based on this information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of people who are graduates in city B and who are non-graduates in city A?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of graduates in city B is 30/100 x 70 lakh = 21 lakh. Total number of non-graduates in city C is 40/100 x 60 lakh = 24 lakh. So, the required sum is 21 + 24 = 45 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1084,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. In the following bar-chart the information about total population of five cities (A, B, C, D and E) and the percentage distribution of non-graduates, graduates and post graduates is given. Answer the questions based on this information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of people in all five cities who are post graduates?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;73 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;69 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;71 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total number of post graduates in city A is 30/100 x 40 lakh = 12 lakh. Total number of post graduates in city B is 25/100 x 70 lakh = 17.5 lakh. Total number of post graduates in city C is 10/100 x 60 lakh = 6 lakh. Total number of post graduates in city D is 15/100 x 90 lakh = 13.5 lakh. Total number of post graduates in city E is 30/100 x 80 lakh = 24 lakh. So, total number of post graduates in all the cities is 12 + 17.5 + 6 + 13.5 + 24 = 73 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1085,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. In the following bar-chart the information about total population of five cities (A, B, C, D and E) and the percentage distribution of non-graduates, graduates and post graduates is given. Answer the questions based on this information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of the number of people who are graduates in cities A and E together to the number of people who are non-graduates in cities C and E together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 : 16&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 : 14&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of graduates in city A is 40/100 x 40 lakh = 16 lakh. Total number of graduates in city E is 25/100 x 80 lakh = 20 lakh. So, total number of graduates required is 16 + 20 = 36 lakh. Total number of non-graduates in city C is 40/100 x 60 lakh = 24 lakh. Total number of non-graduates in city E is 45/100 x 80 lakh = 36 lakh. Total number of non-gradates required is 24 + 36 = 60 lakh. So, the ratio is 36: 60 = 3: 5.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1086,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. In the following bar-chart the information about total population of five cities (A, B, C, D and E) and the percentage distribution of non-graduates, graduates and post graduates is given. Answer the questions based on this information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the average number of graduates in all the five cities together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;22.3 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21.7 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of graduates in city A is 40/100 x 40 lakh = 16 lakh. Total number of graduates in city B is 30/100 x 70 lakh = 21 lakh. Total number of graduates in city C is 50/100 x 60 lakh = 30 lakh. Total number of graduates in city D is 35/100 x 90 lakh = 31.5 lakh. Total number of graduates in city E is 25/100 x 80 lakh = 20 lakh. So, total number of graduates in all the cities is 16 + 21 + 30 + 21.5 + 20 = 108.5 lakhs. So, the average number of graduates will be 108.5/5 = 21.7 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1087,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. In the following bar-chart the information about total population of five cities (A, B, C, D and E) and the percentage distribution of non-graduates, graduates and post graduates is given. Answer the questions based on this information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of post graduates in city E is what percentage of the number of non-graduates in city A?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;180%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total number of post graduates in city E is 30/100 x 80 = 24 lakhs. Total number of non-graduates in city A is 30/100 x 40 = 12 lakhs. So, the required percentage is 24/12 x 100% = 200%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1088,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population (in lakhs) of 3 regions within the country over a period of five years and the table gives us information about the percentage break up of population into different age groups from these regions in different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;629&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of people in age group 0 &amp;ndash; 20 years from Mumbai from all the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18.25 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18.85 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18.65 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18.45 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 0 &amp;ndash; 20 years from Mumbai in 2010 is 17 x 15/100 = 2.55 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 0 &amp;ndash; 20 years from Mumbai in 2011 is 20 x 20/100 = 4 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 0 &amp;ndash; 20 years from Mumbai in 2012 is 18 x 15/100 = 2.7 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 0 &amp;ndash; 20 years from Mumbai in 2013 is 22 x 20/100 = 4.4 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 0 &amp;ndash; 20 years from Mumbai in 2014 is 24 x 20/100 = 4.8 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the total number of people is 2.55 + 4 + 2.7 + 4.4 + 4.8 = 18.45 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1089,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population (in lakhs) of 3 regions within the country over a period of five years and the table gives us information about the percentage break up of population into different age groups from these regions in different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;629&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of number of people in age group 40 &amp;ndash; 60 years from Delhi in 2012 to the number of people in age group 60+ years in 2014?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 : 17&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17 : 10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 : 8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 : 16&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 40 &amp;ndash; 60 years from Delhi in 2012 is 16 x 25/100 = 4 lakhs. Number of people in the age group 60 + years from Delhi in 2014 is 17 x 40/100 = 6.8 lakhs. So, the required ratio is 10: 17.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1090,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population (in lakhs) of 3 regions within the country over a period of five years and the table gives us information about the percentage break up of population into different age groups from these regions in different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;629&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of people in age group 20 &amp;ndash; 40 years is highest in which year from Chennai?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2012&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2013&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 20 &amp;ndash; 40 years from Chennai in 2010 is 20 x 20/100 = 4 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 20 &amp;ndash; 40 years from Chennai in 2011 is 23 x 25/100 = 5.75 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 20 &amp;ndash; 40 years from Chennai in 2012 is 25 x 30/100 = 7.5 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 20 &amp;ndash; 40 years from Chennai in 2013 is 21 x 30/100 = 6.3 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of people in the age group 20 &amp;ndash; 40 years from Chennai in 2014 is 18 x 25/100 = 4.5 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the number is highest in 2012.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1091,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population (in lakhs) of 3 regions within the country over a period of five years and the table gives us information about the percentage break up of population into different age groups from these regions in different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;629&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of people in age group 60 + years from Delhi in 2013 is what percent of the number of people in age group 60 + years in Mumbai from 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;96%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;98%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;97%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total number of people in the age group 60 + years from Delhi in 2013 is 14 x 35/100 = 4.9 lakhs. Total number of people in the age group 60 + years from Mumbai in 2011 is 20 x 25/100 = 5 lakhs. So, the required percentage is 4.9/5 x 100% = 98%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1092,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the information carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population (in lakhs) of 3 regions within the country over a period of five years and the table gives us information about the percentage break up of population into different age groups from these regions in different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;629&quot; height=&quot;121&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Total population of Chennai from all the years together is what percent more than total population of Delhi from all the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;31%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total population from Chennai over the years is 20 + 23 + 25 + 21 + 18 = 107 lakhs. Total population from Delhi over the years is 15 + 20 + 15 + 14 + 17 = 81 lakhs. So, the required percentage is [107 &amp;ndash; 81]/81 x 100% = 26/81 x 100% = 32%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1093,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The given bar graph shows the number of mobile users of three brands (X, Y and Z) in different cities. The table shows the percentage of Males among these mobile users for each brand.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;412&quot; height=&quot;141&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the number of Female mobile users of X brand in City C?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16960&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16720&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16480&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16240&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The total number of users for brand X in city C is 38000. Out of those users, 56% are male users. So, the remaining 44% are female users. So, the total number of female users required is 44/100 x 38000 = 44 x 380 = 16720&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1094,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The given bar graph shows the number of mobile users of three brands (X, Y and Z) in different cities. The table shows the percentage of Males among these mobile users for each brand.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;412&quot; height=&quot;141&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of Male users of Y brand in all the cities?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;148260&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;147260&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;146260&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;145260&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of male users for Y brand in city A is (50/100) x 45 x 1000 = 22,500.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of male users for Y brand in city B is (54/100) x 40 x 1000 = 21,600.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of male users for Y brand in city C is (44/100) x 65 x 1000 = 28,600.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of male users for Y brand in city D is (38/100) x 42 x 1000 = 15,960.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of male users for Y brand in city E is (40/100) x 30 x 1000 = 12,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of male users for Y brand in city F is (68/100) x 70 x 1000 = 47,600.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of males required is 22500 + 21600 + 28600 + 15960 + 12000 + 47600 = 148260.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1095,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The given bar graph shows the number of mobile users of three brands (X, Y and Z) in different cities. The table shows the percentage of Males among these mobile users for each brand.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;412&quot; height=&quot;141&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the average number of users of X brand and the average number of users of Z brand in all the six cities together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3750&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5000&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Total number of X brand users is 45 + 55 + 38 + 20 + 68 + 75 = 300,000.&lt;br /&gt;So, average number of users of brand X is 300,000/6 = 50,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of X brand users is 30 + 55 + 70 + 65 + 75 + 35 = 330,000.&lt;br /&gt;So, average number of users of brand X is 330,000/6 = 55,000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required difference is 5000.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1096,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The given bar graph shows the number of mobile users of three brands (X, Y and Z) in different cities. The table shows the percentage of Males among these mobile users for each brand.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;412&quot; height=&quot;141&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of Female brand Z users in City A and B together is what percentage of the total number of Male brand X users in City C and D together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;88.70%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;90.30%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;92.40%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;93.70%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Number of male users for brand X in city C is (56/100) x 38 x 1000 = 21280.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of male users for brand X in city D is (62/100) x 50 x 1000 = 31000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of male members is 21280 + 31000 = 52280.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of female users for brand Z in city A is (40/100) x 30 x 1000 = 12000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of female users for brand Z in city B is (66/100) x 55 x 1000 = 36300.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of female members is 12000 + 36300 = 48300.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The required ratio is (48300/52280) x 100% = 92.4%&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1097,11,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: The given bar graph shows the number of mobile users of three brands (X, Y and Z) in different cities. The table shows the percentage of Males among these mobile users for each brand.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%203%20-%20Ex%203/224.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;412&quot; height=&quot;141&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of Male users of brand Z in City A is what percentage more than the number of Female users of brand Z in City F? (Approximate value)&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2.85%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2.55%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3.15%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Number of male users of brand Z in city A is (60/100) x 30 x 1000 = 18000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of female users of brand Z in city F is 50/100 x 35 x 1000 = 17500.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required percentage is [(18000 &amp;ndash; 17500)/17500] x 100% = 100/35% = 2.85%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1098,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below: Following graph gives the Profit earned (in Crore) by Three companies A, B &amp;amp; C over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the average profit earned by all the three companies in the year 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;300 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;400 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;350 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;520 crore&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Average profit earned by the companies in 2011 is (400 + 450 + 350)/3 = 1200/3 = 400 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1099,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below: Following graph gives the Profit earned (in Crore) by Three companies A, B &amp;amp; C over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which of the following years was the difference between the profits earned by Company B and Company A the minimum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2006&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2007&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;It is minimum in 2010 and the minimum value is 25 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1100,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below: Following graph gives the Profit earned (in Crore) by Three companies A, B &amp;amp; C over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which of the following years was the total profit earned by all three companies together the highest?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2007&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2012&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total profit earned by that companies in the year 2012 is the maximum and the maximum value is (400 + 425 + 475) crore = 1300 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1101,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below: Following graph gives the Profit earned (in Crore) by Three companies A, B &amp;amp; C over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the approximate percentage increase in the profit earned by Company B from 2007 to 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;64&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Required percentage increase is (450 - 250)/250 x 100% = 80%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1102,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions given below: Following graph gives the Profit earned (in Crore) by Three companies A, B &amp;amp; C over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the difference between the profit earned by Company A in 2007 and the profit earned by Company C in 2009?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200 crore&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since both are same, there is no difference.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1103,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following graph shows the number of students passed (in thousands) from two Universities over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the respective ratio between the number of students passed from University A in 2010 and the number of students passed from University B in 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 : 13&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 : 11&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11 : 13&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 : 11&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Required Ratio = 40 : 55 = 8 : 11&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1104,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following graph shows the number of students passed (in thousands) from two Universities over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the sum of the students passed from University A in years 2008, 2010 and 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;125000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;135000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The required sum is 30,000 + 40,000 + 50,000 = 120,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1105,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following graph shows the number of students passed (in thousands) from two Universities over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Number of students passed from University B in the year 2009 is what percentage (rounded off to two digits) of the total number of students passed from University A over the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21.98%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11.32%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;19.65%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11.23%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Required Percentage is [30/(35 + 50 + 30 + 40 + 50 + 60)] x 100% = (30/265) x 100% = 11.32%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1106,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following graph shows the number of students passed (in thousands) from two Universities over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the total number of students passed from both the Universities in year 2009 together and the total number of students passed in the year 2012 from both the Universities together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24000&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of students in 2009 is 50 + 30 = 80,000. Total number of students in 2012 is 60 + 55 = 115,000. &amp;there4;The difference = 115,000 &amp;minus; 80,000 = 35,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1107,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following graph shows the number of students passed (in thousands) from two Universities over the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;416&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the respective ratio between the number of students passed in year 2008, 2010 and 2012 from University B?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 4 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 3 : 51&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8 : 9 : 11&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Required Ratio 40 : 45 : 55 = 8 : 9 : 11.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1108,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of televisions (in thousands) manufactured by three different companies in six different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;558&quot; height=&quot;444&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If 25 percent of the number of televisions manufactured by company A over all the years together were black and white, then what was the number of coloured televisions manufactured by company-A over all the years together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.4 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1.8 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18000&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total number of televisions manufactured by company A =(30 + 35 +35 + 40 + 45 + 55) thousand = 240 thousand.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4;Required number of coloured televisions = 240000 &amp;times; 75/100 = 180000 = 1.8 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1109,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of televisions (in thousands) manufactured by three different companies in six different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;558&quot; height=&quot;444&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the cost of manufacturing one television in the year 2008 was Rs.12000, then what was the total expenditure of company C for manufacturing all the televisions in the same year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 42 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 52 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 5.2 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4.2 crore&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Required expenditure = (12,000 &amp;times; 35,000) = 420,000,000 = 42 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1110,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of televisions (in thousands) manufactured by three different companies in six different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;558&quot; height=&quot;444&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was percentage increase in the number of televisions manufactured by company-C in year 2008 as compared to the previous year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Required percentage increase = (35-25)/25 &amp;times; 100 = 40%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1111,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of televisions (in thousands) manufactured by three different companies in six different years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;558&quot; height=&quot;444&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the approximate average number of televisions manufactured by company B over all the years together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30677&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40833&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40566&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;43055&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Required average is (25 + 30 + 45 + 40 + 55+ 50)/6 x 1000 = 245000/6 = 40833.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1112,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of televisions (in thousands) manufactured by three different companies in six different years.&lt;/p&gt