e red portion stands for the next five years. Study the grapha and answer the question.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;591&quot; height=&quot;381&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which of the items listed below accounts for the maximum expenditure during the year 1981 to 1985?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Communication&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Education&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Health&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Housing&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Out of the items listed in the question, clearly maximum expenditure during 1981-85 is on housing.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1129,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;DIrections: The following bar diagram represents the percentages of total expenditure incurred by a state during the years 1981- 90 for different items. In each bar the blue portion stands for the expenditure during the first five years and the red portion stands for the next five years. Study the grapha and answer the question.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;591&quot; height=&quot;381&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which of the items listed below accounts for the maximum expenditure during 1986 to 1990?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Agriculture&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Communication&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Education&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Health&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Out of the items listed in the question, clearly the maximum expenditure during 1986-90 is on agriculture.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1130,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;DIrections: The following bar diagram represents the percentages of total expenditure incurred by a state during the years 1981- 90 for different items. In each bar the blue portion stands for the expenditure during the first five years and the red portion stands for the next five years. Study the grapha and answer the question.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;591&quot; height=&quot;381&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The amount of expenditure on Agriculture is approximately what proportion of that on industry during the year 1986-90?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1/5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1/4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1/3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data inadequate&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Expenditure on agriculture during 1986-90 = (15-10) % of total expenditure = 5x/100 = x/20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Expenditure on industry during 1986-90 = (52.5-27.5) % of total expenditure = 25x/100 =x/4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Required ratio = x/20 : x/4 = 1 : 5.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1131,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;DIrections: The following bar diagram represents the percentages of total expenditure incurred by a state during the years 1981- 90 for different items. In each bar the blue portion stands for the expenditure during the first five years and the red portion stands for the next five years. Study the grapha and answer the question.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;591&quot; height=&quot;381&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the total expenditure on housing is Rs. 610 crore during 1981 -85, the total expenditure on industry during the same period would (approximately)&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 2440 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 1220 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 4620 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Expenditure on housing during 1981-85 = 10% of total expenditure.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Let the total expenditure be Rs. x.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Then, 10% of x = 610 crore or 10x/100 = 610 crore =&amp;gt; x = 6100 crore.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total expenditure on industry during 1981-85 = 25% of 6100 crore Rs 1525 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1132,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;DIrections: The following bar diagram represents the percentages of total expenditure incurred by a state during the years 1981- 90 for different items. In each bar the blue portion stands for the expenditure during the first five years and the red portion stands for the next five years. Study the grapha and answer the question.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.7.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;591&quot; height=&quot;381&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Out of every 10,000 rupees spent during 1981-90 approximately, how much was spent during the years 1981-85 on housing?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 1400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 700&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 1000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 2800&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;20% of total expenditure during 1981-90 was spent on housing.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Expenditure on housing during 1981-90 for a total expenditure of Rs 10000 = (20&amp;times;10000/100) = Rs 2000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Ratio of expenditure on housing during 1981-85 and that during 1986-90 = 10/ (20-10) = 1/1.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, Expenditure on housing during 1981-85 = Rs 1000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1133,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph and answer the questions given below:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;587&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Out of the total number of students who opted for the given three subjects, in the year 2009, 38% were girls. How many boys opted for Mathematics in the same year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1322&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1332&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1312&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Cannot be determined&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Number of students who opted for all three subjects in 2009 = (20 + 20 + 5) thousand = 45000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of boys = 45000/100 x 62 = 27900.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since, we do not know the number of girls in Mathematics, number of boys opted for Mathematics cannot be determined.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1134,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph and answer the questions given below:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;587&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the total number of students in the University in the year 2007 was 455030, then, the total number of students who opted for the given three subjects were approximately what percent of the total students?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;19&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Required percentage = (15 + 15 + 10) x 1000/455030 x 100 = 4000000/455030 = 9%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1135,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph and answer the questions given below:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;587&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of students who opted for Hindi and who opted for Mathematics in the years 2006, 2007 and 2009 together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;97000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;93000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;95000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Required number of students = (5 + 35 + 15 + 15 + 20 + 5) x 1000 = 95 x 1000 = 95000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1136,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph and answer the questions given below:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;587&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The total number of students who opted for Mathematics in the years 2005 and 2008 together are approximately what percent of the total number of students who opted for all three subjects in the same years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;38&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;42&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Required percentage = [15+30]/[5+35+15+25+30+30] x 100 = 45/145 x 100 = 32%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1137,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph and answer the questions given below:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.8.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;587&quot; height=&quot;335&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the respective ratio between the number of students who opted for English in the years 2006 and 2008 together and the number of students who opted for Hindi in the year 2005 and 2009 together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 : 7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11 : 7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Required ratio = (25 + 30): (5 + 20) = 55 : 25 = 11 : 5.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1138,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Monthly income (Rs in thousand) of three different persons in six different years&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.9.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;584&quot; height=&quot;350&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the difference between the total monthly salary of Arun in all the years together and Suman&#039;s monthly income in the year 2007?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.24 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.14 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 11.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 12.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Arun monthly income in all year together = 14 +18 + 23 +21 + 27 + 26 = 129 thousand. Suman&#039;s monthly income in the year 2007 = 15 thousand. &amp;there4; Difference = 129 &amp;ndash; 15 = 114 = 114 x 1000 = 114000 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1139,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Monthly income (Rs in thousand) 