Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;480&quot; height=&quot;288&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which of the following pairs of years the total import is equal to total export in the same pair of years ?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1996 and 1997&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1993 and 1998&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1998 and 1999&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1995 and 1996&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Obvious from the graph.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1171,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;480&quot; height=&quot;288&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The total exports in the years 1995, 1996 and 1999 together are what per cent of the total import during the same period? (up to two decimal places).&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;107&amp;middot;41&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;107&amp;middot;14&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;96&amp;middot;29&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;93&amp;middot;67&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total exports in the years 1995, 1996 and 1999 = 35 + 40 + 55 = 130 crore. Total imports in the years 1995, 1996 and 1999 = 40 + 50 + 45 = 135 crore. Now required % = 130/135 &amp;times;100 = 96.29%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1172,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;480&quot; height=&quot;288&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which of the following pairs of years and the per cent increase in the export over the previous year is correctly matched?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1996 - 14&amp;middot;29&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1997 - 10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1995 - 33&amp;middot;33&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1994 - 11&amp;middot;11&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;In 1996, % increase in export = 5/35 &amp;times; 100 = 14&amp;middot;29%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1173,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;524&quot; height=&quot;323&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the average number of females from all the Organizations together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3550&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3300&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Reqd. average = (2750 + 4000 + 4250 + 3750+ 3500)/5 = 18250/5 = 3650&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1174,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;524&quot; height=&quot;323&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of males from Organization A is approximately what per cent of the total number of males from all the Organizations together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;28&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;31&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Reqd. % = 3000 &amp;times; 100/ (3000 + 3750 + 4000 + 2500+ 3250) = 3000/16500 &amp;times;100 = 18&amp;middot;18%&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1175,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;524&quot; height=&quot;323&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the total number of females and the total number of males from all the Organizations together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1750&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1800&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2050&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Required difference = 18250 &amp;ndash; 16500 = 1750&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1176,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;524&quot; height=&quot;323&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the respective ratio of number of females from Organizations C to the number of females from Organization E?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14 : 17&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17 : 14&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14 : 15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 : 14&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Reqd. ratio = 4250 : 3500 = 17 : 14&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1177,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.16.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;524&quot; height=&quot;323&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The total numbers of males from Organizations A &amp;amp; B together are approximately what per cent of the total number of males from Organizations C, D and E together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;58&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;69&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;52&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Reqd. % = 6750/9750 &amp;times; 100 = 69.23%&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1178,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population of 5 different regions and the percentage breakup of Men, Female and Children in each of them.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the average number of Male population in all the years together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.65 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.25 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.45 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.35 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Male population in 2009 is 45/100 x 20 = 9 lakh. Male population in 2010 is 38/100 x 30 = 11.4 lakh. Male population in 2011 is 41/100 x 45 = 18.45 lakh. Male population in 2012 is 52/100 x 40 = 20.8 lakh. Male population in 2013 is 29/100 x 35 = 10.15 lakh. Total male population over the years is 9 + 11.4 + 18.45 + 20.8 + 10.15 = 88.25. So, the average male population over the years is 88.25/5 lakh = 17.65 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1179,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population of 5 different regions and the percentage breakup of Men, Female and Children in each of them.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the total Female population and the total child population over all the years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.35 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.45 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.55 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Difference between female and child population in 2009 is (27 &amp;ndash; 28) x 20/100 = &amp;ndash; 0.2 lakh. Difference between female and child population in 2010 is (34 &amp;ndash; 28) x 30/100 = 1.8 lakh. Difference between female and child population in 2011 is (24 &amp;ndash; 35) x 45/100 = &amp;ndash; 4.95 lakh. Difference between female and child population in 2012 is (23 &amp;ndash; 25) x 40/100 = &amp;ndash; 0.8 lakh. Difference between female and child population in 2013 is (42 &amp;ndash; 29) x 35/100 = 4.55 lakh. So, the total difference is (1.8 + 4.55) &amp;ndash; (0.8 + 4.95 + 0.2) = 6.35 &amp;ndash; 5.95 = 0.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1180,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population of 5 different regions and the percentage breakup of Men, Female and Children in each of them.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of the total male population in 2009 and 2010 to the total female population in 2012 and 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;114 : 239&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;239 : 114&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23 : 48&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;231 : 479&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Male population in 2009 is 45/100 x 20 = 9 lakh. Male population in 2010 is 38/100 x 30 = 11.4 lakh. So, total male population is 9 + 11.4 = 20.4 lakh. Feale population in 2012 is 23/100 x 40 = 9.2 lakh. Feale population in 2013 is 42/100 x 35 = 14.7 lakh. So, total female population is 9.2 + 14.7 = 23.9 lakh. So, the required ratio is 114: 239&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1181,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population of 5 different regions and the percentage breakup of Men, Female and Children in each of them.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of Female and male population in 2009 is what percentage of Number of male and Child population in 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33.33%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;39.20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36.70%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30.00%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total male and female population in 2009 is [40 + 27] x 20/100 = 67 x 0.2 = 13.4 lakh. Total male and children population in 2011 is [41 + 35] x 45/100 = 76 x 4.5 = 34.2 lakh So, the required ratio is 13.4/34.2 x 100% = 39.2%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1182,11,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The bar graph gives the total population of 5 different regions and the percentage breakup of Men, Female and Children in each of them.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%202%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/225.17.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of Females in 2013 is what percent more or less then number of Children in 2009?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;64.28% more&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;66.48% more&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;65.38% more&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;67.28% more&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of females in 2013 is 23/100 x 40 = 9.2 lakh. The number of children in 2009 is 28/100 x 20 = 5.6 lakh. So, the required percentage is [9.2 &amp;ndash; 5.6]/5.6 x 100% = 64.28% more.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1183,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage profit earned by two companies &#039;A&#039; and &#039;B&#039; during the period of 2008 to 2014. Study the graph and then answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the expenditure of company A and B in year 2008 was 18.5 lakh and 17.3 lakh respectively then what was the income of company A and company B together in year 2008?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;47.27 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48.27 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48.54 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;47.54 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Expenditure of company A in 2008 is Rs. 18.5 lakh and profit percentage in 2008 is 30%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the income for company A in 2008 is 18.5 x (100 + 30)/100 lakh = 24.05 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Expenditure of company B in 2008 is Rs. 17.3 lakh and profit percentage in 2008 is 40%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the income for company A in 2008 is 17.3 x (100 + 40)/100 lakh = 24.22 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total income for the two companies is 24.05 + 24.22 = 48.27 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1184,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage profit earned by two companies &#039;A&#039; and &#039;B&#039; during the period of 2008 to 2014. Study the graph and then answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the income of company A in 2011 and that of B in 2013 are Rs. 24.36 lakh and Rs. 18.36 lakh respectively then what is the total expenditure of company A in 2011 and company B in 2010?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32.16 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;31.24 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32.84 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;33.56 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The income of company A in 2011 is Rs. 24.36 lakh and the profit percentage is 35%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the expenditure for company A in 2011 is 24.36 x 100/(100+35) = 24.36/1.35 = 18.04 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The income of company B in 2013 is Rs. 18.36 lakh and the profit percentage is 30%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the expenditure for company A in 2011 is 18.36 x 100/(100+30) = 18.36/1.3 = 14.12 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total expenditure required is 18.04 + 14.12 = 32.16 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1185,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage profit earned by two companies &#039;A&#039; and &#039;B&#039; during the period of 2008 to 2014. Study the graph and then answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the expenditure of company A in 2009 and income of company B in 2011 are equal then what will be the ratio of income of company A in 2009 and expenditure of company B in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 : 8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;19 : 10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Can&#039;t be calculated&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the expenditure of company A in 2009 and income of B in 2011 be Rs. Z each.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since the profit percent for A in 2009 is 35%, the income for A in 2009 is Z x 135/100 = 1.35Z.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since the profit percent for B in 2011 is 40%, the expenditure for B in 2011 is Z x 100/140 = Z/1.4.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required ratio is 1.35Z: Z/1.4 = (1.35 x 1.4): 1 = 1.89: 1 which is approximately equal to 19: 10.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1186,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage profit earned by two companies &#039;A&#039; and &#039;B&#039; during the period of 2008 to 2014. Study the graph and then answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the expenditure of company A in 2012 and company B in 2009 are equal then the income of company A in 2012 is approximately what percentage of income of company B in 2009?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;92.85%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;86.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;107.7%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;118.5%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the expenditure of company A in 2012 and of company B in 2009 be Rs. Z each.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since the profit percent for A in 2012 is 40%, the income for A in 2009 is Z x 140/100 = 1.4Z.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since the profit percent for B in 2009 is 30%, the income for B in 2009 is Z x 130/100 = 1.3Z.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage required is 1.4Z/1.3Z x 100% = 1400/13 = 107.7%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1187,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage profit earned by two companies &#039;A&#039; and &#039;B&#039; during the period of 2008 to 2014. Study the graph and then answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In the following years, in which year is the percentage rise/fall percent profit of company B is maximum compare to its previous year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2008&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2009&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;It is highest in 2011.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1188,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the line graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The line graph shows the total production of fruits in different years (in tons) and the pie graph shows the percentage of each variety of fruits which remains the same throughout the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If 16 2/3% of Mango produced in 2012 was exported at Rs. 45 per kg, what was the total revenue, earned from export of Mango in the year 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3.375 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3.5 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3.125 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3.25 Lakh&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total amount of mango, in tons, produced in 2012 is 300 x 15/100 = 45 tons. Out of it, 16 2/3% is exported. So, amount of mango exported is 50/300 x 45 = 7.5 tons. So, total revenue is 7.5 x 1000 x 45 = 3.375 lakh rupees.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1189,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the line graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The line graph shows the total production of fruits in different years (in tons) and the pie graph shows the percentage of each variety of fruits which remains the same throughout the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the respective ratio between total Orange and Mango produced in 2010 to same fruits produced in 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 : 6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Since the ratio of each fruit remains the same over the years, the required ratio is simply the ratio of the total production. So, ratio required is 250: 300 = 5: 6.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1190,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the line graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The line graph shows the total production of fruits in different years (in tons) and the pie graph shows the percentage of each variety of fruits which remains the same throughout the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If half of the Grapes produced in 2008 was exported and total revenue generated was approximately Rs. 1.65 lakh, what was the price per ton generated by Grapes exported?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 5000 / ton&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6000 / ton&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 5500 / ton&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6500 / ton&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total amount of grapes produced in 2008 is 300 x 22/100 = 66 tons. So, amount of grapes that was exported is 50% = 66 x 50/100 = 33 tons. The total amount of revenue generated is Rs. 1.65 lakhs. So, the price per ton is 1.65/33 = Rs. 5000/ton.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1191,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the line graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The line graph shows the total production of fruits in different years (in tons) and the pie graph shows the percentage of each variety of fruits which remains the same throughout the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If total fruits produced in 2006 is 25 % less than fruits produced in 2011, then how many Pineapple are produced in 2006?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75 tons&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;70 tons&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80 tons&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;85 tons&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total production in 2006 will be 400 x 100/75 = 300 tons. So, total pineapple production in 2006 is 300 x 25/100 = 75 tons.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1192,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the line graph carefully to answer the questions that follow. The line graph shows the total production of fruits in different years (in tons) and the pie graph shows the percentage of each variety of fruits which remains the same throughout the years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the respective ratio between Orange produced in 2010 to Mango produced in 2006, if total fruits produced in 2006 is 50% less than fruit produced in 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total production in 2006 will be 300 x 100/50 = 150 tons. Total production in 2010 is 250 tons. So, the required ratio is (250 x 18/100): (150 x 15/100) = 90: 45 = 2: 1.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1193,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage growth in population of six cities A, B, C, D, E and F from 2011 to 2012 and 2012 to 2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the population of City A is 5.4 lakh in year 2011 then what will be its population in year 2013.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7.842 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8.424 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8.765 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The population in 2011 is 5.4 lakh. The increment percentages over the next two years are 25% and 20% respectively. So, the population in 2013 will be 5.4 x 125/100 x 120/100 = 5.4 x 6/4 = 8.1 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1194,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage growth in population of six cities A, B, C, D, E and F from 2011 to 2012 and 2012 to 2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage increase in population of city C from year 2011 to year 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;55%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;62.5%&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The total increment from 2011 to 2013 will be (x + y + xy/100)% or [30 + 25 + 7.5] % = 62.5%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1195,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage growth in population of six cities A, B, C, D, E and F from 2011 to 2012 and 2012 to 2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the population of city E and City D are equal in year 2012 then the population of city E is approximately what percentage of population of city D in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;92%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;96%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;104%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;108%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let their populations be each P. So, their populations in 2013 will be 1.35P and 1.3P respectively, as the growth rates are 35% and 30% respectively. So, the required percentage is 1.3P/1.35P x 100% = 2600/27 = 96.296% = 96%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1196,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage growth in population of six cities A, B, C, D, E and F from 2011 to 2012 and 2012 to 2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the population of city-F in year 2013 is 16.848 lakh, then what was its population in year 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9.2 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9.6 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10.4 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the population in 2011 be P. Since the growth percentages are 35% and 25%, the population in 2013 will be 1.35 x 1.25P = 16.848 lakh. So, P = 16.848/[1.35 x 1.25] = 9.984 lakh or 10 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1197,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following line graph shows the percentage growth in population of six cities A, B, C, D, E and F from 2011 to 2012 and 2012 to 2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the population of city-B and city-D in year 2011 are equal to 6 lakh, then what will be the difference between population of city-D in 2013 and population of city-B in 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3.1 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.3 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;0.5 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Population of city B in 2011 would be 6/1.2 = 5 lakhs. (Growth % in 2011 &amp;ndash; 12 is 20%) The population of D in 2013 would be 6 x 35% = 8.1 lakhs. (Growth % in 2012 &amp;ndash; 13 is 35%) So, the difference will be 8.1 &amp;ndash; 5 = 3.1 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1198,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Refer to the following information for the following questions. The following bar chart shows the sales (in Rs. crore) for a company over the years and the line graph shows the expense as a percentage of the total sales.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the profit in 2012 in Rs. crore?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21.84&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;21.42&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;22.84&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;22.42&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;We can see that the expense is 48% of the total sale. So, the remaining 52% will be the profit on the total sale. So, the total profit will be 52/100 x 42 crore = 21.84 crore&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1199,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Refer to the following information for the following questions. The following bar chart shows the sales (in Rs. crore) for a company over the years and the line graph shows the expense as a percentage of the total sales.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;By what percentage has the expense changed (approximately) between 2010 and 2011?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;118.57%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;116.57%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120.57%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;115.6%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total expense in 2010 is 42/100 x 20 crore = 840 lakhs. Total expense in 2011 is 54/100 x 34 crore = 1836 lakhs. So, percentage increase is [1836 &amp;ndash; 840]/840 x 100% = 996/840 x 100% = 118.57%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1200,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Refer to the following information for the following questions. The following bar chart shows the sales (in Rs. crore) for a company over the years and the line graph shows the expense as a percentage of the total sales.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the approximate percentage change in the profit between 2011 and 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Profit percentage in 2011 is 46% and in 2012, it is 52%. So, total profit in 2011 is 34 x 46/100 = Rs. 1564 lakhs and in 2012 is 52/100 x 42 crore = 2184 lakhs. So, the required percentage is [2184 &amp;ndash; 1564]/1564 x 100% = 620/1564 x 100% = 39.64%&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1201,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Refer to the following information for the following questions. The following bar chart shows the sales (in Rs. crore) for a company over the years and the line graph shows the expense as a percentage of the total sales.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which year shows the maximum percentage change in sales?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2012&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2013&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The year is 2011 where there is a 70% change in the sales.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1202,12,'1','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Refer to the following information for the following questions. The following bar chart shows the sales (in Rs. crore) for a company over the years and the line graph shows the expense as a percentage of the total sales.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%201%20-%20Ex1/232.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the average profit of all given years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.32 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.32 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;18.32 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;19.32 crore&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total profit in 2010 is 20 x 58/100 = Rs. 1160 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total profit in 2011 is 34 x 46/100 = Rs. 1564 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total profit in 2012 is 52/100 x 42 = 2184 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total profit in 2013 is 38 x 54/100 = Rs. 2052 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total profit in 2014 is 34 x 50/100 = Rs. 1700 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total profit over the years is 1160 + 1564 + 2184 + 2052 + 1700 = 8660 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the average profit will be 86.60/5 = Rs. 17.32 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1203,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of imports to exports of two companies A and B during the period 2009&amp;ndash;2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of imports to exports of Company A in the year 2010 was what percentage more than that of Company B in the same year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The values of the ratio for A and B are 0.9 and 0.75 respectively. So, the required percentage is [0.9 &amp;ndash; 0.75]/0.75 x 100% = 20%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1204,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of imports to exports of two companies A and B during the period 2009&amp;ndash;2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the exports of Company A in the year 2011 was Rs 10 lakhs, then what would be the value of imports in the same year for Company B?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 8 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 12.5 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 9 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Can&amp;rsquo;t be determined&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;We cannot determine the value of imports for B because we do not know the specific value of the exports or the imports for company B. Only the ratio is given.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1205,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of imports to exports of two companies A and B during the period 2009&amp;ndash;2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the imports of Company A in the year 2011 and the exports of Company B in the year 2012 were Rs 60 lakhs and Rs 50 lakh respectively, then what is the ratio of the imports of Company A in the year 2011 to that of Company B in the year 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 : 9&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 : 10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The imports of company A in 2011 is Rs. 60 lakh and the ratio of imports to exports is 1.2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the exports for company A in 2011 is 60/1.2 = Rs. 50 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The exports of company B in 2012 is Rs. 50 lakh and the ratio of imports to exports is 0.9.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the imports for company B in 2012 is 50 x 0.9 = Rs. 45 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the ratio required is 50: 45 = 10: 9.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1206,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of imports to exports of two companies A and B during the period 2009&amp;ndash;2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which of the years is the difference between the imports and exports of Company A the maximum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2008&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2009&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Can&amp;rsquo;t be determined&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;This value cannot be determined. For e.g. If imports are 10 crore and exports are 20 crore, then the ratio of imports to exports is 0.5. If imports are 40 crore and exports are 80 crore, then the ratio of imports to exports is still 0.5 but the difference is now increased 4 times. So, we need additional data in this case.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1207,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of imports to exports of two companies A and B during the period 2009&amp;ndash;2014.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the imports of Company A in 2013 was Rs. 88 lakhs and the exports of Company B in 2014 was Rs. 320 lakhs, then by what percentage was the imports of Company B in 2014 more than the exports of Company A in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The imports of company A in 2013 is Rs. 88 lakh and the ratio of imports to exports is 1.1.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the exports for company A in 2013 is 88/1.1 = Rs. 80 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The exports of company B in 2014 is Rs. 320 lakh and the ratio of imports to exports is 0.5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the imports for company B in 2014 is 320 x 0.5 = Rs. 160 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the percentage required is 320/160 x 100% = 200%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1208,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the question given below it: The pie diagram shows the percentage proportion of income of seven companies in a state during financial year &amp;ndash; 2013 &amp;ndash; 14 and the line diagram shows the percentage profit of these companies during the same Financial Year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the expenditure of company D is Rs. 800 lakh, what was the total income of all the given companies together in Rs. crore?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;51.11&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;51.22&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50.11&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50.22&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Here E = 800 lakh and x = 15%, so, the income of D is 800 x 115/100 = Rs. 920 lakhs. The income of D is only 18% of the total income of all the companies. So, the total income is 920 x 100/18 = Rs. 51.111 crore. * If the profit is x%, then the income would be (100 + x) E/100, where E is the expenditure.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1209,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the question given below it: The pie diagram shows the percentage proportion of income of seven companies in a state during financial year &amp;ndash; 2013 &amp;ndash; 14 and the line diagram shows the percentage profit of these companies during the same Financial Year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If in the given financial year, income of company A was Rs. 4.4 crore, what was the approximately expenditure of company C in that year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 2 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 4 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 1.83 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3.66 crore&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Income of A and income of C are in the ratio 14: 7 or 2: 1. So, the income of C is 4.4/2 = Rs. 2.2 crore. The percentage profit of C in that year is 20%. So, the expenditure of C in that year is 2.2 x 100/120 = Rs. 1.83 crore. * If the profit is x%, then the expenditure would be 100Y/ (100 + x), where Y is the income.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1210,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the question given below it: The pie diagram shows the percentage proportion of income of seven companies in a state during financial year &amp;ndash; 2013 &amp;ndash; 14 and the line diagram shows the percentage profit of these companies during the same Financial Year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of the expenditure of company F to company B?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;55 : 39&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;54 : 38&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;11 : 8&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The incomes of company F and company B will be in the ratio 20: 13 respectively. Let them be 20Y and 13Y respectively. The profits for F and B are 20% and 10% respectively. So, the expenditures of F and B are 20Y/1.2 and 13Y/1.1 respectively. So, the required ratio is 22: 15.6 = 220: 156 = 55: 39.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1211,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the question given below it: The pie diagram shows the percentage proportion of income of seven companies in a state during financial year &amp;ndash; 2013 &amp;ndash; 14 and the line diagram shows the percentage profit of these companies during the same Financial Year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the difference between the income of company F and company A is Rs. 750 crore, what is the expenditure of both the companies together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3483.33 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3583.33 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3383.33 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 3283.33 crore&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of the incomes of company F and company A is 20: 14 or 10: 7. So, let the incomes be 10Y and 7Y respectively. So, the difference will be 10Y &amp;ndash; 7Y = 3Y = 750 =&amp;gt; Y = Rs. 250 crore. So, the incomes of both of them will be Rs. 2500 crore and Rs. 1750 crore respectively. Since the respective profits are 20% and 25% respectively, their expenditures will be 2500/1.2 = Rs. 2083.33 crore and 1750/1.25 = Rs. 1400 crore respectively. So, the sum of their expenditures is 2083.33 + 1400 = Rs. 3483.33 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1212,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the question given below it: The pie diagram shows the percentage proportion of income of seven companies in a state during financial year &amp;ndash; 2013 &amp;ndash; 14 and the line diagram shows the percentage profit of these companies during the same Financial Year.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the income of company D and B together is Rs. 310 crore, then find the profit of company B in that year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 11.82 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 11.72 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 11.62 crore&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 11.52 crore&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Income of D and B is 31% of the total income. So, income of B will be 310 x 100/31 x 13/100 = Rs. 130 crore. So, the expenditure of company B will be 130/1.1 = Rs. 118.18 crore. So, the profit of company B will be 130 &amp;ndash; 118.18 = Rs. 11.82 crore.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1213,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the questions given below. Following line-graph shows the total number of boys and girls selected in an entrance examination during the period 2009 to 2014 and the table shows the percentage of rural boys among total boys and the percentage of rural girls among total girls selected in examination.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;341&quot; height=&quot;139&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the average number of girls selected from rural areas in all six years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2560&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2540&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2520&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2500&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of girls selected from the rural background is (4000 x 30/100) + (15000 x 42/100) + (12000 x 24/100) + (8000 x 16/100) + (10000 x 25/100) + (5000 x 35/100) = 1200 + 6300 + 2880 + 1280 + 2500 + 1750 = 15910.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the average number of girls selected from rural background is 15910/6 = 2561.67 = 2560.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1214,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the questions given below. Following line-graph shows the total number of boys and girls selected in an entrance examination during the period 2009 to 2014 and the table shows the percentage of rural boys among total boys and the percentage of rural girls among total girls selected in examination.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;341&quot; height=&quot;139&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the average number of boys selected and the average number of girls selected in all the six years together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1250&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1750&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total number of boys selected is 6 + 12 + 15 + 10 + 8 + 12 = 63,000. Total number of girls selected is 4 + 15 + 12 + 8 + 10 + 5 = 54,000. So, the required difference is 63000/6 &amp;ndash; 54000/6 = 1500.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1215,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the questions given below. Following line-graph shows the total number of boys and girls selected in an entrance examination during the period 2009 to 2014 and the table shows the percentage of rural boys among total boys and the percentage of rural girls among total girls selected in examination.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;341&quot; height=&quot;139&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In the year 2012, the difference between the total number of boys selected from urban areas and the total number of girls selected from rural areas?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6950&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6920&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6850&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6820&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total number of boys of urban background selected in 2012 is 10,000 x 82/100 = 8200. Total number of girls of rural background selected in 2012 is 8,000 x 16/100 = 1280. So, the difference required is 8200 &amp;ndash; 1280 = 6920.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1216,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the questions given below. Following line-graph shows the total number of boys and girls selected in an entrance examination during the period 2009 to 2014 and the table shows the percentage of rural boys among total boys and the percentage of rural girls among total girls selected in examination.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;341&quot; height=&quot;139&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In the year 2011, the number of boys selected from urban areas is approximately what percentage more than the number of girls selected from rural area?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;320%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;300%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;250%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;340%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of urban boys selected in 2011 is 15000 x 81/100 = 12150. Number of rural girls selected in 2011 is 12000 x 24/100 = 2880. So, the percentage required is [12150 &amp;ndash; 2880]/2880 x 100% = 9270/2880 x 100% = 321. 875%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1217,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following information carefully and answer the questions given below. Following line-graph shows the total number of boys and girls selected in an entrance examination during the period 2009 to 2014 and the table shows the percentage of rural boys among total boys and the percentage of rural girls among total girls selected in examination.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.3.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;341&quot; height=&quot;139&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of the girls selected from urban areas in the year 2010 to the number of girls selected from rural areas in the year 2014?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;174 : 35&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35 : 174&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 : 1&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of urban girls selected in 2010 is 15000 x 58/100 = 8700. Number of rural girls selected in 2014 is 5000 x 35/100 = 1750. So, the ratio is 8700: 1750 = 174: 35&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1218,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following line graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. Percentage profit earned by three shopkeepers in six different years are given in the line diagram below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If shopkeeper B sold 450 items in 2010 at Rs. 21 per item, what is the cost price of all items together during the same year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 7650&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6750&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 6175&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Total income for him is 450 x 21 = Rs. 9450. His profit percentage is 40%. So, his total cost price will be C = 9450/1.4 = Rs. 6750. * If the income is Y and profit percentage is x, then the expense is 100Y/ (100 + x).&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1219,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following line graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. Percentage profit earned by three shopkeepers in six different years are given in the line diagram below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If amount of profit earned by shopkeeper C in 2013 is Rs. 90,000, what was the selling price of all items in that year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 398500&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 395000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 390000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 397500&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Profit percent for shopkeeper C in 2013 is 30%. If the cost price of the items is C, then the selling price will be 1.3C and the profit is 0.3C So, 0.3C = 90,000 =&amp;gt; C = 300,000. So, the selling price is 1.3C = Rs. 390,000.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1220,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following line graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. Percentage profit earned by three shopkeepers in six different years are given in the line diagram below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the per cent rise in percentage profit of shopkeeper A in 2011 from the previous year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;48%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50%&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The percentage profit in the two years is 30% and 45%. So, the percentage required is [45 &amp;ndash; 30]/30 x 100% = 50%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1221,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following line graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. Percentage profit earned by three shopkeepers in six different years are given in the line diagram below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of the profit earned by the shopkeeper A in 2010 to profit earned by shopkeeper C in 2012?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;6 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data inadequate&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;We do not know the incomes or expenditures of A and C. so, data is inadequate to come to a decision in this case.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1222,12,'2','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Read the following line graph carefully and answer the questions that follow. Percentage profit earned by three shopkeepers in six different years are given in the line diagram below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter3%20-%202%20-%20Ex2/233.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which of the following statement is definitely true?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The amount of profit earned by shopkeeper B in the year 2010 and 2011 are the same.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Shopkeeper A earned the highest amount of the profit in 2010.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The amount of profit earned by shopkeeper A and C are the same in 2012.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these.&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;None of these statements will always be true because we do not have the details. e.g. if the expenditure for B in both the years are same, then the profit is not same and so, in this case, the statement &amp;lsquo;The amount of profit earned by shopkeeper B in the year 2010 and 2011 are the same&amp;rsquo; is wrong. e.g. if his expense in 2010 is the same as the expense in 2011, then the statement &amp;lsquo;Shopkeeper A earned the highest amount of the profit in 2010&amp;rsquo; is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1223,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of expenditure to income of three companies A, B and C during the period 2008&amp;ndash;2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which of the following years is the percentage loss/profit of Company C the maximum?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2014&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2009&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The percentage profit will be highest when the expenditure to income ratio is the lowest. So, the year required is 2014.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1224,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of expenditure to income of three companies A, B and C during the period 2008&amp;ndash;2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the expenditure of Company A in 2008 and 2009 together is Rs 60 lakhs, then what is its income in2008 and 2009 together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 120 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 150 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs 66.66 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data inadequate&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;We do not know the year wise breakup and so, we cannot determine the income. Data is inadequate here. If the expenditures are 30 lakh and 30 lakh, then the incomes will be 30/0.4 = 75 lakh and 30/0.6 = 50 lakh respectively. If the expenditures are 40 lakh and 20 lakh, then the incomes will be 40/0.4 = 100 lakh and 20/0.6 = 33.33 lakh respectively.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1225,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of expenditure to income of three companies A, B and C during the period 2008&amp;ndash;2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the expenditure of Company B in 2009 and 2012 together is Rs 60 lakhs then what is its income in 2008 and 2012 together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 66.66 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 100 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 36 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Data inadequate&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since the expenditure to income ratio is the same in both the years, we can calculate the income. The total income will be 60/0.6 = Rs. 100 lakhs.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1226,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of expenditure to income of three companies A, B and C during the period 2008&amp;ndash;2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which of the years does Company C gain 100% profit?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2013&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2009&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2010&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2011&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The profit percentage will be 100%, if the expenditure to income ratio is 0.5. So, the year required is 2011.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1227,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Following line graph shows the ratio of expenditure to income of three companies A, B and C during the period 2008&amp;ndash;2013.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.1.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage decrease in the percentage profit of Company C from 2009 to 2010?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;125%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;62.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;In 2009, the expenditure to income ratio is 0.8. So, for a Rs. 80 investment, the profit earned will be Rs. 20. So, the profit percentage is 20/80 x 100% = 25%. In 2010, the expenditure to income ratio is 0.4. So, for a Rs. 40 investment, the profit earned will be Rs. 60. So, the profit percentage is 60/40 x 100% = 150%. So, the change in percentage is 150 &amp;ndash; 25 = 125%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1228,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar chart shows the production of computers (in thousands) by six different companies during the year 2012 and 2013, and the line chart shows the percentage sales of these companies during the two years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage rise in production of company C from year 2012 to 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.4%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15.3%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14.7%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The production for C increases from 134,000 to 156,000 computers from the year 2012 to 2013. So, the percentage increase is [156 &amp;ndash; 134]/134 x 100% = 22/134 x 100% = 16.4%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1229,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar chart shows the production of computers (in thousands) by six different companies during the year 2012 and 2013, and the line chart shows the percentage sales of these companies during the two years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the number of computers that the company E sell in years 2012 and 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;22300&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;22400&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23300&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;The company produced 105,000 computers and then sold 58% of those mobiles. So, it has sold 105,000 x 58/100 = 1050 x 58 = 60900 computers in 2013. The company produced 130,000 computers and then sold 64% of those mobiles. So, it has sold 130,000 x 64/100 = 1300 x 64 = 83200 computers in 2013. So, the required difference is 83200 &amp;ndash; 60900 = 22300.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1230,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar chart shows the production of computers (in thousands) by six different companies during the year 2012 and 2013, and the line chart shows the percentage sales of these companies during the two years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of phone sold by A in year 2012 and 2013 together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;126840&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;128640&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;128460&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;128840&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The company produced 120,000 computers and then sold 52% of those mobiles. So, it has sold 120,000 x 52/100 = 1200 x 52 = 62400 computers in 2013. The company produced 138,000 computers and then sold 48% of those mobiles. So, it has sold 138,000 x 48/100 = 1380 x 48 = 66240 computers in 2013. So, total number of computers sold by company A is 62400 + 66240 = 128640 computers.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1231,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar chart shows the production of computers (in thousands) by six different companies during the year 2012 and 2013, and the line chart shows the percentage sales of these companies during the two years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the average percentage of sales for all the companies during 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;56.5%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;55%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;55.6%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;56%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Total production during 2013 is 138 + 132 + 156 + 112 + 130 + 158 = 826 thousand. Total amount sold is (138 x 48/100) + (132 x 60/100) + (156 x 56/100) + (112 x 52/100) + (130 x 64/100) + (158 x 54/100) = 66.24 + 79.20 + 87.36 + 58.24 + 83.20 + 85.32 = 459.56 thousand. So, the average percentage of sales is 459.56/826 x 100% = 55.636%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1232,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Following bar chart shows the production of computers (in thousands) by six different companies during the year 2012 and 2013, and the line chart shows the percentage sales of these companies during the two years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.2.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between total sale of F in 2012 and total sale of B in 2013?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2310&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2340&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2350&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2320&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Total sale of F in 2012 is 62/100 x 124 thousand = 76,880 computers. Total sale of B in 2013 is 60/100 x 132 thousand = 79,200 computers. So, the difference in the sales is 79,200 &amp;ndash; 76,880 = 2320 computers.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1233,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Read the line graph carefully to answer the questions below. The line graph gives the number of students that are hired by each of the four companies for each of its locations.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the total number of students hired by RRB for all centers?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2300&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2350&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2450&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2400&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of students hired by RRB in all the centers is 500 + 250 + 550 + 300 + 700 = 2300.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1234,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Read the line graph carefully to answer the questions below. The line graph gives the number of students that are hired by each of the four companies for each of its locations.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Total no. of students hired by all the companies for Bangalore center is?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1650&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1750&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1600&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1700&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Total number of students hired by all the companies in Bangalore center is 500 + 550 + 250 + 350 = 1650.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1235,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: Read the line graph carefully to answer the questions below. The line graph gives the number of students that are hired by each of the four companies for each of its locations.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference betwe