00 + 650 + 400 = 2250. Total number of students hired by RRB in all the centers is 500 + 250 + 550 + 300 + 700 = 2300. Total number of students hired by DRDO in all the centers is 300 + 450 + 250 + 500 + 650 = 2150. Total number of students hired by BHEL for all its centers is 200 + 400 + 350 + 700 + 450 = 2100. So, RRB hires the maximum number of students.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1238,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: The following questions are based on the diagram given below. The line graph gives the average speed of 3 different cars on 5 different days and the table gives us the time that they have spent travelling in each of these days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.4.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;347&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of distance travelled by Q on day 2 and R on day 4 and P on day 5?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 6 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2 : 3 : 6&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 6 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 : 12 : 15&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Distance travelled by Q on day 2 is 15 x 8 = 120 km. Distance travelled by R on day 4 is 30 x 12 = 360 km. Distance travelled by P on day 5 is 18 x 10 = 180 km. So, the required ratio is 120: 360: 180 = 2: 6: 3.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1239,12,'3','&lt;p&gt;Direction: The following questions are based on the diagram given below. The line graph gives the average speed of 3 different cars on 5 different days and the table gives us the time that they have spent travelling in each of these days.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%203-%20Ex3/234.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;576&quot; height=&quot;336&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapte