45 = 22 : 29.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1253,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following line graph gives the number of passengers (in thousands) travelling by different airlines A, B, C, D and E in three months January, February and March.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;467&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the respective ratio of the total number of passengers travelling by Airline B to that of Airline E during three months?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15 : 7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17 : 19&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;29 : 31&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23 : 25&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;The required ratio is (40 + 45 + 60) : (40 + 50 + 65) = 145 : 155 = 29: 31.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1254,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following line graph gives the number of passengers (in thousands) travelling by different airlines A, B, C, D and E in three months January, February and March.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.3.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;556&quot; height=&quot;467&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which of the following Airlines has the highest number of passengers during three months?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;A&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;E&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;C&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;D&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;A has the highest number (175,000) of passengers.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1255,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions accordingly. Following line graph gives the number of passengers (in thousands) travelling by different airlines A, B, C, D and E in three months January, February and March.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.3.1.j