-Expenditure)/Expenditure &amp;times; 100%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;557&quot; height=&quot;437&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the approximate average percent profit earned by company X over all the years together?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;57&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;36&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;45&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;53&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Average profit percentage earned is (40 + 45 + 35 + 47.5 + 50+55)/6 = 272.5/6 = 45.5.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1261,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions: Percent profit earned by two companies over the years Percent Profit = (Income-Expenditure)/Expenditure &amp;times; 100%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;557&quot; height=&quot;437&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If in the year 2009 incomes of both the companies X and Y were the same, what was the respective ratio of their expenditures in that year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7 : 5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16 : 15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23 : 211&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;None of these&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Since the profits are 50% and 60% respectively and the expenditures are E1 and E2, and the incomes are I1 and I2, then I1 = 1.5E1 and I2 = 1.6E2. But I1 = I2 =&amp;gt; E1 : E2 = 16 : 15.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1262,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions: Percent profit earned by two companies over the years Percent Profit = (Income-Expenditure)/Expenditure &amp;times; 100%.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.4.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;557&quot; height=&quot;437&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the percentage increase in percent profit of company Y in the year 2008 from the previous year? (rounded off to two digits after decimal)&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;17.65&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;19.25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16.55&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15.75&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Required percentage = (50 - 42.5)/42.5 &amp;times; 100 =17.65%.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(1263,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of trees planted by three different NGOs in five different States.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;In which state was the total number of trees planted by NGO-A and NGO-B together second lowest?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Bihar&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Punjab&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Haryana&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Assam&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Number of trees planted by NGO-A and NGO-B together: Bihar =&amp;gt; 100 + 60 = 160, Punjab =&amp;gt; 120 + 80 = 200, Haryana =&amp;gt; 140 + 80 = 220, Assam =&amp;gt; 160 +150 = 310, Tamil Nadu =&amp;gt; 180 + 140 = 320. So, it is second lowest in Punjab.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1264,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of trees planted by three different NGOs in five different States.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.5.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What was the difference between the trees planted by NGO-A in Haryana and the number of trees planted by NGO-C in Tamil Nadu?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;90&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;80&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;120&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;100&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Required difference = 160 &amp;minus; 80 = 80.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1265,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully to answer the questions that follow: Number of trees planted by