ph carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which of the following is the highest difference in production between two adjacent years?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;9 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&amp;middot;5 lakhs&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Directly obtained by the graph.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1291,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following graph carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.10.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Which year had the highest per cent increase in production over the previous year?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1999&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;2002&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1997&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Per cent increase in 1999 = [17.5 &amp;ndash; 10]/10 &amp;times; 100 = 75%. Per cent increase in 2000 = [25 &amp;ndash; 17.5]/17.5 &amp;times; 100 = 42.86%. =&amp;gt; In 1999, It is the highest.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1292,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following Graph carefully and answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The population of the state &amp;lsquo;Q&amp;rsquo; in the year of 1999 was what per cent of its population in the year of 2000?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;66.67%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;47.33%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;130%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;37%&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Let the population of the state &amp;lsquo;Q&amp;rsquo; in 1999 = 100. &amp;there4; Population in 2000 = 150. &amp;there4; The required % = 100/150 &amp;times; 100 = 66 2/3%.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1293,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following Graph carefully and answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The population of the state &amp;lsquo;O&amp;rsquo; in the year of 1998 was 8 lakh, then what was its approximate population in the year of 2000?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;24 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;26 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;14 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;23 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The population of the state &amp;lsquo;O&amp;rsquo; in the year of 2000 = 8 &amp;times; 180/100 &amp;times; 160/100 = 23 lakh.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1294,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following Graph carefully and answer the questions that follow&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%203%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/235.11.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;482&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If the population of the states &amp;lsquo;M&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;R&amp;rsquo; in 1998 are in the ratio 3 : 2 and the population of the state &amp;lsquo;M&amp;rsquo; in 1999 was 126 lakh, then what was the population of the state &amp;lsquo;R&amp;rsquo; in 2000?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;70 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;93.60 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;152 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;65 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Let the population of the states &amp;lsquo;M&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;R&amp;rsquo; in 1998 be 3y and 2y respectively. &amp;there4; 3y &amp;times; 140/100 =126 &amp;rArr; x= 30. &amp;there4;Population of the state &amp;lsquo;R&amp;rsquo; in 1998 = 30 &amp;times; 2 = 60 lakh and in 2000 = 60 &amp;times;1.3 &amp;times;1.2 = 93.60 lakh&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1295,12,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following Graph carefully and answer the questions that follow&