ese&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;The required ratio = 14% of 3800 : 17% of 4200 = 38 : 51.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1435,13,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following diagram carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;481&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.12.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;481&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;If in a given year, 1&amp;sbquo;00&amp;sbquo;000 tourists visited India and the age-wise distribution data applies to all countries, the number of American tourists who visited India during the year and are in the age group of 20-40 years is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;20&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&amp;sbquo;000&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of Americans who visited India = 60% of 1,00,000 = 60,000. Number of Americans in the age group of 20 &amp;ndash; 40 years who visited India = 20% of 60,000 = 12,000&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1436,13,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: Study the following diagram carefully and answer the questions that follow.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;481&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.12.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;481&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;With the same data given in the previous question, what would be the number of Russian tourists who are below 20 years of age?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3000&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;300&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;330&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3500&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;No. of Russian Tourists = 5