04%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.12.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;481&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.12.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;481&quot; height=&quot;289&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the ratio of British tourists below 20 years to the Russian tourists above 40 years ?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;1 : 2&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12 : 1&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;3 : 4&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;4 : 3&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Ratio of British tourists below 20 years and Russian tourists above 40 years = 60% of 20&amp;sbquo;000 : 20% of 5000 = 12&amp;sbquo;000 : 1000 = 12 : 1.&lt;/p&gt;','Hard'),(1440,13,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: In a junior college, the total number of students is 2500. The percentage of students studying in different streams is shown in the given pie-chart and the ratio of boys to girls in each stream is given in the table. Answer the following questions based on the given information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;617&quot; height=&quot;322&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;383&quot; height=&quot;140&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the total number of boys and the total number of girls studying in the college?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;65&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;Number of boys in MPC branch is 2/3 x 21/100 x 2500 = 350.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of boys in PCB branch is 1/6 x 24/100 x 2500 = 100.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of boys in CEC branch is 3/5 x 15/100 x 2500 = 225.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of boys in MEC branch is 3/7 x 14/100 x 2500 = 150.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of boys in HEC branch is 5/9 x 18/100 x 2500 = 250.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Number of boys in PCMB branch is 3/4 x 8/100 x 2500 = 150.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of boys in the college is 350 + 100 + 225 + 150 + 250 + 150 = 1225.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Total number of girls in the college is 2500 &amp;ndash; 1225 = 1275.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the required difference is 50.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1441,13,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: In a junior college, the total number of students is 2500. The percentage of students studying in different streams is shown in the given pie-chart and the ratio of boys to girls in each stream is given in the table. Answer the following questions based on the given information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;617&quot; height=&quot;322&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;383&quot; height=&quot;140&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of girls studying in CEC is approximately what per cent of the total number of students in the same branch?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;60%&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Ratio of the number of girls to boys in CEC branch is 2: 3. So, the required ratio is 2/5 x 100 = 40%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1442,13,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: In a junior college, the total number of students is 2500. The percentage of students studying in different streams is shown in the given pie-chart and the ratio of boys to girls in each stream is given in the table. Answer the following questions based on the given information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;617&quot; height=&quot;322&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;383&quot; height=&quot;140&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the number of boys studying CEC and the number of girls studying MEC in the college?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;50&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;40&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of boys studying CEC is 15/100 x 3/5 x 2500 = 225. Number of girls studying MEC is 4/7 x 14/100 x 2500 = 200. So, the required difference is 225 &amp;ndash; 200 = 25.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1443,13,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: In a junior college, the total number of students is 2500. The percentage of students studying in different streams is shown in the given pie-chart and the ratio of boys to girls in each stream is given in the table. Answer the following questions based on the given information.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;617&quot; height=&quot;322&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/DI%20-%20Chapter%204%20-%204%20-%20DPPS/245.13.2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;383&quot; height=&quot;140&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;The number of boys studying PCMB is what per cent more than the number of girls studying in the same branch?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;150%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;200%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;180%&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;175%&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The ratio of the boys and girls studying in PCMB is 3: 1. So, the required percentage is [3 &amp;ndash; 1]/1 x 100% = 200%.&lt;/p&gt;','Medium'),(1444,13,'4','&lt;p&gt;Directions: In a junior college, the total number of students is 2500. The percentage of students studying in different streams is shown in the given pie-chart and the ratio of boys to girls in each stream is given in the table. Answer the following questions based on the given information.