gt;&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(2120,20,'1','&lt;p&gt;The Venn diagram shown below gives the number of students passing in each subject among three subjects Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry. Total number of students appearing for the examinations is 68.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/reasoning/312.11-15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;370&quot; height=&quot;185&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Answer the questions that follow using this information.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many students passed in both Physics and Mathematics but not Chemistry?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;7&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;12&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;Number of students who passed in both Physics and Mathematics but not Chemistry is given by the intersection region of Physics and Mathematics Sections but should not include the Chemistry students. Number of such students is 7.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(2121,20,'1','&lt;p&gt;The Venn diagram shown below gives the number of students passing in each subject among three subjects Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry. Total number of students appearing for the examinations is 68.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;tinymce/uploaded/reasoning/312.11-15.1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;370&quot; height=&quot;185&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Answer the questions that follow using this information.&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;How many students passed both Physics and Chemistry?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;10&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;15&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;8&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;We can include all the students who passed in Chemistry or Physics irrespective of whether they passed in Mathematics or not. So, number of such students required is 10 + 5 = 15.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(2122,20,'1','&lt;p&gt;The Venn diagram shown below gives the number of students passing in each subject among three subjects Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry. Total number of students appearing for