insert  into `rs_quotes_5082015`(`id`,`quote`,`author`) values (1,'Failure will never overtake me if my determination to succeed is strong enough.','Og Mandino'),(2,'I have always tried to go a step past wherever people expected me to end up.','Beverly Sills'),(3,'Always do your best. What you plant now, you will harvest later.','Og Mandino'),(4,'In order to succeed, we must first believe that we can.','Nikos Kazantzakis'),(5,'It does not matter how slowly you go as long as you do not stop.','Confucius'),(6,'You have to learn the rules of the game. And then you have to play better than anyone else.','Albert Einstein'),(7,'Things do not happen. Things are made to happen.','John F. Kennedy'),(8,'With the new day comes new strength and new thoughts.','Eleanor Roosevelt'),(9,'You are never too old to set another goal or dream a new dream.','C.S.Lewis'),(10,'If you can dream it, you can do it.','Walt Disney'),(11,'Do not watch the clock. Do what it does. Keep going.','Sam Levenson'),(12,'Our great weakness lies in giving up. The most certain way to succeed is always try one more time.\r\n','Thomas. A. Edison\r\n'),(13,'Keep your eyes on the stars and your feet on the ground.\r\n','Theodore Roosevelt\r\n'),(14,'The secret of getting ahead is getting started.\r\n','Mark Twain\r\n'),(15,'A creative man is motivated by the desire to achieve, not by the desire to beat others.\r\n','Ayn Rand\r\n'),(16,'The will to win, the desire to succeed, the urge to reach your full potential... these are the keys that will unlock the door to personal excellence.\n','Confucius\r\n'),(17,'We may encounter many defeats but we must not be defeated.\n','Mary Angelou\r\n'),(18,'Start where you are. Use what you have. Do what you can.\n','Arthur Ashe\r\n'),(19,'Believe in yourself! Have faith in your abilities! Without a humble but reasonable confidence in your own powers you cannot be successful or happy.\r\n','Norman Vincent Peale\r\n'),(20,'Expect problems and eat them for breakfast.\r\n','Alfred A. Montapert\r\n'),(21,'There is only one corner of the universe you can be certain of improving, and that\'s your own self.\r\n','Aldous Huxley\r\n'),(22,'Optimism is the faith that leads to achievement. Nothing can be done without hope and confidence.\r\n','Hellen Keller\r\n'),(23,'Problems are not stop signs, they are guidelines.\n','Robert H. Schuller\r\n'),(24,'Either I will find a way, or I will make one.\r\n','Philip Sidney\r\n'),(25,'Ever tried. Ever failed. No matter. Try Again. Fail again. Fail better.\r\n','Samuel Beckett\r\n'),(26,'Do the difficult things while they are easy and do the great things while they are small. A journey of a thousand miles must begin with a single step.\r\n','Lao Tzu\r\n'),(27,'Be kind whenever possible. It is always possible.\r\n','Dalai Lama\r\n'),(28,'What you do today can improve all your tomorrows.\r\n','Ralph Marston\r\n'),(29,'From my tribe I take nothing, I am the maker of my own fortune.\r\n','Tecumseh\r\n'),(30,'Without hard work, nothing grows but weeds.\r\n','Gordon B. Hinckley\r\n'),(31,'Never give up, for that is just the place and time that the tide will turn.\r\n','Harriet Beecher Stowe\r\n'),(32,'Do you want to know who you are? Don\'t ask. Act! Action will delineate and define you.\r\n','Thomas Jefferson\r\n'),(33,'If you don\'t like something, change it. If you can\'t change it, change your attitude. Don\'t complain.\r\n','Maya Angelou\r\n'),(34,'By failing to prepare, you are preparing to fail.\r\n','Benjamin Franklin\r\n'),(35,'The key is to keep company only with people who uplift you, whose presence calls forth your best.\r\n','Epictetus\r\n'),(36,'Quality is not an act, it is a habit.\r\n','Aristotle\r\n'),(37,'Consult not your fears but your hopes and your dreams. Think not about your frustrations, but about your unfulfilled potential. Concern yourself not with what you tried and failed in, but with what it is still possible for you to do.\r\n','Pope John XXIII\r\n'),(38,'Perseverance is failing 19 times and succeeding the 20th.\r\n','Julie Andrews\r\n'),(39,'I know where I\'m going and I know the truth, and I don\'t have to be what you want me to be. I\'m free to be what I want.\r\n','Muhammad Ali\r\n'),(40,'You are not here merely to make a living. You are here in order to enable the world to live more amply, with greater vision, with a finer spirit of hope and achievement. You are here to enrich the world, and you impoverish yourself if you forget the errand.\r\n','Woodrow Wilson\r\n'),(41,'If you\'re going through hell, keep going.\r\n','Winston Churchill\r\n'),(42,'Even if you fall on your face, you\'re still moving forward.\r\n','Victor Kiam\r\n'),(43,'Setting goals is the first step in turning the invisible into the visible.\r\n','Tony Robbins\r\n'),(44,'Accept the challenges so that you can feel the exhilaration of victory.\r\n','George S. Patton\r\n'),(45,'There is no passion to be found playing small - in settling for a life that is less than the one you are capable of living.\r\n','Nelson Mandela\r\n'),(46,'There\'s a way to do it better - find it.\r\n','Thomas A. Edison\r\n'),(47,'If you don\'t design your own life plan, chances are you\'ll fall into someone else\'s plan. And guess what they have planned for you? Not much.\r\n','Jim Rohn\r\n'),(48,'Pursue one great decisive aim with force and determination.\r\n','Carl von Clausewitz\r\n'),(49,'Be Impeccable With Your Word. Speak with integrity. Say only what you mean. Avoid using the word to speak against yourself or to gossip about others. Use the power of your word in the direction of truth and love.\r\n','Miguel Angel Ruiz\r\n'),(50,'No bird soars too high if he soars with his own wings.\r\n','William Blake\r\n'),(51,'Motivation will almost always beat mere talent.\r\n','Norman Ralph Augustine\r\n'),(52,'Change your life today. Don\'t gamble on the future, act now, without delay.\r\n','Simone de Beauvoir\r\n'),(53,'I learned that we can do anything, but we can\'t do everything... at least not at the same time. So think of your priorities not in terms of what activities you do, but when you do them. Timing is everything.\r\n','Dan Millman\r\n'),(54,'We are taught you must blame your father, your sisters, your brothers, the school, the teachers - but never blame yourself. It\'s never your fault. But it\'s always your fault, because if you wanted to change you\'re the one who has got to change.\r\n','Katharine Hepburn\r\n'),(55,'After a storm comes a calm.\r\n','Matthew Henry\r\n'),(56,'Do not wait to strike till the iron is hot; but make it hot by striking.\r\n','William Butler Yeats\r\n'),(57,'Never, never, never give up.\r\n','Winston Churchill\r\n'),(58,'Be gentle to all and stern with yourself.\r\n','Saint Teresa of Avila\r\n'),(59,'Aim for the moon. If you miss, you may hit a star.\r\n','W. Clement Stone\r\n'),(60,'Knowing is not enough; we must apply. Willing is not enough; we must do.\r\n','Johann Wolfgang von Goethe\r\n'),(61,'Set your goals high, and don\'t stop till you get there.\r\n','Bo Jackson\r\n'),(62,'Motivation is the art of getting people to do what you want them to do because they want to do it.\r\n','Dwight D. Eisenhower\r\n'),(63,'You simply have to put one foot in front of the other and keep going. Put blinders on and plow right ahead.\r\n','George Lucas\r\n'),(64,'Do something wonderful, people may imitate it.\r\n','Albert Schweitzer\r\n'),(65,'Perseverance is not a long race; it is many short races one after the other.\r\n','Walter Elliot\r\n'),(66,'I don\'t believe you have to be better than everybody else. I believe you have to be better than you ever thought you could be.\r\n','Ken Venturi\r\n'),(67,'Don\'t give up. Don\'t lose hope. Don\'t sell out.\r\n','Christopher Reeve\r\n'),(68,'Don\'t fight the problem, decide it.\r\n','George C. Marshall\r\n'),(69,'Good, better, best. Never let it rest. \'Til your good is better and your better is best.\r\n','St. Jerome\r\n'),(70,'When something is important enough, you do it even if the odds are not in your favor.\r\n','Elon Musk\r\n'),(71,'The more we do, the more we can do.\r\n','William Hazlitt\r\n'),(72,'One finds limits by pushing them.\r\n','Herbert Simon\r\n'),(73,'I attribute my success to this - I never gave or took any excuse.\r\n','Florence Nightingale\r\n'),(74,'Do the one thing you think you cannot do. Fail at it. Try again. Do better the second time. The only people who never tumble are those who never mount the high wire. This is your moment. Own it.\r\n','Oprah Winfrey\r\n'),(75,'Step by step and the thing is done.\r\n','Charles Atlas\r\n'),(76,'There is always room at the top.\r\n','Daniel Webster\r\n'),(77,'The harder the conflict, the more glorious the triumph.\r\n','Thomas Paine\r\n'),(78,'I\'ve worked too hard and too long to let anything stand in the way of my goals. I will not let my teammates down and I will not let myself down.\r\n','Mia Hamm\r\n'),(79,'Do not wait; the time will never be \'just right.\' Start where you stand, and work with whatever tools you may have at your command, and better tools will be found as you go along.\r\n','George Herbert\r\n'),(80,'Well done is better than well said.\r\n','Benjamin Franklin\r\n'),(81,'True happiness involves the full use of one\'s power and talents.\r\n','John W. Gardner\r\n'),(82,'The past cannot be changed. The future is yet in your power.\r\n','Mary Pickford\r\n'),(83,'The first step toward success is taken when you refuse to be a captive of the environment in which you first find yourself.\r\n','Mark Caine\r\n'),(84,'The will to succeed is important, but what\'s more important is the will to prepare.\r\n','Bobby Knight\r\n'),(85,'The more man meditates upon good thoughts, the better will be his world and the world at large.\r\n','Confucius\r\n'),(86,'I really believe that everyone has a talent, ability, or skill that he can mine to support himself and to succeed in life.\r\n','Dean Koontz\r\n'),(87,'Big shots are only little shots who keep shooting.\r\n','Christopher Morley\r\n'),(88,'Whatever you want in life, other people are going to want it too. Believe in yourself enough to accept the idea that you have an equal right to it.\r\n','Diane Sawyer\r\n'),(89,'Who seeks shall find.\r\n','Sophocles\r\n'),(90,'Learning is the beginning of wealth. Learning is the beginning of health. Learning is the beginning of spirituality. Searching and learning is where the miracle process all begins.\r\n','Jim Rohn\r\n'),(91,'Be miserable. Or motivate yourself. Whatever has to be done, it\'s always your choice.\r\n','Wayne Dyer\r\n'),(92,'A will finds a way.\r\n','Orison Swett Marden\r\n'),(93,'If you fell down yesterday, stand up today.\r\n','H. G. Wells\r\n'),(94,'You can never quit. Winners never quit, and quitters never win.\r\n','Ted Turner\r\n'),(95,'Know or listen to those who know.\r\n','Baltasar Gracian\r\n'),(96,'A goal is a dream with a deadline.\r\n','Napoleon Hill\r\n'),(97,'You can\'t build a reputation on what you are going to do.\r\n','Henry Ford\r\n'),(98,'Act as if what you do makes a difference. It does.\r\n','William James\r\n'),(99,'Set your sights high, the higher the better. Expect the most wonderful things to happen, not in the future but right now. Realize that nothing is too good. Allow absolutely nothing to hamper you or hold you up in any way.\r\n','Eileen Caddy\r\n'),(100,'March on. Do not tarry. To go forward is to move toward perfection. March on, and fear not the thorns, or the sharp stones on life\'s path.\r\n','Khalil Gibran\r\n'),(101,'You must take action now that will move you towards your goals. Develop a sense of urgency in your life.\r\n','H. Jackson Brown, Jr.\r\n'),(102,'If you want to succeed you should strike out on new paths, rather than travel the worn paths of accepted success.\r\n','John D. Rockefeller\r\n'),(103,'Small deeds done are better than great deeds planned.\r\n','Peter Marshall\r\n'),(104,'You just can\'t beat the person who never gives up.\r\n','Babe Ruth\r\n'),(105,'Do whatever you do intensely.\r\n','Robert Henri\r\n'),(106,'Determine never to be idle. No person will have occasion to complain of the want of time who never loses any. It is wonderful how much may be done if we are always doing.\r\n','Thomas Jefferson\r\n'),(107,'I\'ve found that luck is quite predictable. If you want more luck, take more chances. Be more active. Show up more often.\r\n','Brian Tracy\r\n'),(108,'The most effective way to do it, is to do it.\r\n','Amelia Earhart\r\n'),(109,'I know not age, nor weariness nor defeat.\r\n','Rose Kennedy\r\n'),(110,'Either you run the day or the day runs you.\r\n','Jim Rohn\r\n'),(111,'Opportunity does not knock, it presents itself when you beat down the door.\r\n','Kyle Chandler\r\n'),(112,'If you ask me what I came into this life to do, I will tell you: I came to live out loud.\r\n','Emile Zola\r\n'),(113,'Learn from the past, set vivid, detailed goals for the future, and live in the only moment of time over which you have any control: now.\r\n','Denis Waitley\r\n'),(114,'I am not afraid... I was born to do this.\r\n','Joan of Arc\r\n'),(115,'Do your work with your whole heart, and you will succeed - there\'s so little competition.\r\n','Elbert Hubbard\r\n'),(116,'The ultimate aim of the ego is not to see something, but to be something.\r\n','Muhammad Iqbal\r\n'),(117,'It is very important to know who you are. To make decisions. To show who you are.\r\n','Malala Yousafzai\r\n'),(118,'Get action. Seize the moment. Man was never intended to become an oyster.\r\n','Theodore Roosevelt\r\n'),(119,'Decide what you want, decide what you are willing to exchange for it. Establish your priorities and go to work.\r\n','H. L. Hunt\r\n'),(120,'You create your opportunities by asking for them.\r\n','Shakti Gawain\r\n'),(121,'Every exit is an entry somewhere else.\r\n','Tom Stoppard\r\n'),(122,'To be a good loser is to learn how to win.\r\n','Carl Sandburg\r\n'),(123,'I\'d rather attempt to do something great and fail than to attempt to do nothing and succeed.\r\n','Robert H. Schuller\r\n'),(124,'I think people who are creative are the luckiest people on earth. I know that there are no shortcuts, but you must keep your faith in something Greater than You, and keep doing what you love. Do what you love, and you will find the way to get it out to the world.\r\n','Judy Collins\r\n'),(125,'One way to keep momentum going is to have constantly greater goals.\r\n','Michael Korda\r\n'),(126,'It\'s always too early to quit.\r\n','Norman Vincent Peale\r\n'),(127,'A somebody was once a nobody who wanted to and did.\r\n','John Burroughs\r\n'),(128,'Follow your inner moonlight; don\'t hide the madness.\r\n','Allen Ginsberg\r\n'),(129,'The people who influence you are the people who believe in you.\r\n','Henry Drummond\r\n'),(130,'Go for it now. The future is promised to no one.\r\n','Wayne Dyer\r\n'),(131,'Always continue the climb. It is possible for you to do whatever you choose, if you first get to know who you are and are willing to work with a power that is greater than ourselves to do it.\r\n','Ella Wheeler Wilcox\r\n'),(132,'No matter how many goals you have achieved, you must set your sights on a higher one.\r\n','Jessica Savitch\r\n'),(133,'Where there is a will, there is a way. If there is a chance in a million that you can do something, anything, to keep what you want from ending, do it. Pry the door open or, if need be, wedge your foot in that door and keep it open.\r\n','Pauline Kael\r\n'),(134,'In motivating people, you\'ve got to engage their minds and their hearts. I motivate people, I hope, by example - and perhaps by excitement, by having productive ideas to make others feel involved.\r\n','Rupert Murdoch\r\n'),(135,'We aim above the mark to hit the mark.\r\n','Ralph Waldo Emerson\r\n'),(136,'You have to make it happen.\r\n','Denis Diderot\r\n'),(137,'Press forward. Do not stop, do not linger in your journey, but strive for the mark set before you.\r\n','George Whitefield\r\n'),(138,'If you don\'t like how things are, change it! You\'re not a tree.\r\n','Jim Rohn\r\n'),(139,'The more things you do, the more you can do.\r\n','Lucille Ball\r\n'),(140,'Never complain and never explain.\r\n','Benjamin Disraeli\r\n'),(141,'If you want to conquer fear, don\'t sit home and think about it. Go out and get busy.\r\n','Dale Carnegie\r\n'),(142,'There is nothing deep down inside us except what we have put there ourselves.\r\n','Richard Rorty\r\n'),(143,'Wherever you are - be all there.\r\n','Jim Elliot\r\n'),(144,'Crave for a thing, you will get it. Renounce the craving, the object will follow you by itself.\r\n','Swami Sivananda\r\n'),(145,'I was motivated to be different in part because I was different.\r\n','Donna Brazile\r\n'),(146,'When one must, one can.\r\n','Charlotte Whitton\r\n'),(147,'The hardships that I encountered in the past will help me succeed in the future.\r\n','Philip Emeagwali\r\n'),(148,'Only I can change my life. No one can do it for me.\r\n','Carol Burnett'),(149,'\r\nWhen you fail you learn from the mistakes you made and it motivates you to work even harder.\r\n','Natalie Gulbis\r\n'),(150,'Poverty was the greatest motivating factor in my life.\r\n','Jimmy Dean\r\n'),(151,'You need to overcome the tug of people against you as you reach for high goals.\r\n','George S. Patton\r\n'),(152,'If you think you can do it, you can.\r\n','John Burroughs\r\n'),(153,'The turning point was when I hit my 30th birthday. I thought, if really want to write, it\'s time to start. I picked up the book How to Write a Novel in 90 Days. The author said to just write three pages a day, and I figured, I can do this. I never got past Page 3 of that book.\r\n','James Rollins\r\n'),(154,'Set yourself earnestly to see what you are made to do, and then set yourself earnestly to do it.\r\n','Phillips Brooks\r\n'),(155,'You can\'t expect to hit the jackpot if you don\'t put a few nickels in the machine.\r\n','Flip Wilson\r\n'),(156,'Hitch your wagon to a star.\r\n','Ralph Waldo Emerson\r\n'),(157,'Always desire to learn something useful.\r\n','Sophocles\r\n'),(158,'They can conquer who believe they can.\r\n','Virgil\r\n'),(159,'Never give in and never give up.\r\n','Hubert H. Humphrey\r\n'),(160,'Be thine own palace, or the world\'s thy jail.\r\n','John Donne\r\n'),(161,'How do you know you\'re going to do something, untill you do it?\r\n','J. D. Salinger\r\n'),(162,'Deserve your dream.\r\n','Octavio Paz\r\n'),(163,'Begin to be now what you will be hereafter.\r\n','William James\r\n'),(164,'God always strives together with those who strive.\r\n','Aeschylus\r\n'),(165,'You can\'t wait for inspiration. You have to go after it with a club.\r\n','Jack London\r\n'),(166,'Only the educated are free.\r\n','Epictetus\r\n'),(167,'Either move or be moved.\r\n','Ezra Pound\r\n'),(168,'Never retreat. Never explain. Get it done and let them howl.\r\n','Benjamin Jowett\r\n'),(169,'To begin, begin.\r\n','William Wordsworth\r\n'),(170,'Your heaviest artillery will be your will to live. Keep that big gun going.\r\n','Norman Cousins\r\n'),(171,'To know oneself, one should assert oneself.\r\n','Albert Camus\r\n'),(172,'I am not a has-been. I am a will be.\r\n','Lauren Bacall\r\n'),(173,'The weeds keep multiplying in our garden, which is our mind ruled by fear. Rip them out and call them by name.\r\n','Sylvia Browne\r\n'),(174,'Go big or go home. Because it\'s true. What do you have to lose?\r\n','Eliza Dushku\r\n'),(175,'I can, therefore I am.\r\n','Simone Weil\r\n'),(176,'If you don\'t ask, you don\'t get.\r\n','Stevie Wonder\r\n'),(177,'We make the world we live in and shape our own environment.\r\n','Orison Swett Marden\r\n'),(178,'Leap, and the net will appear.\r\n','John Burroughs\r\n');

