insert  into `sundar_23`(`id`,`topic_id`,`q_type`,`Introduction`,`Question`,`Op1`,`Op2`,`Op3`,`Op4`,`Answer`,`Solution`,`Difficulty_level`) values (1,23,'1','','&lt;p&gt;How many integers n, where 100 &amp;lt; n &amp;lt; 200, are divisible neither by seven nor by eleven?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;75&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;76&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;77&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;78&lt;/p&gt;','4','&lt;p&gt;Integers between 100 and 200 that are divisible by 7 are 105, 112, 119 &amp;hellip; 196. There are 13 numbers.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Integers between 100 and 200 that are divisible by 9 are 110, 121, 132 &amp;hellip; 198. There are 9 numbers.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Integers between 100 and 200 that are divisible by both 7 and 9 is 154. Only 1 number. So, total number of numbers divisible by either 7 or 9 is 13 + 9 &amp;ndash; 1 = 21.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, total number of numbers divisible neither by 9 or 7 is 99 &amp;ndash; 21 = 78.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(2,23,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The total number of factors of the number 3000 is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;31&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;30&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;16&lt;/p&gt;','2','&lt;p&gt;The prime factorization of 3000 is 3000=3&amp;times;2&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;times;5&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The number of factors of 3000 is (1+1)(3+1)(3+1)=2&amp;times;4&amp;times;4=32 because, for the number expressed in the form of x&lt;sup&gt;a&lt;/sup&gt;y&lt;sup&gt;b&lt;/sup&gt;z&lt;sup&gt;c&lt;/sup&gt; where x, y and z are prime numbers, the number of factors is (x+1)(y+1)(z+1).&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(3,23,'1','','Find the sum of the first 15 multiples of 13.','1365','1560','1460','1465','2','The sum of the first 15 multiples of 13 will be 13 + 26 + 39 + â€¦ + 195 = 13 x (1 + 2 + 3 + â€¦ + 15) = 13 x 15 x 16/2 = 13 x 120 = 1560.','Easy'),(4,23,'1','','Some money is collected by raising subscription for opening a society. If the whole amount collected is 300 currency notes of 1000 denomination and 400 currency notes of 500 denomination and if each person subscribed as many rupees as twice the number of subscribers, find the number of subscribers.','400','300','500','600','3','Let the number of subscribers be k. so, the total amount of money collected is k x 2k.\nSo, 2k x k = (300 x 1000) + (400 x 500) = 500000 =&gt; k = 500.','Easy'),(5,23,'1','','The smallest number which when added to 6, the sum is exactly divisible by 11, 13, 7 and 9 is','9003','9000','9006','9009','1','Let the smallest number required be k. so, (k + 6) is exactly divisible by 11, 13, 7 and 9.\nSo, (k + 6) must be the LCM of 11, 13, 7, 9.\nSo, (k + 6) = 11 x 13 x 7 x 9 = 9009 =&gt; k = 9003.','Easy'),(6,23,'1','','The smallest number, on being divided by 3, 4, 6, 10 and 16 leaves 9 as remainder in each case will be','240','249','489','729','2','The smallest number which on being divided by 3, 4, 6, 10 and 16 leaves a remainder 0 is the LCM of 3, 4, 6, 10, 16 which is 240.\nSo, the required number is 240 + 9 = 249.','Easy'),(7,23,'1','','When X is subtracted from the numbers 9, 15 and 27, the remainders are in continued proportion. What is the value of X?','5','6','4','3','4','Let X be the number that is to be subtracted from each number. \nSo, (9-x), (15-x) and (27-x) are in continued proportion and so (15-x)^2=(9-x)(27-x).\nSo, 225-30x=243-36x=&gt;6x=18=&gt;x=3.','Easy'),(8,23,'1','','The sum of all the odd numbers starting from 1 and ending up to the greatest number of three digits is','250000','25000','25,00,000','50000','1','The sum of first n odd numbers is equal to the square of n.\nIn this case, we are dealing with the first 500 odd numbers. So, the required sum is 500 x 500 = 250,000.','Easy'),(9,23,'1','','&lt;p&gt;Ravi saves one coin of Rs. 10 on first day of the month, three coins of Rs. 10 on the second day of the month, five coins of Rs. 10 on third day and so on. How much money will he have at the end of the month?&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 885&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 870&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 865&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;Rs. 820&lt;/p&gt;','1','&lt;p&gt;We can see that the series is an AP with the first term 1 and the common difference 2. So, the total savings will be S&lt;sub&gt;30&lt;/sub&gt;=(30/2) x [1+(29&amp;times;2)]=15&amp;times;59=Rs.885&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(10,23,'1','','Two numbers 5413 and 4316 when divided by a certain number of three digits, leaves the same remainder. Find the number.','293','173','263','421','3','When two numbers divided by a third number leaves the same remainder, the difference of the two numbers is also divisible by the third number.\nHere the difference is 5413 â€“ 4316 = 1052 = 4 x 263. \nSo, the required number is 263.','Easy'),(11,23,'1','','The remainder obtained when a prime number greater than 6 is divided by 6 is','1 or 3','1 or 5','3 or 5','2 or 4','2','If you divide a number by 6 and get the remainder as 2 or 4, the number is even and so will not be prime.\nIf you divide a number by 6 and get the remainder as 3, the number is divisible by 3 and so will not be prime.\nSo, the only choices left for the remainder is 1 or 5.','Easy'),(12,23,'1','','The fare of a cab is Rs. x for the first four kilometers and Rs. 10 per kilometer thereafter. If a passenger pays Rs. 245 for a journey of 19 kilometers, what is the value of X?','85','75','95','80','3','Cost for the first 4 kilometers is â€˜xâ€™ and the cost for the next 15 kilometers is 15 x 10 = Rs. 150.\nSo, the total cost is x+150=245=&gt;x=95.','Easy'),(13,23,'1','','Find the least number which when divided by 36, 48 and 64 leaves the remainders 25, 37 and 53 respectively','565','563','656','657','1','Let the least number required be k. k when divided by 36, 48 and 64 leaves the remainders 25, 37 and 53 respectively.\nSo, 36, 48 and 64 will perfectly divide (k + 11) because the remainders will be 0 in all cases.\nSo, (k + 11) is the LCM of 36, 48 and 64. So, (k +11) = 576 =&gt; k = 565.\nSo, the required number is 565.','Easy'),(14,23,'1','','In which of the following base systems is 25 doubled by reversing the digits?','12','11','8','9','3','Let the base of the number system be b. so, 25 will be equal to (2b + 5) and the number obtained by reversing the digits is (5b + 2).\nAccording to the question (5b + 2) = 2(2b + 5) =&gt; 5b + 2 = 4b + 10 =&gt; b = 8.\nIn base 8, 25 will be 21 and 52 will be 42 and so, 52 will be double of 25.','Easy'),(15,23,'1','','A boy was asked to multiply a certain number by 35, but he multiplied it by 53 and so, his answer is greater than the correct one by 288. Find the number to be multiplied.','18','10','14','16','4','Let the required number be x. Then, 53x â€“ 35x = 288 =&gt; 18x = 288 =&gt; x = 16. \nSo, the required number = 16','Easy'),(16,23,'1','','In a cricket match, Ram and Rahul scored a century each (more than 100 runs) and Ashok and Karan scored a half century each. Karan scored 84 runs and Ashok scored 31 runs less than Karan. Rahul scored 101 runs. The sum of the scores of all the four players is 372. How many runs did Ram score?','124','134','144','114','2','Score of Ram is 372 â€“ 84 â€“ 101 â€“ (84 â€“ 31) = 134 runs.','Easy'),(17,23,'1','','&lt;p&gt;The sum of square of two numbers is 74 and the square of their difference is 4. The product of the two numbers is&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;32&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;49&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;35&lt;/p&gt;','&lt;p&gt;25&lt;/p&gt;','3','&lt;p&gt;Let the numbers be a and b. Then a&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;+b&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;=74 and (a-b)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;=4 =&amp;gt;2ab=74-4=70.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, the product of the two numbers is 70/2 = 35.&lt;/p&gt;','Easy'),(18,23,'1','','How many pairs of natural numbers are there the difference of whose squares is 45?','3','2','1','0','1','484 is the square of 22 and 529 is the square of 23. The difference is 45.\n36 is the square of 6 and 81 is the square of 9. The difference is 45.\n4 is the square of 2 and 49 is the square of 7. The difference is 45. So, totally 3 pairs.','Easy'),(19,23,'1','','The H.C.F of two numbers is 10 and their L.C.M is 120. If one of the numbers is 24, then other number is','40','100','60','50','4','The product of HCF and LCM of the two numbers is equal to the product of the numbers itself.\nSo, if the second number is b, then 24b = 10 x 120 =&gt; b = 10 x 5 = 50.','Easy'),(20,23,'1','','Four prime numbers are written down in ascending order of magnitude. The product of the first three is 385 and that of the last three numbers is 1309. Find the sum of all the four prime numbers.','42','46','36','40','4','Product of the first 3 prime numbers is divisible by 5, but the product of last 3 prime numbers is not divisible by 5. So, 5 must be the first prime number.\nThe product of the remaining 2 prime numbers in the group is 385/5 = 77 = 7 x 11.\nSo, the second and third prime numbers are 7 and 11. \nThe fourth prime number will be given by 1309/77 = 17.\nSo, the required sum is 5 + 7 + 11 + 17 = 40.','Easy');

